title: braised onion sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Add onions and cook them over medium heat until they are soft and transparent.
Stir in the sugar; reduce the heat and cook, very slowly for about 1 hour.
Stir in the wine; cook briefly and pour over cooked pasta.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: manicotti with spinach and cheese crepes(12 entree crepes)
directions: Put spinach in mixing bowl with salt, pepper, garlic powder, onion powder, nutmeg, Ricotta cheese, eggs, 1 1/2 cups Jack cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Stir to mix well.
Divide mixture
evenly among crepes and roll up.
Place crepes in a single layer in greased shallow baking dish.
Cover with foil.
Dish can be refrigerated at this point.
Before serving, bake in 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Remove foil and sprinkle with remaining Jack cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes more or until cheese has melted.

title: yule bowl
directions: Stick the oranges full of the cloves and bake until soft.
Pour the rum and sugar over them and set them aflame (do this in a flameproof pot).
Extinguish with the cider, add the spices and keep hot over a low flame or in a crock pot, until ready to serve. Very elegant in a punch bowl.
Serves 10-12.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Make pudding.
Mix pudding with Cool Whip.
Chop up fruit of your choice and dip into mixture.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix
together
sugar,
salt and flour.	Add
chocolate, melted in scalded milk.
Cook until thick, then add butter and eggs. Cook
minutes longer and add vanilla.
Cool
before putting in baked pastry shell.
Top with whipped cream.

title: chili verde
directions: Put all in crock-pot without water.
Cook on low for 3 to 4 hours.
Before serving, add flour and water for gravy.
(If not hot enough, add 1/4 to 1/2 teaspoon crushed red pepper.)
Adjust seasonings to taste.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Stew chicken with salt, onion and celery.
Bone and cut chicken into small pieces.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Place broccoli in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Place chicken in next.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder, salt and pepper. Pour over broccoli and chicken.
Top with bread crumbs and cheese. Cook, covered, 45 minutes or until bubbly in 350° oven.
Freezes well.
Thaw and cook.

title: mrs. lewis' meat loaf
directions: Steam cook for 1 1/2 hours in electric skillet.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as package directs and drain well.
Mix in celery, onion, cheese and salad dressing.
Put in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle herb-seasoned crumbs on top and cover with margarine.

title: eclair dessert squares
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch buttered pan with whole graham crackers.
Make pudding according to package directions, then mix with Cool Whip. Pour half the pudding mixture over the graham crackers.
Place another layer of crackers over the pudding and top with remaining pudding.
Cover layer with graham crackers.
Top with chocolate icing and refrigerate for 2 days.

title: stuffed baked potato
directions: Bake 6 large potatoes 1 1/2 hours at 400 degrees.
Cut lengthwise into halves.
Scoop out the potato leaving the skin intact.
Mash all the potatoes in a bowl and add all ingredients with the exception of the cheddar cheese and dash of paprika, till fluffy.
Can add a small amount of milk if needed, but do not get this mixture too loose.

title: party punch
directions: Mix and pour into punch bowl over ice ring.

title: cyclops cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat butter and peanut butter with electric mixer until smooth.
Add the 1/2 cup sugar and brown sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add the egg, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Mix the cookie mix as directed on the box.
Put into a deep pie plate.
Cook until done; let cool.
Mix the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla; spread over the cookie.
Add your favorite fruit slices on top.

title: mary's brownies
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar and mix well.
Melt together the margarine and chocolate; cool slightly and add to first mixture.
Mix together dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes.

title: cherry sherbet punch
directions: Combine Kool-Aid with water, stirring until dissolved.
Add sugar and juice of 1 lemon.
Slice lemon thinly and add to mixture.
Stir until all ingredients are well blended.
Place the 3 scoops of sherbet on top of the punch (it will blend in).
Serve well chilled.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli while preparing or earlier in the day.
Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Fill 9 x 13-inch pan with Tater Tots (enough to cover bottom of pan).
Cook Tater Tots as directed on bag.
Let broccoli thaw.
Put ground beef on top of Tater Tots. Put broccoli atop beef.
Mix milk and soup; pour over layers.
Top with cheese and bake for 35 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve when slightly cooled.

title: chutney glaze
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Baste on ham last 45 minutes of baking, basting frequently.

title: fire "n" see pickles
directions: Drain pickles.
In large dishpan mix pickles, sugar, garlic, hot sauce and red pepper.
Let stand for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
After this, put back into pickle jar with new pickle juice.
Refrigerate.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut shortening into dry mixture.
Add enough water to make soft dough, but not sticky.
Knead well. Let stand about 30 minutes.
Roll out into 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into 3-inch squares.
Fry in deep fat.
Serve with honey.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thinly slice the potatoes (about 1/4-inch).
Add to salted water and boil 5 minutes.
Drain.
In mixing bowl, whisk together the soups and milk.
Add onions, pimentos and pepper to taste.
Spray a 2 or 3-quart oblong casserole with nonstick spray.
Put potatoes in bottom of casserole.
Put all other ingredients on potatoes and top with cheese.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 9 x 13-inch baking dish with tortillas.
Brown ground beef with onion.
Mix soup, beans and tomatoes.
Layer meat on top of tortillas.
Next add layer of soup mixture.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake until bubbly hot.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream; add vanilla.
Don't overbeat.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350° in a greased and floured Bundt or angel food pan.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In center of each tortilla, place 1/4 cup chicken, 2 tablespoons cheese and 1 tablespoon salsa; roll up. Arrange seam side down in 8-inch square baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake 25 minutes or until heated.

title: oven roasted garlic potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash potatoes.
Place potatoes in small roasting pan.
Drizzle olive oil over potatoes.
Sprinkle garlic, salt and pepper over potatoes.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes, until tender and browned.

title: pineapple banana deluxe salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add 7-Up.
When partly set, add pineapple, marshmallows and sliced bananas.
When completely set, spread topping.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat until mixture is smooth. Bake in a well-greased cake pan in moderate oven 350° for 45 minutes. Ice cake while hot.

title: granny's sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to sugar and egg mixture.
Roll out and cut out various shapes.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
When cool, frost with powdered sugar and lemon glaze that has been tinted an appropriate color.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour, cinnamon soda, salt, baking powder and nutmeg.
In another bowl, combine zucchini, sugar, cooking oil and lemon peel.
Mix well. Add flour mixture. Stir just until combined. Stir in nut meats.
Pour batter into loaf pan, 8 x 4 x 2-inch. Bake in a 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes on wire rack. Remove from pan.
Let cool and wrap.
Let stand overnight before slicing.

title: snickerdoodles cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and blend well.
Stir together dry ingredients and stir into mixture until well mixed. Roll into balls the size of small walnuts and roll into mixture of 2 teaspoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Bake until light brown.
These cookies puff up at first, then flatten out.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Press coconut and pecans into bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix and pour on top of this.
Mix the cream cheese, oleo and powdered sugar.
Drop by spoonfuls on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: plate of pasta
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add broccoli and can of chicken broth.
Then add parsley, oregano, basil, salt and peppers.
Bring to simmer for 10 minutes or until broccoli is done. Pour over cooked pasta, toss and serve.

title: lima beans in sour cream
directions: Cook beans until tender.
Rinse in hot water.
Put in a large, greased casserole dish.
Add butter, salt, brown sugar, mustard, molasses and sour cream.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale.
Chill.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.

title: butterscotch cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass pan).
In medium saucepan, melt morsels and butter.
Stir in crumbs and nuts. Press half of mixture firmly onto bottom of heavily greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: annie's pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine, butter and Crisco.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour, baking powder and milk alternately, ending with flour.
Fold in flavoring on low speed.
Bake in a tube pan for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 275°.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms and finely chop to 1/3 cup.
Cook and stir stems, onion and pepper in 3 tablespoons margarine until tender (5 minutes).
Remove from heat; stir in crumbs, salt, thyme, turmeric and pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon margarine in shallow baking dish until melted.
Fill caps.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°, broil setting or at 550° 3 to 4 inches from heat for 2 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: just-like campbell's tomato soup
directions: Saute onions in oleo; stir in flour, salt, pepper and sugar. Cook until smooth and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir in tomato juice.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Fill jars and cook 30 minutes.

title: millionaire cake
directions: Mix together and beat with spoon for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Prepare and
bake
cake according to directions on box. Cut the 2 layers in half to make 4 layers.
Mix other ingredients; frost cake and refrigerate for 2 days.

title: las vegas cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, margarine and eggs.
Pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream together cream cheese, powdered sugar, eggs and nuts.
Pour on top of other mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a 9 x 13-inch buttered glass pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
The last few minutes of baking, put crushed potato chips and a little grated cheese on top.
Freezes well.
Any vegetable can be substituted for beans. Serves 12 people.

title: nanny's dump cake
directions: You will need a long pan, 2 1/2-inches deep, 13-inches long by 9-inches wide, metal (may have to cook longer).

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a 3 quart greased casserole dish.
Pour mix over the top of ingredients and bake at 375° for 45 minutes to an hour or until golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: layered salad
directions: In order given, layer in 9 X 13 pan. Mix: 2 cups mayonnaise, 2 Tbsp. sugar, 2 Tbsp. Parmesan cheese. Spread over salad as frosting. Top with 4 oz. grated cheddar cheese. Cover lightly with plastic wrap. Refrigerate overnight.

title: peanut butter dip for fruit
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve with slices of apples, pears, bananas, etc.

title: mushroom delight
directions: Simmer onions in margarine until soft.
Add chopped celery and sliced mushrooms.
Simmer together 3 minutes.
Add soup and flavor packet from noodles.
Add boiled noodles.
Combine all in casserole; top with cashews.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350° (don't overbake).

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cube about a large walnut size.
Put in ice water and let stand at least 1 hour.
Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put Parmesan cheese and flour in a paper bag and shake.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Remove potatoes from ice water and put in bag; shake good.
Arrange in the melted buttered baking dish.
Bake at 400°.
After 1/2 hour, turn and continue baking for another 1/2 hour.
Serves approximately 6 to 8.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Cream 1/2 cup sugar and the shortening.
Add the next 4 ingredients; beat until smooth.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan or baking dish.
Pour onto this batter the berries with the juice and 1/2 cup sugar.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
The crust will rise to the top.

title: settler beans
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Crumble bacon and add with onion to meat.
Place in a casserole dish; add remaining ingredients. Mix and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: crescent cheeseburgers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large frying pan, brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in chili sauce, soup mix, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Spoon hot meat mixture over triangles.
Roll up; start at shortest side of triangle and roll to form 2 triangles.
Place a cheese triangle over each meat-filled crescent.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 to 17 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 8 sandwiches.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions.
Cook bacon until crisp; crumble.
Add onion, green pepper and mushrooms to bacon fat and cook until tender.
Stir in flour, chicken broth, cream and pimiento.
Simmer until sauce thickens.
Add salt and pepper. Combine sauce, chicken, bacon and cooked spaghetti.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: green chili sauce
directions: Cook on top of stove until desired thickness.

title: chicken meatballs
directions: About 1 hour before serving, preheat oven to 400°. Grease 13 x 9-inch metal baking pan. Chop bread until fine crumbs form (you will have about 1 cup crumbs). Grate enough onion to equal 1 tablespoon. Finely shred carrots to equal 1/2 cup. In large bowl, mix bread crumbs, onion, shredded carrots, ground chicken, salt and 1 tablespoon chopped parsley. Shape chicken mixture into 20 meatballs. (Meatball mixture is very moist and sticky; for easier shaping, use wet hands.) Place meatballs in baking pan; bake 25 minutes or until meatballs are lightly browned and cooked through.

title: sausage meatballs
directions: Combine sausage, bread crumbs, egg, celery and onion in a bowl; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: apple nut bread
directions: Cream shortening with sugar. Add eggs and beat well. Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with apples.
Add nuts. Pour in loaf pan and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: salmon caesar
directions: In medium bowl, beat together eggs, milk and soup.
Stir in croutons, flaked salmon, green pepper and onion.
Pour into buttered 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set in center.

title: marinated mussels(cozze di marinati)
directions: Drain and rinse mussels.
In saucepan combine celery, 2 tablespoons minced onion, garlic,
parsley, 1/2 cup olive oil, vinegar, pepper, salt and onion.
Bring
to
a boil and remove from heat.
Add mussels
to
hot
liquid;
cool.
Let marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Arrange a small platter with a bed of lettuce, if desired.
Place mussels on platter and sprinkle chopped garlic and sliced onion
on
top.
Pour
some
of
the marinade over top of mussels
along with the olive oil.
Serve with garlic bread or
on
an
antipasto
platter,
if desired. Makes 6 servings.

title: papa wood's "sugar popcorn"
directions: Scoop out the seeds from the pumpkin.
Wash the seeds.
Pat dry on a paper towel.
Salt the seeds.
Grease a cookie sheet with 1 to 2 tablespoons butter.
Spread seeds on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until seeds are golden brown and crispy.

title: hot slaw(as told to me by my mother)
directions: Put 1 stick of butter in pan and cut cabbage (pepper and salt it).
Cook until tender.
Mix together a scant tablespoon of flour,
vinegar,
sugar
and milk.	Set cabbage off after it has become tender and pour this mixture over it, return to cook until flour is cooked but do not boil.
MMMMMMMM GOOD!

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Stir together jam and buttermilk.
Freeze firm.
Break up mixture:
whip until fluffy and refreeze.
Enjoy.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add soy sauce and water.
Simmer 2 minutes. Add celery and onion and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Will need 1 cup water to thicken.
Blend cornstarch and water to thicken and add remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve with rice or chow mein noodles.

title: reuben sandwich
directions: Place corned beef, then sauerkraut, Miracle Whip and cheese on 4 slices of bread.
Top with other bread slices.
Spread butter on outside of bread.
Grill in skillet or on griddle until browned and cheese melts.

title: chilli bake
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Mix with chilli and tomatoes.
Pour into a 9 x 11-inch baking dish. Mix corn meal, egg and milk.
Pour over top of chilli mix.
Bake at 450° until top is brown and cornbread done.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt caramels in evaporated milk.
Pour evenly over baked layer of cake and sprinkle with milk chocolate chips and chopped nuts.
Pour remaining batter over top.
Return to oven and bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes.
Check cake by inserting a toothpick in center.
It should come out clean.

title: apple salad
directions: Layer the first 4 ingredients in a dish in order listed.
The remaining ingredients will be cooked for a sauce.
Combine remaining ingredients in pan; cook over low heat until thick.
Cool and pour over Apple Salad.
Mix together just before serving.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Mix egg, flour, pudding and butter to make crust.
Spread on bottom of pan and pour drained peaches on top.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and 3 tablespoons of peach juice until creamy.
Pour over peaches.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° until crust is golden brown.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O.
Stir in cream cheese while hot.
Add all ingredients.
Cool a bit and stir in whipped cream.
Chill until firm.

title: marinated pasta salad
directions: Marinate in refrigerator overnight before serving.
I stir several times during first few hours to make sure seasonings get into pasta.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Saute onion, pepper and mushrooms in Italian dressing.
Push to one side.
Cook chicken in Italian dressing just until no longer pink inside.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Place chicken in 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine all ingredients, except for cornstarch and water.
Pour over chicken. Cook at Medium-high (70%) for 20 minutes, until chicken is done, turning after 10 minutes.
Remove chicken and cover to keep warm.

title: preserved children
directions: Mix the children and dogs well together.
Put them on the field, stirring constantly.
Pour the brook over the pebbles, sprinkle the field with flowers and spread over all a deep blue sky and bake in the sun.
When brown, set away to cool in the bathtub.

title: reese's brownies
directions: Prepare Duncan Hines double fudge brownie mix as written on box.
Place either 2-inch or 2 1/4-inch foiled cupcake papers on a cookie sheet or in muffin tins.
Fill each cupcake paper 3/4 full.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Melt 1/2 stick butter and saute vegetables until transparent. Add the remaining ingredients and cook 5 minutes.
Add cut up chicken.
Cook slowly for 3 to 4 hours, covered.
Cook 2 (7 ounce) packages spaghetti.
Add to mixture.
If too dry, add more broth. May add small can mushrooms and/or ripe olives and 1/2 pound grated cheese.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Combine cornstarch, soy sauce, vinegar, sugar, ginger and garlic powder; set aside.
In wok or large skillet, stir-fry chicken in hot oil for 2 or 3 minutes.
Add peppers and cook 3 minutes.
Add pineapple and juice, then stir in cornstarch mixture.
Cook over low heat and stir until slightly thickened. Serve over rice.

title: smothered steak
directions: Put steak, flour, salt and pepper in crock-pot.
Stir well. Layer the remaining ingredients in order.
Do not stir while simmering in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on high for 1 hour.
Then low for 8 hours or on high for 5 hours.
Stir together when ready to serve it over rice.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Bake chicken breasts at 350° for 60 minutes.
Remove skin and bones.
Cut into strips.
Cook broccoli as directed on package. Place in well-buttered casserole dish; lay chicken strips on top. Mix soup with mayonnaise and pour it on top of chicken.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs, then cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: strawberry angel food cake
directions: Break angel food cake into pieces in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Dissolve jello in 2 cups of boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries.
Pour jello over the cake in the pan.
Press the mixture into the cake.
Refrigerate about 3 hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit well then mix all ingredients together.
Let sit in refrigerator overnight for best flavor.
Makes a lot. Recipe may be halved.

title: mounds coconut candy
directions: Melt butter and mix with sugar and Eagle Brand milk until smooth.
Remove from heat and add coconut.
Line a pan with wax paper.
Roll mixture into balls and freeze until firm.
(If you need to wait for the pans, refrigerate until ready to use again.) Melt chocolate and paraffin and dip coconut ball in the mixture. Put on wax paper until firm.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa and stir into hot milk.
Cook until thick.
Add beaten egg yolks, stirring well.
Add vanilla and oleo and beat again.
Pour into baked crust.
Top with whipped egg whites made from 3 egg whites and bake.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift together the first five ingredients.
Add Crisco oil, eggs, vanilla and grated zucchini.
May add nuts and raisins, if desired.
Mix ingredients.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with chilled raw vegetables or with crackers or bread.
Makes 3 cups.
Can be made a day ahead to blend flavors.

title: shimmering tropical fruit
directions: Drain Tropical fruit salad; reserve juice.
Add enough water to make 1 3/4 cups liquid.
Heat liquid to boiling.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Stir in fruit salad.
Pour in 1-quart mold or 8 foil muffin pan liners.
Chill until firm.
Unmold onto plate to serve.
Garnish as desired. Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy microwave chocolate fudge
directions: Melt butter in a large bowl, then combine sugar, cocoa and milk; microwave for 2 minutes.
Stir well and add vanilla and nuts. Refrigerate until set, about 2 hours.
Kids and men love this candy!

title: chicken and linguine
directions: Put flour, salt and pepper in a paper bag.
Take chicken, one piece at a time, place in bag and shake until chicken is coated with flour mixture.
Brown coated chicken in olive oil.
When all of the chicken is brown, drain off excess oil.
Sprinkle onion soup over chicken.
Pour wine and water over chicken.
Simmer, covered, over low heat for 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: quesadilla(1 serving)
directions: Heat oil in a nonstick skillet; add 1 tortilla. Layer with half the Cheddar cheese, all of the chicken and mushrooms and half the Monterey Jack cheese. Top with the second tortilla. Cover and heat until cheese melts and bottom tortilla is crisp and golden brown. Turn over; sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Cook until bottom tortilla is crisp and golden brown and cheese is melted. Cut into wedges; serve with sour cream and salsa, if desired.

title: mary ollie's wedding punch
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Before adding the ginger ale, pour out a portion of the punch into a container to freezer.
Serve the punch over the frozen punch.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Mix together the margarine, flour and nuts. Press into bottom of 13x9 pan. Bake in 350 degree oven for 20 minutes. Cool thoroughly.

title: no fail! pie crust
directions: Whip 1 cup softened butter.
Gradually add 1/3 plus cup milk. Mix flour with salt and sugar.
Add flour mix.
Do not overmix. Consistency should be coherent, but not too sticky dough.
(Can finish mixing with hands.)
Let rest 1 hour minimum in ball.
Roll out with minimum of flour on floured surface.
Brush with egg mixture.
Sprinkle cinnamon/sugar on top if wanted.

title: christmas cranberry-orange salad
directions: In large bowl, dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in cranberry sauce, cold water, lemon juice, cinnamon and cloves. Refrigerate about 1 1/2 hours or until thickened, then stir in the oranges.
Pour into a 5-cup mold or glass dish.
Refrigerate until completely firm.

title: flour icing
directions: Cook flour and milk to thick paste. Refrigerate 1 hour. Beat shortening, vanilla and sugar until creamy. Mix with flour paste and whip until thick.

title: play dough
directions: Cook on medium heat until dough is right consistency for use (about 3 to 5 minutes).
Stir constantly while cooking.
When it thickens and pulls away from the sides of the pan, pour out on countertop and knead for 1 minute.
Store in plastic bag.

title: chicken and pasta toss
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Rinse under cold running water; drain.
In medium salad bowl, combine pasta, spinach, chicken, cherry tomatoes, mushrooms and Parmesan cheese.
In small bowl, whisk together oil, mustard, lemon juice, garlic salt, 3 tablespoons water and 1/8 teaspoon pepper until smooth.
Pour over pasta mixture; toss lightly.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: texas sheet cake and frosting
directions: In large bowl, mix flour, sugar and salt.
Bring to boil margarine, water and cocoa.
In small bowl, mix eggs, milk, vinegar, vanilla and soda.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl. Pour into greased sheet cake pan (11 x 18 x 1-inch).
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: harvard beet spice cake
directions: Beat butter with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Blend beets in blender until smooth.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with beets to butter mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Fold in nuts.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Beat lemonade and Cool Whip together for 2 minutes.
Add the sweetened condensed milk; beat with other ingredients for about 3 minutes.
Pour into shell; refrigerate several hours.

title: delicious cookies
directions: Preheat oven at 325°.
Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients except pecans.
Mix until combined.
Stir in pecans.
Form into balls the size of a walnut.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly brown.
Do not overcook. Let cool before removing from pan.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Soften cheese and margarine. Add flour. Mixture will be very stiff. Form into ball and store covered in refrigerator for 1 hour. Shape into 24 one-inch (walnut size) balls. Place in tiny ungreased muffin tins. Press against bottom and sides of cup to form small pastry cups.

title: edwards mansion orange muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking powder in large mixing bowl.
Add the following ingredients in the order given, one at a time, while stirring: shortening, soft butter, beaten eggs, milk and orange juice.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Brown beef until crumbly, but not dry.
Before beef is done, push to one side of pan and saute onion, green pepper and celery. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover pan tightly and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve hot over toasted buns. Serves 6 to 8.

title: teresa's broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate.

title: mom's fudge sauce
directions: Mix together butter and cocoa.
Add sugar, 1/2 cup at a time. Over low heat, gradually add evaporated milk.
Bring to boil and continue to boil for 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir often.
Add vanilla. Remove from heat and serve.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chicken and rice pilaf
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking dish.
Mix dressing and preserves and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle on onion soup.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese log
directions: In serving dish, layer the following ingredients in this order:
Frito Lay bean dip, guacamole, sour cream, chopped tomatoes, chopped black olives, shredded Cheddar cheese and chopped green onions.
Chill and serve.
Scoop bites with corn chips.

title: alene's meringue
directions: Add water before beating.
Beat until foamy, but not stiff. Then add 8 tablespoons of sugar, one tablespoon at a time, beating well between each addition.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Cut in shortening. Dissolve yeast in the 4 tablespoons very warm water. Add yeast and buttermilk to the flour mixture. Mix well. Place in refrigerator to chill. When ready to bake, roll out to 1/4-inch thickness on a well floured board, using a floured rolling pin. Cut with a 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter. Dip into melted butter and fold over to make "pocketbooks." Place on ungreased baking sheet or pan. Bake in 400° oven until lightly browned. Dough does not have to rise before baking and will keep in the refrigerator for a couple of days.

title: beef tater bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Make an even layer of uncooked ground beef in bottom of 9-inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with onion slices.
Add 1 layer of frozen Tater Tots, completely covering beef and onions.
Add soup, pouring it evenly over mixture.
Top with grated cheese. Bake 1 hour.
Cut into squares.
Serves 6.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Crumble sausage into a large saucepan.
Cook over medium-low heat.
Add onion; cook and stir until transparent.
Drain, discarding all but 3 tablespoons of the drippings.
Stir in flour. Cook over medium-low heat about 8 minutes or until mixture turns golden.
Slowly add milk.
Add seasonings and cook, stirring until thick.
To serve, slice biscuits and spoon gravy over halves. Serves 6.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Stir together dry ingredients, add eggs.
Slowly stir in buttermilk and then butter.
Add raisins.
Bake 1 hour, 10 minutes in greased loaf pan at 350°.

title: jalapeno pie
directions: Line pie plate with jalapenos.
Cover with grated sharp Cheddar cheese.
Heap and round to top of pan.
Beat eggs and pour over top of cheese.
Bake at 275° for 45 minutes.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Melt butter and sugar.
Cool.
Add unbeaten eggs and mix well. Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a greased shallow pan at 325° to 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Cream butter and sugar gradually and cream until light and fluffy. Add extract. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Alternately add flour mixture and milk, beating until blended after each addition. Wrap dough into foil or plastic wrap and chill several hours. Roll out part of the dough at a time, 1/8-inch thick on floured board. Cut with 2 1/2-inch cookie cutters. Sprinkle with granulated sugar and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes until edges are brown. Cool on racks. Makes 6 dozen.

title: chicken soup (greek egg-lemon soup)(greek; heart healthy.)
directions: Cover fowl with water and chicken broth and heat gradually to boiling point with onion and celery. Cook until fowl is tender, about 1 1/2 hours, adding salt when half done. Remove fowl from broth and set aside on warm platter. Strain broth; bring to boiling point. Stir in rice; cover and simmer over moderate heat until rice is cooked. Stir the contents frequently while rice is cooking. Cool soup slightly and blend with the following Egg-Lemon recipe. Serve immediately. Makes 6 servings.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add 1 egg at a time; beat until smooth.
Add flour gradually; beat until smooth.
Add flavoring (of your choice).
Add 7-Up.
Pour into greased cake pan.
Bake in a 350° oven (preheated) for 40 minutes.

title: cranberry fluff
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and let stand 12 hours in refrigerator.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix all ingredients, except the margarine.
Melt margarine in pan.
Leave some margarine in pan, put the rest in the mix.
Cook in an oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: tapioca jello salad
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients together until thick; let cool. Mix the Dream Whip according to package directions.
Add the Dream Whip, drained pineapple and oranges to the cooled jello.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into balls the size of walnut. Place on shallow baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Spread pie filling in bottom of a 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine dry cake mix, nuts and butter.
Mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle over pie filling.
Bake 40 minutes or until golden brown at 350°.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: ritz cracker pie(1 pie)
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Add sugar like angel food cake.
Add rest of ingredients.

title: stack cake
directions: Cream together the sugar and shortening.
Add egg, molasses and buttermilk and mix well.
Sift together the flour, soda, salt, baking powder and ginger and add to the other mixture.
Mix well. Add vanilla.
It makes a dough.
Divide into 5 equal balls and roll out as for pastry to fit 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool and stack with dried apples.

title: brown sugar fudge cake
directions: Cream shortening and gradually add sugar beating at medium speed.
Add eggs beating well after each addition, then add chocolate and beat well.
Combine flour, soda and add to cream mixture stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 8 inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until a toothpick is inserted in center and comes out clean.
Cool on wire racks spread creamy chocolate frosting between layers and on top.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Spoon into prepared pie crust. Cover with top crust; crimp edges to seal.
Slit top crust.
Bake at 370° for 40 minutes.

title: hunan vegetables(hot and sour)
directions: Combine ginger, garlic and black beans in a small bowl and set aside.
Blend stock, soy sauce, vinegar and sugar in another bowl. Bring pot of water to boil.
Fill another bowl with ice water. Blanch cauliflower for 1 minute, then plunge into ice water. Repeat process with remaining vegetables.

title: cheese stars
directions: Mix together cheese and margarine.
Sift together flour, salt and pepper.
Combine and chill in refrigerator.
Roll out like cookie dough and cut into small star shapes with a cutter.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: oyster stew
directions: Heat milk and cream just to scalding in a medium size saucepan.
Stir in corn and liquid, salt, paprika, pepper and thyme.
Saute green onions in butter slowly.
Then add oysters and liqueur; cook slowly for 5 minutes or just until edges of oysters start to curl.
Stir into the scalded milk mixture.
Heat very slowly, just to boiling.

title: chow chow
directions: Combine all the chopped vegetables in a large kettle and mix well. Sprinkle with salt and allow to stand overnight.
The next day, drain off liquid.
Tie pickling spices in a piece of cloth or cheesecloth.
Combine the vinegar, sugar, pickling spice bag and all other spices in a large kettle.
Simmer 20 minutes. Add the vegetables to the mixture and cook over low heat until almost reaches boiling point.
Pack the hot chow chow in hot sterilized jars and seal at once.
Allow to stand 2 weeks before eating.

title: lemon yam puff
directions: Cook unpeeled whole yams in boiling water for 30 minutes or until tender; drain.
Peel and mash until
smooth.
If dry, add a little hot water.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until light and fluffy.
Transfer to a greased 2-quart casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Melt margarine in large, shallow pan. Stir in salts and Worcestershire sauce.
Add cereal, pretzels, pecans and peanuts; mix until all pieces are coated.
Bake for 1 hour.
Spread on paper towels and allow to cool.
Store in airtight containers.

title: creamy summer fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate 15 minutes before serving. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: In a medium bowl, combine spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise, soup mix, water chestnuts and green onions.
Cover; chill.
Serve with bread, crackers, chips, etc.
Makes 3 cups.

title: carrots au gratin
directions: Heat oven to
Cook
carrots
in 1/2-inch boiling salted water for
minutes.
Combine
crackers, onion salt, green pepper and
black
pepper.
Alternate
carrots and crumb mixtures in greased 1 quart baking dish.
If any carrot liquid is left, spoon over
top.
Pour
butter over and sprinkle with cheese. Bake 20 or 25 minutes or until cheese melts.
(Can be made the day ahead, and then put in oven when ready to use.)

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Mix well in large bowl all ingredients. (May have to add more bread crumbs if mushy.) Put in bottom of Dutch oven or large type pan and add water to the bottom 1 inch. Cook at 350 degrees for 1/2 hour covered, uncover and cook additional 1/2 hour. Add catsup to top of meat loaf during last 1/2 hour, if desired.

title: bread pudding
directions: Arrange toast in buttered dish (use deep dish).
Break into pieces if you must.
Sprinkle with raisins; stir the rest altogether (except 2 tablespoons of sugar).
Pour over toast and let stand (10 minutes).
Keep pushing down in milk mix so it soaks up milk.
Mix cinnamon and sugar and sprinkle over top.
Cook at 350° until top is brown and knife comes out clean when tested, 25 minutes is good timing.
Serve warm or cold with vanilla sauce (very good) if desired.

title: sensational beef stroganoff
directions: Slice beef across the grain (will slice more easily if frozen 1 hour), very thin slices.
Cook 1/2 the beef with 1/2 the onion in 1 tablespoon oleo in a skillet over high heat.
Remove from skillet and repeat with remainder of beef, onion and oleo.
Return all beef to skillet.
Stir in soup and paprika.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat; stir in sour cream.
Heat through.
Serve over noodles.

title: hot ham and cheese rolls
directions: Cut ham and cheese into 1/4-inch cubes.
Chop eggs; combine all ingredients.
Spread into 12 frankfurter rolls.
Wrap in foil and heat in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix milks and pudding mix; fold in Cool Whip.

title: bountiful bean stew
directions: Rinse beans.
Cover with water; boil 2 minutes.
Let stand 1 hour, then simmer, covered, 50 minutes until beans are tender. Add all the rest of the ingredients except cheese.
Simmer 30 minutes until carrots are done.
Stir in cheese just before serving.
Serves 8.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients together. Spread on bottom of dish, then spread apples over this.
Mix the 1/2 cup flour and 1/2 cup sugar together and spread over the apples.
Melt the butter and pour on top. Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and part of onion.
Drain.
Add kidney beans and taco seasoning.
Simmer.
Combine lettuce, tomatoes, remaining onions, and cheese in large bowl.
When ready to serve, add Fritos, ground beef mixture, and dressing.
Mix well and serve.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, oil and vanilla.
Beat until soft and fluffy.
Combine all dry ingredients and stir gradually to creamed mixture.
Chill for 4 hours or longer.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with glass or fork dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: mama's dumplings
directions: Combine flours and egg.
Add enough cold water to make a stiff dough.
Drop into boiling chicken broth.
You may drop them from a teaspoon or roll them out using a little self-rising flour. Reduce heat to medium and cook until tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: cornstarch cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar well together; add the milk, then the cornstarch and flour sifted with the salt and baking powder. Add last the whites of the eggs beaten to a stiff froth.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Use rather shallow pans.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and drain. Add seasonings and stir well. Add other ingredients. Cook on low for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Serve over taco chips or Mexican cornbread. Top with sour cream and/or grated cheese.

title: russian tea
directions: Simmer water, cinnamon and cloves for 5 minutes.
Add fruit juices, tea and sugar.
Don't boil, just simmer!

title: mexicali chili
directions: Brown beef.
Add to beef and cook until tender the onion, pepper, garlic and chili powder.
Add soups, water, cheese and salt.
Cook over low heat for 20 minutes, stirring often.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Measure water into large bowl with cover, sprinkle dry yeast and dissolve in water.
Add margarine, sugar and egg in order listed; blend well.
Add flour slowly and blend well.
Cover bowl and store in refrigerator until 1 1/2 hours before serving time. Spoon dough into greased muffin pan and let double in size.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.
Serve hot.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: crunchy chicken breasts
directions: Dip chicken in oil. Roll in crushed Cheese Nips. Place in casserole dish. Cook at 375° for an hour, turning chicken halfway through cooking time.

title: spicy shrimp and noodle soup
directions: Thaw shrimp, if frozen.
Peel and devein.
In medium bowl, combine lemon juice, chili powder, cumin and pepper.
Add shrimp. Toss to coat.
Let shrimp stand for 20 minutes at room temperature, stirring occasionally.

title: fudge
directions: Place powdered sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in mixing bowl. Cook for three minutes in microwave on high, covered loosely. Remove bowl and mix with spoon to completely blend ingredients. Add vanilla, nuts and marshmallows.
Pour into a greased 9 inch paper plate and allow to cool 40 minutes in refrigerator before serving.

title: baked cabbage rolls
directions: Scald cabbage in salted hot water; drain well.
Mix remaining ingredients and form 12 to 14 beef balls.
Place in cabbage leaves; fold and roll up.
Fasten with toothpicks.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Pour 1 1/2 cups water over cabbage rolls and cover. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover; bake for 15 minutes, until golden brown.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Cook milk, sugar, cocoa, and margarine until margarine melts. Stir in peanut butter, vanilla, and oats.
Mix all together and drop on wax paper.
Cool until firm.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms and remove stems.
Saute mushroom caps in butter (both sides) and drain well.
Combine the bacon, olives and juice in food processor.
Stuff mixture into caps.
Place on baking sheet.
Sprinkle cheese on top of each.
Heat broiler to 500° and place in oven for 5 minutes.

title: garden pizza
directions: Flatten the crescent rolls in a large jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix the cream cheese with the salad dressing.
Mix with seasoned salt, garlic powder and oregano. Place mixture on cooled crust.
Top with whatever vegetables you desire.
Spread the cheese on top.
Refrigerate 2 hours ahead. Keeps 3 to 4 days in refrigerator.

title: overnight casserole
directions: Put altogether; soak overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lite strawberry fruit dip
directions: Mix strawberries in blender.
Fold in Cool Whip and Sweet 'N Low.
Chill.

title: peaches n' cream cheesecake
directions: Combine flour, pudding mix, baking powder, salt, egg, milk and butter in large mixing bowl.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 10-inch deep dish pie plate.
Drain peaches well. Arrange peach slices decoratively atop batter.

title: bet's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Combine ingredients.
Bring to a boil; simmer at least 30 minutes.

title: hamburger chop suey
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet.
Drain grease.
Add diced celery, bean sprouts, bouillon, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes.
Make a smooth paste of cornstarch, brown sugar and soy sauce.
Stir into meat and cook another 10 minutes or until sauce is slightly thick.
Serve hot over Chinese noodles or rice.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Cook onion in butter until tender. Add cheese and soup.
Stir until melted.
Place broccoli in a casserole dish and pour soup mixture over.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and cold milk until thickened.
Add sweetened condensed milk and then fold in Cool Whip.
Let set until thickened.
Layer cookies, bananas and then pudding.
Add another layer of cookies, bananas and pudding.
Top with cookie crumbs, if desired.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Layer potatoes in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Melt butter in saucepan with onion and salt.
Pour butter mixture over potatoes and bake for 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Sprinkle cheese over potatoes, then parsley. Bake for 15 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Remove bones from chicken and arrange in oblong casserole dish. Sprinkle with the onion, coarsely chopped.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese (or other cheese).
Combine Ro-Tel tomatoes and soups.
Pour over mixture in casserole.
Top with crushed Doritos. Bake at 400° about 40 minutes.
For extra spice, decorate with rings of jalapeno pepper before serving or serve with picante sauce.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients in a large bowl; blend until smooth.
Pour mixture into a large greased slightly pan; bake 1 hour at 350°. In my oven, it bakes in about 50 minutes.

title: fresh tomato sauce
directions: Chop tomatoes, removing seeds.
Saute onion in margarine. Stir in tomatoes, garlic, parsley, salt, basil and pepper.
Puree mixture in food processor or blender.
Serve over pasta or fresh vegetables.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: meatballs for spaghetti
directions: Blend all together; form into balls, dropping into boiling sauce.
Cook for 3 to 4 minutes before stirring (because if you stir as you drop you can form balls).
Cook for 20 to 25 minutes until done.

title: corn casserole
directions: Retain 3 to 4 tablespoons liquid and put over corn.
Put corn in greased casserole and add liquid.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread over corn.
Crush 1 package crackers and mix with 1 stick melted oleo and spread over top of casserole.
Cook in 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes or until well browned.

title: spoon bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs.
Add the rest of the ingredients into buttered casserole.
Bake 1 hour until toothpick comes out dry.
Enjoy.

title: play dough for kids
directions: Mix all ingredients together in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture gathers on spoon and forms dough.
This will take about 6 minutes.
Dump onto waxed paper until cool enough to handle and knead to form a pliable mass. Store in covered container or plastic bag.
Food coloring may be added to make different colors.
Yields 2 pounds play dough.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cook and stir chicken in hot oil in large skillet until well browned.
Add peppers, cook and stir for 1 to 2 minutes.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Pour small bottle of Italian dressing over mixture and refrigerate overnight.
Drain excess liquid the next day, if needed.
Add jar of salsa.

title: bacon sandwich
directions: Get an apple (make sure there is no worm holes).
Get a knife. Peel off skin.
Get peanut butter.
Take your knife and put peanut butter on your apple.
Be sure to clean up your mess before your Mom sees it!

title: danna's chewy bar cookies
directions: Cream the butter.
Gradually add sugars, beating well.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture, stirring well.
Stir in vanilla and pecans. Spread in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 30 minutes.
Cut into 2 x 1-inch bars; cool on wire racks.
Yields about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into serving pieces.
Season with salt and pepper and roll in flour.
Heat oil in large skillet or Dutch oven.
Brown meat on both sides.
Add onion, celery, green pepper, tomato soup and water.
Simmer on low flame about 45 minutes or until meat is tender.

title: artichoke salad
directions: Combine ingredients in layers in a large salad bowl.
Spoon small amount of artichoke oil over salad; refrigerate.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Cook everything together over a double boiler until thick and smooth.
Pour into pint jar.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together. Pour over berries. Bake at 350 degrees until done.

title: french pecans
directions: Beat egg white, brown sugar and vanilla.
Dip pecans in mixture.
Place
on
a greased cookie sheet.
Bake one hour at 225°.

title: "diet" breakfast tortilla
directions: Microwave potato for 2 minutes and dice.
Scramble egg.
Spray pan with cooking spray (Pam) and brown onion and diced potato together.
Place egg and potato mixture in a warm flour tortilla. Serve with picante sauce.
Food exchanges:
1 protein, 1 1/2 breads, 1 fat.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Spread the pie fillings in the bottom of a 9 x 11-inch cake pan, mixing in the lemon juice and cinnamon.
Sprinkle the dry cake mix on top.
Melt the oleo and pour on top, covering all of the mixture.
Sprinkle the pecans evenly over the top.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until clear.
Add Jell-O; stir.
Add strawberries and pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: potato casserole
directions: Beat
the
potatoes good.
Add margarine, cream cheese, sour cream and
chives.	Mix
all together.
Pour in casserole dish and bake until slightly brown.

title: cheesy chowder
directions: Dissolve bouillon cube in water. Add potatoes, mixed vegetables and onion. Cover.
Simmer 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: sauerkraut and beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add
raw rice, V-8 juice, seasonings, sugar and green peppers.
Pour	meat
mixture into greased, oblong casserole dish.
Cover
with
the
sauerkraut. Sprinkle with brown sugar.	Pour 2 cups warm water over all in the casserole.	Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: white chocolate clusters
directions: Melt white chocolate.
Mix Rice Krispies, pecans and pretzels. Stir until coated.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.
Let sit until firm.

title: vinegar cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Add and mix in dry ingredients and pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: halibut steaks with tangy mustard sauce
directions: Arrange halibut steaks in a large, shallow baking dish. Combine orange juice and next 5 ingredients in a small bowl, stirring well.
Pour over steaks.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator 1 hour, turning once.

title: cereal killer cookies
directions: Combine oatmeal and Brickle chips.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine firmly packed brown sugar, granulated sugar and margarine in mixing bowl and beat until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Continue beating until blended. Add dry ingredients.
Beat until combined.
Add oatmeal/candy mixture.
Stir until well mixed.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet, 2 inches apart.
Bake 10 minutes, in a 350° oven, or until slightly brown.
Cool one minute.
Transfer to cooling rack.

title: holiday eggnog
directions: Beat egg yolks to light yellow.
Add bourbon and rum slowly, beating mixture constantly.
Add sugar, then milk.
Fold in whipping cream, then very stiffly beaten egg whites.
Top with a sprinkling of cinnamon and nutmeg.

title: veggie pizza("sara's favorite")
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Press crescent rolls on large cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Mix cream cheese, dressing mix, mayonnaise and seasonings.
When crescent rolls are cool, spread with cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle chopped veggies and shredded cheese, then top with shredded cheeses.
Cut in squares to serve.
Excellent!

title: family barbecue chicken
directions: Cut chickens in half.
Clean and dry well.
Combine salad oil (or margarine), vinegar, water, salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Heat just to boiling and set aside.
Place chicken on grill over gray coals.
Brush with sauce mixture every 5 minutes or as often as necessary to prevent burning.
Cook until tender. When leg bone turns easily in the socket, chicken is done.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Blend all ingredients and place in a greased and floured 4-cup pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes or until brown on top. Loosen sides with a knife and let stand 5 minutes before turning out of pan.

title: creole dinner
directions: Place bacon on	bottom	of
pan.
Distribute
steak
in layer over bacon.
Add
layer of onions, carrots and potatoes. Add water.
Cook, covered, for 45 minutes on slow heat.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour 1/2 batter in 2 skillets. Sprinkle cheese on top of each.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: oriental chicken and cashews(microwave)
directions: Heat oil in 12 x 8-inch dish at High 2 1/2 to 3 minutes. Meanwhile, combine chicken, garlic, soy sauce, sherry, cornstarch and ginger.
Add to dish and cook at High 4 to 5 minutes; stir twice.
Add green pepper and cashews.
Cook, covered with plastic wrap, at High 3 to 5 minutes or until chicken and green pepper are tender; stir once.
Let stand 3 minutes before serving.
Serves 2.

title: celery almondine
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add celery, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook until celery is crisp and tender.
Shake pan frequently to prevent scorching.
Add green onion tops and onion.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Combine flour and broth; blend into celery mixture.
Stir and cook until sauce begins to thicken.
Stir in milk and simmer about 2 minutes.
Add almonds; toss gently.
Sprinkle with coarsely ground pepper.
Serves 6.

title: men love it salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Set aside. Soften cream cheese with juice from crushed pineapple.
Mix pineapple, celery and nuts together.
Let jello set until thickened.
Then add pineapple, nuts, celery and cream cheese mixture.

title: dee's apple butter bread
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar.
Blend in eggs.
Mix dry ingredients in a separate bowl.
Mix soda and buttermilk in a cup. Add dry and wet ingredients alternately to creamed mixture.
Stir in apple butter and pecans.
Pour into greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 20 minutes more.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: Mix and cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: ley mill lemon pudding
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Grease a pie dish.
Put the bread crumbs to soak in the milk at least one hour before cooking.
Then place in pie dish.
Add the sugar, lemon rind and juice and the beaten white of an egg and stir carefully so that it does not curdle. Bake for
1 1/2 hours.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Bring raisins and water to a boil; cook 5 minutes (simmer). Set aside to cool.
Sift all dry ingredients together except sugar.
In a large bowl, cream butter or margarine and sugar together; cream well.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Add dry ingredients, then add cooled raisin nut mixture.
Add chopped nuts.
Chill dough in refrigerator.
Drop by teaspoon on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 370° for approximately 10 minutes.
Good and easy.

title: lemon whippersnaps
directions: Mix well together. Grease cookie sheet. Drop by teaspoonful onto plate of powdered sugar. Roll dough to coat.
Place balls 1 1/2-inches apart. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: fig preserves cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine all liquids.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to liquids.
Mix well.
Add nuts and figs.
Stir until well blended.
Pour batter into lightly greased and floured tube pan. Bake for 1 hour.
When cake is done, cool in pan for 10 minutes and make sauce for cake.

title: apple juice with mint
directions: Mix apple juice with 3 parts water.
Stir in lemon juice and chopped mint.
Blend until mint leaves are fine.
Chill and serve.

title: cream cheese potatoes
directions: Peel and boil potatoes until done and drain and mashed.
Add all ingredients except butter and Cheddar cheese.
After mixed, pour into casserole dish and top with butter; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with Cheddar cheese; return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: date nut jello
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Chill until firm.

title: lettuce and cauliflower salad
directions: Tear lettuce apart.
Break cauliflower apart into bite size pieces.
Take mayonnaise and spread over to seal.
Fry bacon crisp, drain and crumble.
Dice onion and put on top of bacon.
Put grated Parmesan cheese on top.
Add sugar on top of cheese.
Let stand overnight.
Don't toss until ready to serve.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix mashed potatoes, butter, eggs, milk, vanilla and sugar. Put in casserole dish.
Top with nuts, brown sugar, flour, melted butter mixed together.
Spoon over the potato mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry batter cake
directions: Sprinkle berries with lemon juice.
Pour evenly in well-greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cream 3/4 cup sugar and butter. Sift flour, baking powder and 1/2 of salt together.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Pour batter over berries.
Combine 1 cup sugar, cornstarch and rest of salt. Sprinkle evenly over cake.
Cover cake with boiling water.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: helen's famous brownies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Fold in chocolate and nuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken macaroni salad
directions: Blend lemon juice into mayonnaise.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: *Not frozen, this is found on the grocery shelf.

title: graham toffee bars
directions: Prepare cookie sheet first. May want to spray with Pam for easy cleaning. Line cookie sheet with graham crackers in a single layer. Bring butter, oleo and sugar to slow boil and boil for 5 minutes. Immediately spoon butter mixture over graham crackers, spreading with back of large spoon to make sure all crackers are coated. Sprinkle the nuts generously over the crackers. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Adjust to your oven as these have a tendency to overcook around the edges of the pan. Remove from oven and transfer immediately to wax paper to cool. When cool, break into pieces and store in airtight container.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: In skillet, brown chicken parts in shortening.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until chicken is tender, stirring now and then.
For an extra bright touch, garnish chicken with lemon slices.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lemon poke cake
directions: Place cake layers, top sides up, in 2 clean 9-inch round cake pans.
Pierce cake with large fork at 1/2-inch intervals.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in medium bowl 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Carefully pour 1/2 of the gelatin over 1 cake layer.
Pour remaining gelatin over second cake layer. Refrigerate 3 hours.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Boil cabbage long enough to loosen leaves.
Peel leaves and set aside.
Mix hamburger, tomato sauce, rice and seasonings. Make small balls of meat, put inside cabbage leaves and roll. Stick toothpick in them to hold together.
Place in deep pot. Pour tomato soup and kraut (drained) around the edge.
Cook for 2 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Heat milk, add butter and salt.
Cool slightly and add the corn meal and baking powder which have been sifted together, then the beaten eggs and chopped onion.
Stir well together.
Place the corn in a greased casserole and put the corn meal mixture over, mixing ever so slightly.
Mixture should be very thin.
If necessary add a bit more milk.
Bake, uncovered, in a moderate oven (350°) for 45 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: milky wonder cake
directions: Melt candy bars in 1 stick of butter.
Beat other stick of margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and soda alternately with buttermilk; mix until smooth.
Add melted candy bars and mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
(Start checking for doneness after 1 hour.) Frost if desired.

title: classic green bean bake
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine soup, soy sauce, pepper, milk and beans and 1/2 can of onions.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes until hot.
Stir.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix thoroughly; will be quite moist.
Make into small meatballs and brown in deep fat.
Drain all but 2 tablespoons of fat and add 1 can of beef bouillon (2 cubes).
Add meat.
Baste and simmer on the stove for 20 minutes or bake in oven for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: scalloped corn
directions: In the pan that you are going to bake in, melt the margarine. Then pour it into a large bowl and add your corn, sour cream and eggs (and peppers and onions, if desired).
Stir in cornbread mix and pour into your pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until golden brown.

title: norman clark's cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries in boiling water until skins split.
Run water and cranberries through a sieve to separate skins, discard skins. Add sugar to cranberries, stir until dissolved.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water, add to cranberry mixture.
Refrigerate until soft set, add nuts, pineapple and grapes.
Pour into mold or serving bowl.
Refrigerate until set.
Serve with whipped topping (optional).

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix Bisquick, sugar, egg and milk.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Stir in the nuts and bananas.
Pour the mixture into a well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Cook broccoli until done.
Drain.
Beat biscuit mix, milk, eggs and salt until smooth.
Stir in broccoli and cheese.
(Save a little cheese to sprinkle on top.)
Pour into dish and bake for an hour or until knife inserted, comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix German chocolate cake as directed on package.
Put 1/2 mixture into 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake for 15 minutes at 350°. (Butter and sugar cake pan and the crust won't be dry.)

title: no fuss caramel corn
directions: Place popped corn and peanuts in large brown paper bag.
Set aside.
Combine brown sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt in a 2-quart glass bowl or casserole dish. Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes, stirring after each minute, until mixture comes to a boil.
Microwave 2 minutes more.
Stir in baking soda.
Pour syrup mixture over popped corn and nuts.
Close bag and shake well. Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake bag again.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes more.
Shake bag and pour caramelized corn into large bowl.
Separate when cool.

title: caramel fruit dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together with mixer until creamy. Chill.
Serve with apple and banana slices.
Also good with grapes.

title: cauliflower dip
directions: Mix all well.
Delicious served with vegetable trays for parties.

title: make ahead breakfast bake
directions: Brown sausage; drain fat.
Spread bread cubes in a buttered 9 x 12-inch dish.
Sprinkle sausage over bread.
Add cheese. Combine remaining ingredients; beat well and pour over cheese. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until set.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: In a bowl, mix the cottage cheese and dry Jell-O, then the crushed pineapple, whipped cream and then nuts. Chill.

title: michele's truffles
directions: Melt chocolate with
butter
slowly in double boiler or heavy saucepan.
Remove
from
heat
and add liquor, stirring well until
all
liquor is absorbed.
Refrigerate at least 40 minutes or
until
mixture
hardens.
Shape into marble sized balls and roll in chocolate jimmies.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cook cake mix by directions.
Cook pineapple and sugar together until syrupy.
After cake cools, put some of pineapple on cake plate.
Put one layer.
Poke holes in it.
Put pineapple on layer. Top with other layer.
Poke holes and put remaining pineapple. After it cools, put Cool Whip completely for icing.

title: martha's baked beans
directions: Brown meat.
Drain in colander.
Saute bell pepper and onion in same skillet.
Combine meat, bell pepper, onion and pork and beans.
Add barbecue sauce to make soupy.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles.
Turn heat down to 300° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry crisscross
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat butter and sour cream until light and fluffy.
Add flour and mix well.
Cover and chill dough about 1 hour or firm enough to handle.
Dough must be well chilled. Divide dough in half.
Leave other half in fridge until ready to use.
Roll dough to an approximate 10 x 8-inch rectangle.
Place this rectangle on a greased baking pan.
Spread 1/2 of filling lengthwise down the center of rectangle.
Sprinkle with 1/2 the nuts.

title: mock swiss steak
directions: Blend together the first 4 ingredients and put into baking dish. Refrigerate overnight.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes in three 8-inch cake pans.
Slice layers in half.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Cream the cream cheese. Pour hot jello into cheese.
Add nuts and drained pineapple.
Add Cool Whip and cool.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Boil chicken and take meat off bone; cut into bite-size pieces. Saute onion and garlic in butter until tender.
Cut tortillas into fourth or sixths.
Dip in hot Crisco.
Remove fast.
Blend Ro-Tel tomatoes and soups.
Add onion.
Butter casserole dish.
Put layer of tortillas on bottom.
Add soup mix; then layer of chicken. Repeat layers until dish is full.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: steak and gravy
directions: Pound steak with a knife or saucer well.
Roll in flour, pepper and salt.
Brown on both sides in hot oil or shortening. Reduce heat.
Add a small amount of water and simmer until tender. Keep enough water in pan for gravy.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, well.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes, remove from pan.

title: papa's rock cornish hens
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Place hens in a lightly greased 9x13 in. baking dish.
Stuff each hen with lemon half and 1/4 of sliced leeks, then sprinkle with seasonings.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour or until hens are cooked through and juices run clear. Let stand 10 minutes, then remove lemon & leeks.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix vinegar, brown sugar, salt, butter, lemon juice, water, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, pepper and ketchup.
Bring to a boil for 20 minutes (uncovered).
Add onion and liquid smoke. Bake for 1 hour at 300° to 325°.

title: grilled basil chicken
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in container of an electric blender; process 30 seconds.
With blender running, gradually add oil in a slow, steady stream.
Reserve 1/4 cup basil mixture. Brush chicken with remaining basil mixture.
Cover; refrigerate 30 minutes.
Cook chicken, covered with grill lid, over medium for 30 minutes, or until done, basting twice with reserved basil mixture. Makes 4 servings.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes in thin slices.
In bowl, beat egg, then add milk.
Add flour, salt, pepper and garlic and whip mixture until smooth.
Melt margarine in heavy skillet over medium-low heat.
Dip tomatoes, a slice at a time, in batter and place in skillet.
Fry until brown on both sides.

title: garden souffle salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add cold water, vinegar, mayonnaise and pepper. Beat to blend well.
Pour into freezing tray.
Place in freezer 15 to 20 minutes, or until firm about 1 inch around edge and soft in center.
Pour into a bowl and whip until fluffy and thick.
Fold in onion and vegetables.
Pour into a 1-quart mold or individual molds.
Chill until firm. Unmold onto salad greens.
Makes about 4 cups.
May be doubled and put into a 2-quart mold for crowd.

title: old-time fresh peach crumb pudding
directions: Peel and cut peaches into quarters.
Combine 1/2 cup of the sugar
and	3
tablespoons	of
the flour and mix with the peaches.
Turn into
a
10	x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix the remaining sugar and flour.	Add butter or margarine and cut it to crumb consistency.	Sprinkle crumbs over peaches.
Bake in a preheated
moderate
oven (375°) for 1 hour or until peaches are tender
and crumbs are brown.
Garnish top as desired with sliced fresh peaches.
Serves 8.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer ingredients in the order given, spreading each.
Bake at 350° for 48 to 55 minutes.
Use a big tube pan.

title: old-fashioned hominy
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a stone jar or enamel pan (nothing else!).
Soak for 15 hours until the husks come off easily. Drain.
Wash in cold water several times, removing the husks. Place in a kettle and cover with water.
Bring to a boil, then simmer until tender, changing the water 3 times in the process. Store in the freezer.

title: what shall we do with the leftover turkey
directions: Butter 2 slices of bread.
Cut into small cubes and set aside. Cut remaining bread in cubes.
Place half of unbuttered cubes in bottom of an 8
x
8 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine turkey, ham, vegetables, seasonings and mayonnaise. Spoon over bread.
Place remaining unbuttered cubes over mixture. Combine eggs and milk; pour over all.
Chill for 1 hour or overnight. Spoon soup over top and sprinkle with the buttered cubes. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until set. Sprinkle shredded cheese over top during the last few minutes of baking.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 healthy servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients using mixer.
Put in greased casserole. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: deviled turkey drumsticks
directions: Shake mixture of flour, chili powder and salt and pepper to taste
in paper bag and add turkey legs to coat.
Brown in shortening.

title: chicken in mushroom sauce
directions: Spray oblong Pyrex baking dish with Pam.
Mix soup, sour cream, sherry and mushrooms.
Layer 1/3 of this mixture in bottom of dish. Place chicken on top, then pour on rest of soup mixture.
Bake at 325° for approximately 3/4 of an hour.
Cook 8 ounces of medium egg noodles.
Pour mixture over.
Sprinkle on chopped parsley.
Enjoy!

title: pralines
directions: Cook in pot until mixture crystallizes.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: christmas festive cookies
directions: Combine and sift together all dry ingredients except rolled oats.
Add rolled oats, pineapple, cherries and nuts until coated well.
Add melted Crisco, eggs and milk.
Drop from teaspoon about 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 10 to 12 minutes or until brown as desired.
Makes approximately 6 dozen.

title: 24-hour seven layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients in large salad bowl in the order listed. (A clear bowl allows you to see the layers.)
Be sure everything is very dry before starting your layers.
Cover the top completely with dressing.

title: finger jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and gelatine in hot water.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: seven-minute frosting
directions: Place all ingredients except vanilla in double boiler.
Beat 1 minute with beater.
Place over boiling water and cook, beating constantly, until frosting forms stiff peaks, about 7 minutes. Don't overcook.
Remove from boiling water. Pour into mixing bowl. Add vanilla. Beat until spreading consistency, about 2 minutes.

title: delmonico potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes.
Chill and peel them.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, grate potatoes.

title: cookie cake
directions: Combine milk and egg.
Add mix and chopped pecans.
Pour into pan and top with chocolate chips and Heath bits.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let set for 1 day.

title: fluffy pumpkin pie
directions: Mix milk with softened cream cheese and stir in pumpkin; blend well.
Mix together pumpkin pie spice and brown sugar (or Sugar Twin) and blend well with pumpkin mixture.
Add vanilla now, if desired.
Whip in pudding and fold in Cool Whip lite.
Garnish with chopped pecans.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Melt oleo, stir in flour and pecan pieces.
Press into pan and bake at 250° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.

title: crust for fried pies
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder, then add shortening.
Use a fork to mix the shortening in.
Mix well.
Add milk and mix.
Make into 2-inch balls and roll out on floured surface.
Makes 10 fried pies.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Combine flour and salt; coat chicken.
Brown in hot oil; drain.
Transfer to crock-pot.
Stir together lemonade, brown sugar, catsup and vinegar.
Pour over chicken.
Cover; cook on high for 3 to 4 hours.
Remove chicken; pour liquid into saucepan. Return chicken to crock-pot; cover to keep warm.

title: swedish pineapple cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order by hand.
Pour into an ungreased, unfloured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven 350°.
Blend sugar and oil, add mashed bananas and eggs one at a time, add vanilla.
Mix flour, soda, allspice and cinnamon together then slowly add to the other ingredients and mix well.
Bake 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 3 small loaf pans.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Let cream cheese soften; beat until fluffy.
Gradually add milk while mixing.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Blend well. Pour into crust.
Chill 2 to 3 hours, then garnish top with cherry pie filling.

title: pineapple coconut pound cake
directions: Beat
butter,
Crisco
and sugar.
Add eggs 1 at a time. Add coconut, flavoring and pineapple alternately with flour and milk; beat
well.
Cook
at
for 1
hour and 20 minutes, starting in cold oven.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine soup, egg, mayonnaise, cheese, seasoning and onions. Mix well.
Add broccoli and mix well.
Spoon into 1 quart greased baking dish.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: all-american apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray a 9-inch deep dish pie plate with vegetable cooking spray.

title: scotch scones
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll mixture out to 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut in circles or wedges.
Brown and slowly bake on sparingly greased griddle (not too hot).

title: sweet potato favorite
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into a casserole dish.

title: butterscotch cinnamon rolls
directions: Sprinkle pecans in 8 x 13-inch pan, then sprinkle butterscotch pudding over pecans.
Next, sprinkle cinnamon over top.
Place frozen dough balls on top.
Melt oleo and brown sugar together; pour over rolls.
Cover pan with Saran Wrap; let set in refrigerator overnight.
Next morning, bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Turn rolls upside down on platter when taken from oven.

title: beet salad
directions: Dissolve gelatins in hot water.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into 9 X 13 pan or dish.
When set, spread with 1 cup salad dressing, 1 cup chopped celery and 1/2 cup chopped green onion, mixed together.

title: sweet-n-sour cuke relish
directions: Whisk together vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper in a nonreactive bowl. Add cucumber, tomato, green pepper and onion. Toss; cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour or up to 2 days.

title: chocolate-peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa and milk 2 minutes.
When it comes to a rolling boil, remove from heat; add vanilla, margarine, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper.
Let cool. Add a little more oatmeal if the mixture does not seem thick enough.

title: mayonnaise
directions: In a blender or a food processor with a metal blade, process all ingredients until smooth.
Refrigerate, covered, for at least 24 hours before using.
Yields 1 cup.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Bake spareribs, meat side up, sprinkle with salt and topped with lemon slices at 350° for 1 hour. Drain fat.
Refrigerate. Combine remaining ingredients.
Grill ribs 6 to 8-inches from heat.
Turn and brush with sauce after 15 minutes. Cook 15 minutes longer, basting frequently. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: white icing
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in iron skillet. Beat for 2 minutes on low speed. Then on beat and whip for 5 more minutes. Take off and place vanilla in icing. Beat for 1 to 2 minutes. Spreads beautifully. If you want, you may spread coconut on top and sides of layers.

title: beef noodle bake
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.In a greased casserole dish, layer noodles.
Mix together in bowl the can of tomatoes, tomato soup, hamburger, and seasonings to taste (onion, salt, pepper, bell pepper, oregano).
Layer this mixture over noodles.
Mix together sour cream, cream cheese and green onion (if desired). Layer this on top.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Defrost potatoes.
Add celery, potato soup and sour cream and mix well.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley flakes.
Bake in slow oven at 300° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in baking dish and cook for 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: barbecue meat loaf
