directions: Mix beef, crumbs, onion, egg, salt, pepper and 1/2 can of tomato sauce.
Form into loaf and put in casserole dish.
Combine rest of sauce and all other ingredients; pour over loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Baste often.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Mix all together in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 375° until light brown.

title: peanut butter roundups
directions: Beat shortening and sugars together until creamy.
Add eggs and peanut butter.
Beat well.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats.

title: fudge eclaire pie
directions: Mix pudding according to directions.
Fold in Cool Whip. Starting with graham crackers on bottom, layer crackers, then pudding (making at least 5 layers).
Frost with frosting and refrigerate.
Best if made 3 days in advance! It's worth the wait!

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine wet ingredients and mix well.
Blend dry ingredients and mix both together.
Grease 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: cheese bread
directions: Dissolve yeast with sugar and 1/4 cup water.
Mix 5 cups flour with salt and make a well and add 1 1/2 cups water, butter and yeast.
Stir and turn out with 1/2 to 1 cup flour.
Knead 10 to 12 minutes.
Cover and let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Punch down and knead in the cheeses.
Halve and let rest 10 minutes.
Roll into a rectangle (11 x 6-inch) and let rest 2 to 3 minutes.
Roll up and place in 8 x 4 x 2-inch well-greased bread tins.
Let rise until top of tins.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cool before slicing.

title: seafood quiche
directions: Saute onion and shrimp in butter until shrimp are curled and pink and onion is translucent.
Pour in crab meat and stir.
Pour mixture in pie crust.
Beat together the eggs, cream, salt, pepper and mace.
Pour over seafood in crust.
Dot the surface with butter.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes until nicely browned and very puffed.
Good hot or cold.
Settles as it cools.
Serves 4.

title: cheddar broccoli salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the broccoli, cheese and onion. Combine the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar. Pour over broccoli mixture and toss to coat. Refrigerate for at least 4 hours. Just before serving, stir in the bacon. Yield: 8 servings.

title: mushroom supreme
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter.
Dissolve beef cubes in water.
Set aside.
Melt butter and blend with flour.
Add cream, salt, pepper and beef broth.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs before baking in a buttered casserole 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers and mix with 1 1/2 sticks melted butter. Pat into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Beat 2 sticks butter, confectioners sugar and eggs together.
Put on top of vanilla wafer mixture. Slice bananas on top of cream mixture.
Drain crushed pineapple and put on top of bananas.
Next, spread on Cool Whip.
Then you can decorate with nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: potato cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, biscuit mix, potato flakes and flavoring.
Mix thoroughly.
Roll into balls about an inch in diameter.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes or until light brown.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: onion casserole
directions: Chop onions into bite-size pieces and place in 2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Chop butter into small pats and place evenly over onions.
Place cheese slices on top.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
The cheese will melt and hold the onions together.
Take out of oven and sprinkle French fried onions on top.
Return to oven and bake for 10 minutes.

title: beef and cheddar soft tacos
directions: Cook beef in skillet until browned. Pour off fat. Add soup and salsa and heat through. Spoon about 1/3 cup meat mixture down center of each tortilla. Top with Lettuce. Fold tortilla around filling. Serve with additional salsa or rice.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger (drain off excess fat).
Add flour, mushrooms and cream of chicken soup.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and heat.
Serve hot over cooked noodles.

title: sara lind's wassail
directions: Simmer 30 minutes and serve hot.

title: texas pecan candy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in tube pan in 250° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: waikiki meatballs
directions: Mix beef, crumbs, onion, egg, salt, ginger and milk thoroughly.
Shape into meatballs.
Melt shortening in a skillet; brown and cook meatballs.
Remove meatballs.
Keep warm.
Pour fat from a pan.
Mix cornstarch and brown sugar.
Stir in reserved pineapple juice, vinegar and soy sauce until smooth.
Pour into a skillet.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Add meatballs, pineapple and green peppers.
Heat thoroughly.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken, debone and shred.
Cook milk, flour and butter until thickened.
Cool.
Add chicken, noodles, mayonnaise, eggs and almonds.
Stir together and bake at 350° for 45-60 minutes.

title: green chili corn cakes
directions: About 15 minutes before serving:
In a medium bowl, mix the corn meal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
With fork, stir in milk, egg and green chilies, just until mixture is moistened. (Batter will be slightly lumpy.)
In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, add 1 tablespoon salad oil until hot.
Pour batter into skillet by scant 1/4 cupfuls, making a few corn cakes at a time. Cook until lightly browned on both sides.
Repeat, adding more oil if needed.
Makes 12 corn cakes, 9 calories each.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, shortening, cocoa and granulated sugar.
Blend in one egg at a time until well mixed.
Add vanilla; stir in flour. Chill several hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 350°.
Drop teaspoonfuls of dough into confectioners sugar.
Roll in sugar and shape into balls.
Place about 2 inches apart on well-greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake!
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: steve's hot buffalo wings
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer covered for an hour.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Heat broiler with rack 5-7 inches away from heat.
Mix mayo, lime juice and taco seasoning.
Place chicken on broiler pan and brush with half the mayo mixture.
Broil 5-7 minutes, turn and brush with remaining mayo mixture.
Continue broiling 8-10 minutes or until tender.

title: boston clam chowder
directions: Saut onion, celery and green pepper. Put in large soup pot. Add milk, clams and juice, soup, potatoes and seasonings. Simmer until potatoes are soft. (Check frequently for scorching.) Just before serving, add crumbled bacon if desired. Yield: 16 cups.

title: chicken feed
directions: Melt butter, add remaining ingredients.
Pour over cereal and mix.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 225 degrees.
Uncover and bake 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: bran-apple muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt in large bowl.
Mix cereal and milk in another bowl and let stand for 5 minutes.
Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in cereal mixture and egg.
Add to flour mixture, stir just until moistened.
Stir in apples.
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together until blended, using salt and pepper to taste.
May be made ahead.
Keeps several weeks in refrigerator.

title: 1-2-3 beef
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into casserole.
Cover.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven.
Can be served over mashed potatoes, rice or noodles.

title: pear relish
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients with salt; let stand overnight. Drain and rinse with 4 changes of water.

title: chunk-of-cheese bread
directions: Bring the water, cornmeal and salt to a boil, stirring constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat and add molasses and butter.
Cool to lukewarm.
Soften the yeast in 1/2 cup warm water, then add to the cornmeal mixture and blend thoroughly. Gradually add the flour and stir to form a stiff dough.
Knead until smooth and satiny, about 5 minutes.

title: pizza delights
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, cook sausage over medium heat; drain off fat. Stir in pizza sauce, ketchup and garlic powder. Set aside. Press biscuits into 20 well-greased muffin cups. Spoon 1 to 2 tablespoons of the meat and sauce into each biscuit. Top with Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Yield: 20 muffin size pizzas.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread over pizza crust.

title: cream corn casserole
directions: Melt oleo in a large skillet or Dutch oven.
Stir in corn. When corn is completely thawed, add cream cheese, stir until melted.
Pour into casserole and bake at 350 degrees for 15-20 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix ingredients in this order:
Crisco and sugar, then eggs, salt, food coloring, flour and milk alternately.
Then add vanilla.
Beat continuously while adding ingredients.

title: ginny's gingerbread
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch baking pan with wax paper that has been greased.

Cream shortening and sugar. Add egg, then molasses. Combine thoroughly and add dry ingredients and water alternately until all have been added. Continue to beat until thoroughly mixed. Pour into pan and bake 35 minutes. Oven: 325°. Yield 15-24 servings.

title: ham pinwheels
directions: Mix together, except for ham.
Spoon onto ham and roll; fasten with toothpicks.
Freeze for a couple of hours, at least.
Then cut and serve.

title: spinach balls(party finger food - make ahead)
directions: Cook spinach and drain thoroughly.
Mix all ingredients and chill.
Shape into balls (1 to 1 1/2-inches) and freeze on tray. Put frozen balls into container and use as desired.
Cook on a tray for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool a little.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: banana split pie
directions: Put this in an oblong casserole dish.
Crust the vanilla wafers. Add a little butter.
Press in the dish and bake 5 minutes or so.
Let cool.
Add the bananas (sliced crossway).
Mix the cream cheese, confectioners sugar and pineapple (drained).
Mix this and put over the bananas.
Next, layer cherry pie filling. Use all.
Next, layer Cool Whip; use all.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans and place cherries about on top to decorate.
Keep chilled.

title: easy-good peach dessert
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, pour 2 large cans sliced peaches and juice.
Sprinkle with cake mix.
Sliver oleo over top.
Scatter crushed nuts over top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
When cool, top with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream (refrigerate).

title: frosty fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, combine sugar, buttermilk, salt and vanilla until well mixed.
Gently stir in drained fruits.
Pour into 9-inch square pan and freeze until firm.
Cut into squares at serving time.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Microwave margarine in a 4 quart microwave safe-bowl on high for 1 minute or until melted.
Add sugar and milk; mix well. Microwave on high for 5 minutes; stir after 3 minutes.
Mix well scrape bowl, continue microwaving on high for 5 1/2 minutes stirring after 3 minutes.
Remove from microwave, stir in chips until melted.
Add remaining ingredients; mixing well.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9 baking pan.
Let cool and cut.
If you want peanut butter fudge add 7 or 8 ounces peanut butter instead of chocolate chips.

title: christmas bread(julekake)
directions: Heat 1 cup milk and 1 teaspoon sugar and dissolve yeast in it. Add 1 cup flour and stir well.
Let rise to double or 1/2 hour. Heat other cup of milk to lukewarm and add salt, sugar, beaten eggs and cardamom.
Add butter.
Mix in 5 to 6 cups flour and work in more on the table, if needed.
Add fruit and raisins before the last cup of flour.
Let rise until doubled.
Make into round loaves or braided ring.
Put in greased pans and let rise to less than double.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 4 loaves.

title: beef and rice "porcupines"
directions: Mix beef, onions, salt and pepper. Form into small balls.
Fry in hot Crisco or Wesson oil.
Turn frequently until light brown but not crusty on all sides.
Add tomato soup and water. Cover and simmer about 45 minutes.

title: my favorite brownies
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels and butter on low heat, stirring constantly.
Let cool.
Stir in eggs, brown sugar and vanilla. Combine dry ingredients.
Add to mixture, stirring until blended. Fold in marshmallows, nuts and semi-sweet morsels.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Center should be springy when taken out of oven.
Be careful not to overbake.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients, mix well, pour into a square baking dish. Bake at 350° until browned.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together in a bowl. Roll into bite size balls. Bake at 350° until brown (about 10 to 15 minutes).

title: rabbit in beer
directions: Place cut-up rabbit in a paper or plastic bag with lightly salted flour.
Brown the floured rabbit in margarine.
Remove meat from the pot and blend in two tablespoons flour in the remaining fat.
Drain liquid from the can of mushrooms and add enough water to this to make about 1 cup.
Add this to the pot gradually and cook until thickened.
Stir in beer and return the rabbit.
Cover and cook until meat is tender.
Add mushrooms and green beans; continue cooking until heated.

title: yogurt fluff
directions: Pour boiling water into blender container.
Add gelatin and blend at low speed until dissolved about 1 minute.
Combine and add water and ice cubes to make 1 cup.
Add to gelatin and stir until ice is melted, then blend in yogurt and vanilla.
Chill in dessert glasses or bowl until set, about 1 hour.
Makes 5 servings (35 calories per serving).

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles and the butter and brown sugar are melted.

title: apple crisp
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Press 1/2 into a greased 9-inch square baking pan. Cover with apples.
In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, water and vanilla.
Cook and stir until thick and clear.
Pour over apples.
Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes or until the apples are tender.
Serve warm with ice cream, if desired.
Yields 8 servings.

title: faye's ham puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 2 baking sheets.
Sift 1/2 cup of flour onto wax paper.
Heat water, salt and 1/4 cup butter until butter melts.
Bring to a full boil.
Add sifted flour all at once. Stir over low heat about 1 minute or until mixutre leaves side of pan and forms a ball.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Beat eggs, one at a time, into mixture, beating until smooth after each addition.

title: jello pineapple dessert
directions: Drain the juice from the crushed pineapple.
Heat juice until boiling, add jello to dissolved.
Add ice cream, stir until smooth.
Add crushed pineapple and refrigerate overnight.
Stir when ready to serve.

title: french onion burger
directions: Mix egg into ground beef, blending well.
Stir in soup mix. Divide mixture into 6 equal parts and form into balls.
Press balls into patties.
Fry, broil or grill to desired wellness, topping with cheeses near the end of cooking time.
Serve burgers on French bread.

title: mom's strawberry pie and sweet crust
directions: Cook sugar, starch and water until thick.
Remove and add strawberry jello.
Pour over strawberries in crust and cool.

title: italian cucumber salad
directions: Toss together all ingredients with bottled Italian salad dressing.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Blend broth into soup in 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: persimmon bread
directions: Sift all 5 dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Make a well in center.
Add eggs, butter, bourbon, persimmon puree, nuts and raisins.
Mix the dough until it is quite smooth.
Butter and flour pan; fill about 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan, then turn on rack.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Lightly combine all ingredients and allow to set 1/2 hour. Add more milk for thinner pancakes.
Cook on lightly greased hot griddle.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on package.
Drain. Blend chicken, onions and mayonnaise in saucepan.
Blend in soups and milk.
Heat and stir until smooth.
Add cheese and heat until cheese melts.
Put noodles into mixture.
Transfer to casserole dish and bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: taco chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400`.
Dice chicken and dredge in taco seasoning (may place chicken/seasoning in plastic bag and shake to coat).
Saute onion and chicken in margarine until brown.
Prepare rice according to directions and drain.
In a casserole dish, arrange rice around edges, and place chicken and onions in the middle.
Combine tomatoes and salsa and pour over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 40 minutes or until cheese is browned.
May be served in warmed fajitas or over taco chips.

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and cook potatoes in salted water.
Mash until all lumps are gone.
Add salt, pepper, onion salt, sour cream and cream cheese.
Whip until light and fluffy.
Cool.
Will keep up to 12 days in refrigerator.
Place in buttered casserole and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: never fail strawberry pie
directions: Put into saucepan; add 2 cups hot water.
Cook until clear. Cool.
Pour over 1 quart of strawberries in a baked pie shell. Top with whipped cream.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute onion and margarine in big pot.
Put the remaining ingredients in pot and mix well.
Pour into casserole dish. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: holiday yam bake
directions: Drain yams; mash well.
Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Add juice to yams.
Add sugar and butter; beat well.
Stir in pineapple and pecans.
Coat inside of 1 1/2-quart casserole with Pam.
Spoon in mixture.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with marshmallows.
Bake for 10 minutes longer.
Serves 8.

title: christmas stollen
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add sugar, salt, eggs, butter and half of the flour.
Beat 10 minutes at medium speed on mixer or by hand.
Blend in rest of flour, almonds and fruits.
Cover; let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Stir down batter by beating 25 strokes.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
On well floured board, divide dough in half, press each half into a 10 x 7-inch oval sheet.
Spread with 2 tablespoons soft butter or margarine.
Fold each in two length-ways, firmly pressing edges in place on greased baking sheet.
Brush top with slightly beaten egg whites mixed with 1 tablespoon water.
Let rise in warm place until light.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until done.
When cool, frost and decorate with almonds and cherries.
Makes 2.

title: onion pie
directions: Saute onions in 1/2 cube butter.
Crush crackers and put into pie pan.
Melt 1 1/2 cubes butter.
Add to crackers.
Mix to form a pie shell.

title: gourmet green bean bake
directions: Cook and drain beans.
In 1-quart casserole dish, blend soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper until smooth.
Stir in beans and 1/2 can onions.
Sprinkle 1/2 can onions on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine applesauce, sugars, vanilla and Egg Beaters until well blended.
Add flour mixture and stir until well blended.
Stir in chocolate chips. Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes or until edges are golden brown. Recipe makes 5 dozen cookies.
Ultra low-fat.

title: gumdrop cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Mix applesauce, soda and water and add to creamed mixture.
Add flour, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves, and mix well.
Then add gumdrops, raisins, nuts, and final 1 c. flour.
Mix well and bake in 9 inch tube pan at 350° for 2 hours 15 minutes.
(Paper bottom and grease sides.)
Let cool a few minutes, then remove from pan.
This cake is just like fruitcake, but doesn't have the fruits.

title: harvest potato boats
directions: Cook sausage until no longer pink. Drain fat.

Add carrots, beans, zucchini and onion. Saute until crisp-tender. Season to taste. Cut large cross in each potato. Squeeze until opening is large enough to hold filling. Spoon a generous serving into each. Top with sour cream.

title: chicken florentine
directions: Cook spinach and drain completely.
Melt butter; stir in garlic, basil and marjoram.
Blend in flour.
Add cream, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Remove from heat; stir in spinach.
Place mixture in a 2-quart baking dish.
Cover spinach mixture with chicken.

title: ham and noodle casserole
directions: Saute butter and onion until transparent; mix remaining ingredients except cheese.
Put all into 2-quart casserole; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zippy curry dip
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 8 ingredients; mix well. Refrigerate until serving. Yield: About 1 cup.

title: j r's parfait pies
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir constantly.
Gradually add ice cream until very thick.
Some chunks of ice cream may not completely melt, this will give it a swirled look, very pretty.
Pour into ready to use crusts. Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
JR prefers them frozen.

title: cran-apple carrot muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon and salt in a large bowl. Then add carrots, raisins, cranberries, pecans, coconut and apples.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, salt and soda and set aside.
Cream together shortening, sugar and bananas.
Add to creamed mixture the eggs and mix.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Add nut meats and vanilla.
Grease and flour 2 large loaf pans.
Divide batter into pans.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour, but check it sooner by inserting a straw into the center of the loaves.

title: debbie greenberg's chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Mix bread stuffing, melted margarine and hot water.
Place half of mixture in greased 12 x 8-inch dish.
Combine cooked chicken, onion, celery and mayonnaise.
Place in dish over bread mixture.
Top with remaining half of bread stuffing mixture.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut butter into dry cake mix until crumbly.
Stir in coconut; pat mixture lightly into 9 x 13-inch pan, building up slight edges.
Bake 10 minutes.
Arrange apple slices on warm crust.
Mix sugar and cinnamon, sprinkle on apples. Blend sour cream and egg yolks.
Drizzle on apples (topping will not completely cover apples).
Bake 25 minutes or until edges are light brown (do not overbake).
Serve warm.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 6 tablespoons of juice.
Combine flour and sugar and stir in reserved juice in a small bowl.
Put pineapple and cheese into a large bowl and stir together.
Then add flour mixture and stir.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture into a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Combine melted butter or margarine and cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle over pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: favorite beef loaf
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Add ground beef.
Mix well. Shape mixture into a loaf in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° about 1 1/4 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine; add other ingredients and mix well. Pour into greased casserole dish; melt 1/4 stick margarine and add 2 cups Ritz cracker crumbs, stir to coat well.
Put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese mixture is bubbly.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown ground beef. Drain off fat. Add remaining ingredients to beef. Keep warm in a fondue pot. Serve with corn chips or flour tortillas.

title: fresh strawberry soup
directions: Puree all ingredients, except mint, in blender.
Put in bowl; cover
and	let
stand
in	refrigerator
for 6 hours or overnight.

title: apple fritters
directions: Beat eggs.
Stir in milk.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and soda and beat in shortening.
Dip apple slices into fritter batter and drop into the hot grease.

title: holiday bread
directions: Mix together milk, egg, oil and vanilla.
Set aside.
Mix together sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to milk mixture.
(Use one of the last four ingredients or your own flavor.)
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan or 3 mini loaf pans.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes or until done.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Combine ingredients; add to a casserole dish.
Bake in oven at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: granny's spanish roast
directions: Salt and pepper the roast. Brown in 3 tablespoons of oil or shortening.
Mix garlic, chili powder, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and water.
Pour this over the browned roast.
Add onions. Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours until tender.
Serve with rice. Gravy is delicious.

title: scallops st. jacques mornay
directions: Saute scallops in butter, mushrooms and white wine.
Add garlic, cream and tarragon.
Thicken with roux.
Top with Swiss cheese and broil to a golden brown.

title: calico dip
directions: Cut off top or round loaf.
Pull inside of bread out (with fork) in dip-sized pieces.
Mix ingredients and spoon into hollow loaf.
Replace round top; wrap in foil and bake in oven at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Before serving, place small pieces of bread pulled from loaf on cookie sheet and place under broiler just long enough to lightly toast and harden pieces.
Remove lid from loaf and dip pieces into cheese mix.
When bread bits are gone, tear off pieces of loaf to eat.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add mashed bananas. Add 2 cups flour, 1 teaspoon soda, pinch of salt, vanilla and nut meats.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ann's pecan pie
directions: In a medium size bowl, beat eggs (with a fork for 1 minute). Add sugar; mix.
Add Karo syrup.
Add melted margarine; mix well. Add the chopped pecans; mix well.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell. Top with whole pecans.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Turn up to 350° and bake until golden brown (about 20 to 30 minutes).

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Rinse
breasts	and pat dry.
Combine cornflake crumbs, seasonings	and Parmesan cheese in a plastic bag.
Dip chicken in milk
and place in the bag of crumbs.
Shake until coated. Place chicken in foil-lined baking dish and drizzle each piece with melted
diet margarine.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: zesty biscuits
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Spoon into muffin tins and bake at 450° until golden brown.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Melt butter.
Put in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Put both cans of cherry pie filling in butter.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over that.
Add coconut and nuts on top and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, to golden brown.

title: beef tips for the working mom
directions: Mix soups together.
Add beef tips and place in crock-pot. Cook all day.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook mixture until thick.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Put in pie shells and cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, Karo, butter and pecans.
Bake at 325° or 350° for 40 or 45 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder together.
Combine eggs, milk, potatoes and butter.
Beat well, then add to first mixture. Fry as for regular pancakes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, milk, salt, cocoa and butter to a boil, then add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Spoon on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Use festive cookie cutters.
The kids will enjoy decorating the cookies for all the holidays.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine 2 cups flour and 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Cut in margarine with a pastry blender until mixture resembles cornmeal. Spoon flour mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; pressing mixture evenly and firmly into bottom of dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until crust is lightly browned.
Combine 1/2 cup flour and baking powder; set aside.
Combine eggs, 2 cups sugar, and lemon juice; beat well.
Stir dry ingredients into egg mixture and pour over baked crust.
Bake at 350° for additional 25 minutes or until lightly brown and set.
Cool on wire rack.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup powdered sugar and cut into bars.
Yields about 2 dozen bars.

title: mickey's favorite chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar together.
Add eggs, beating after each one.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to cream mixture. Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: baked mashed potatoes
directions: Prepare potatoes as you would for mashed potatoes, then add other ingredients.
Put in baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: crispy cheddar treats
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, cheese, margarine and salt.
Mix with electric mixer until well blended.
Stir in rice cereal. Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Place balls 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Flatten balls into thin circles, using the heel of your hand or a flat bottomed glass. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: buttermilk coffee cake
directions: Heat buttermilk to lukewarm; add soda.
Stir in melted butter, sugar and salt.
Add 2 cups flour.
Stir in yeast.
Add eggs. Beat thoroughly.
Add remaining flour and raisins.

title: colcannon
directions: Melt the butter; add onion and cover with a round of greased paper.
Put lid on saucepan and cook over a slow heat for 10 minutes, but do not allow to color.
Add the mashed potatoes, chopped cabbage, pepper, salt and milk.
Mix all together well and reheat thoroughly, stirring all the time.
Pile up in a hot vegetable dish.
Score with a fork.

title: cheese meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients except cheese.
In a shallow baking dish, shape half of the mixture into loaf.
Cut 4 slices of cheese into strips.
Arrange on top of meat.
Top with remaining meat.
Press edges together to seal.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Top with remaining cheese slices.

title: chicken almond
directions: Mix rice, soup and water.
Crumble and brown sausage; drain. Saute onion and pepper lightly.
Add all ingredients with almonds. Put in casserole and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together, adding ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: banana chiffon cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into mixing bowl.
Make a well in dry ingredients and add in order: oil, egg yolks, banana and lemon juice.
Beat until smooth.
Add cream of tartar to whites.
Beat egg whites to very stiff peaks.
Do not underbeat.
Gradually and gently fold banana mixture into egg whites, just until blended.
Do not stir.
Pour into ungreased 10-inch tube pan, 4-inches deep.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.

title: grilled garlicky chicken breasts
directions: Mix salad dressing mix and cheese.
Moisten chicken in water; dip in dressing mixture.
Grill over medium-hot coals 15 to 20 minutes or until cooked through.

title: quick saucy stir-fry
directions: In a large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon of oil over medium heat. Stir-fry vegetables for 4 to 5 minutes until tender-crisp; remove.
Add remaining oil to skillet.
Stir-fry chicken for 4 to 5 minutes until tender.
Return vegetables to chicken and remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients except rice.
Mix well. Serve over hot, cooked rice.
Serves 4.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and cream well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well.
Add baking soda, salt, flour and sour cream.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes in a greased and floured tube pan.

title: cheese dip
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low until cheese is melted (usually takes 1 to 2 hours).

title: sad cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in lightly greased pan at 350° about 25 minutes or until cake puffs up and then flops.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: picante sauce dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and picante sauce.

title: hot sausage sandwiches
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Put in microwave for about 1 minute because this helps to drain more.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Put in fridge overnight.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in salt water.
Drain well and mash squash. Add rest of the ingredients.
Bake in greased casserole dish at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: asparagus roll-ups
directions: Trim off crusts from bread.
Flatten bread with rolling pin, so each slice is really thin.
Beat together 2 cheeses (which have been softened) and egg.
Mix well with rotary beater until smooth. (Leave some lumps of Bleu cheese.)

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Stir in soup.
Add extra Italian seasoning, if desired.
Cook spaghetti and drain.

title: black bean vegetable chili
directions: Place eggplant in colander, toss with salt and let sit for 1 hour to remove moisture; pat dry.
Heat 1/4 cup olive oil, saute onions, zucchini, peppers and garlic for 10 minutes.
Place remaining 1/4 cup olive oil in separate skillet.

Over medium-high heat, saute eggplant until tender, approximately 10 minutes. Remove with slotted spoon to casserole with other ingredients. Add to casserole tomatoes, broth, 1/2 cup parsley, basil and spices.
Cook over low heat 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally. After 30 minutes, add black beans, corn, dill and lemon juice. Cook an additional 15 minutes.
Adjust seasonings and stir in remaining 1/2 cup parsley.

title: pork marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Coat pork tenderloin with sauce and let soak for 1/2 hour.
Bake as usual.

title: stuffed giant shells
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic.
Drain and cool.
Stir in Mozzarella cheese, bread crumbs, parsley and egg.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: coca-cola salad for diabetics
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Drain pineapple; add juice to Coca-Cola and bring to a boil.
Pour over jello and stir until dissolved.
When slightly warm, add cream cheese and beat until thoroughly mixed.
Sweeten strawberries to taste with Sweet One.
Add to mixture and beat slightly.
Add pineapple and nuts; stir until mixed.
Add mayonnaise and mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: creamy pork chops and potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place potatoes and onion in an 8 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour into casserole. Top with pork chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cheri's fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter.
Mix all other ingredients, except fruit.
If mixture is too soupy, add more Bisquick to thicken.
Prepare fruit and add to center of mix.
Do not stir!
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: pink party salad
directions: Heat juice, marshmallows and Jell-O.
Cool.
When cooled, add cheese, nuts and cream.
Chill overnight.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Melt margarine and pour in sugar to dissolve.
Add milk and potatoes to mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Mix well.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: e-z barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter and stir in vinegar, ketchup and mustard.
Pour over meat and bake.

title: cornbread dressing(for turkey)
directions: Crumble cornbread.
Add bread cubes and rice.
Saute onions and celery in margarine until tender.
Add to cornbread mixture. Add beaten eggs, boiled eggs and margarine.
Add spices and soup. Add pecans last.
If dressing is too dry, add either bouillon or water to moisten.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (don't overcook). Dressing should be quite moist when done.

title: chocolate cake
directions: In a large bowl, put the sugar and flour.
In a saucepan, put the oleo, Crisco, water and cocoa.
Bring saucepan ingredients to a boil.
Add to sugar and flour.
Mix well and add the eggs and buttermilk with the soda dissolved in it.
Beat well.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° to 400° for 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk-garlic dressing
directions: Whisk together mayonnaise and buttermilk.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate, covered, at least 8 hours.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Add strawberries.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Layer with onions, then homimy and chili, then cheese.
Add juice until moist.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: russian chicken
directions: Brown chicken breasts in pan with canola oil.
Place in baking dish skin side up.
Brush Russian salad dressing over the chicken and add one can of drained apricots.
Bake at 350° until golden brown and tender (approximately 1/2 to 3/4 hour).
Serve over a bed of wild rice and garnish with steamed broccoli.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and add the rest.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll out thin and let set for 20 minutes.
Add to boiling broth.
Add enough milk for juice.
Never stir!!
Cook until done.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Add pineapple, salt and vanilla.
Dissolve soda in boiling water and add to mixture.
Stir in flour, one cup at a time.
Bake at about 350°.

title: chinese-style chicken
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add chicken, vegetables and garlic.
Stir-fry until chicken is cooked through.
Mix cornstarch, ginger, broth and soy sauce until smooth; stir into skillet.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.

title: barbecue pork ribs
directions: Use a 4-inch deep large roasting pan.
Place your pork ribs in bottom of pan.
Peel and cut onion in half.
Place 1/2 onion on each end of pan.
Cover completely with barbecue sauce (onion and ribs).
Place aluminum foil over pan.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour and 35 minutes.

title: cabbage and more
directions: Heat oil.
Add all ingredients except cabbage and sugar.
Cook 20 minutes.
Add cabbage and 1 cup water.
Cook 20 minutes more or until tender.
Make corn bread and get down!

title: fresh orange juice delight
directions: Soften the gelatin in warm water.
Combine the orange juice and gelatin with Equal or sugar.
Refrigerate until jelled.
Cut the gelatin into small cubes; serve in champagne glasses.
Garnish with the grated orange rind.

title: i can't believe it's cake
directions: Mix cake mix, egg, butter and pecans.
Grease sheet pan. Press ingredients in pan.

title: *carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Mix together oil, eggs and sugar. Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add to egg mixture, then add nuts and carrots.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Use Carrot Cake Frosting (found elsewhere).

title: reese's squares
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate chips.
Press into buttered pan.
Melt chocolate chips.
Pour over peanut butter mixture.
Cool, cut and serve.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix horseradish and dry mustard well.
Mix in remainder of ingredients.
Makes 4 cups.
Good on sliced ham.
Will keep in refrigerator for years.

title: rosemary's pie
directions: Let cream cheese soften and mix with sugar and 3/4 bowl of the cool whip.
Add butterfinger candy bars.
Put this mixture into the crust and top with the remaining cool whip.
Garnish with more crushed candy bars.
Freeze for 4 hours.

title: easy beef goulash
directions: Heat oil.
Brown beef; drain.
Sprinkle uncooked noodles over meat.
Combine water, tomato sauce and onion soup and pour over noodles.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer for about 30 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Add water as needed.

title: blackberry bread
directions: Cream shortening and
add
sugar.
Add eggs and beat in well. Add
remaining
ingredients and mix until well blended. Pour into greased
pans.
Bake
for
55 minutes for large loaf pan, or 30 minutes for small loaf.

title: angels delight
directions: Dissolve marshmallows in hot milk.
Layer ingredients in an oblong pan, starting with crumbs mixed with vanilla and marshmallow mixture, then whipped cream and pineapple.
Top with layer of graham cracker crumbs.
Serves 12.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli pieces for 7 minutes in microwave.
Cook pepper pieces and onions for 5 minutes in microwave.
Mix other ingredients into vegetables.

Cook all (broccoli and vegetables) and other ingredients another 5 to 10 minutes to taste tenderness. Or, may bake in oven for 30 to 45 minutes to taste tenderness and with rest of oven-dinner main meat dish.

title: stuffed peppers(microwave)
directions: Combine beef and onion and microwave 2 to 3 minutes. Add rice, tomato sauce, celery and salt to taste.
Stuff the peppers and place each on a square of plastic wrap. Twist the corners together.
Place into a casserole dish and cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave for 8 minutes.

title: scallop and mushroom pie
directions: Cut cleaned scallops into half, but do not cut the red coral. Simmer in milk with salt and pepper (to taste) for 15 minutes. Strain; reserve milk.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour and mix well.
Gradually stir in warm milk.
Avoid lumps.
Add mushrooms (cut in pieces).
Add the sherry and the scallops.
Place in ovenproof dish.
Cover top with mashed potato.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° until the top is lightly browned, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.
Soft rolls can be added to scallops, if available.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in a large glass bowl.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes; stir well.
Continue cooking for 1 1/2 to 3 minutes on High, or until boiling and sugar dissolves.
Stir in remaining ingredients until melted.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch dish.
Cool; cut into squares.
Makes about 3 dozen fudge squares.

title: appled roll
directions: Make 2 cups of biscuit dough, sweeten with 1 tablespoon sugar. Roll out as for pie crust.

title: german apple cake
directions: In large mixing bowl beat together eggs and sugar.
Add all other ingredients and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crumble streusel topping over batter and bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter, egg, milk, vanilla and sugars.
Add soda, salt and flour.
Shape into balls; roll in sugar and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Top each with a chocolate star immediately; press firmly so cookie cracks around the edge.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: In a large bowl, combine strawberries, 1/4 c of the sugar and lemon juice. Crush with a potato masher until strawberries are almost pureed. Set aside.

title: mexican pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In skillet, brown ground beef, chili powder, salt and garlic salt until light brown.
Drain.
In a small bowl, combine sour cream, mayonnaise and onions.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Cut biscuits in fourths.
Put in large bowl with sugar and cinnamon.
Seal bowl and shake.
Melt margarine and pour over this in a Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine spinach, bacon, eggs, onion and dressing to moisten; toss lightly.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Pick meat from bones and add chicken back to broth.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add celery, carrots, peas and onion. Thicken broth with flour.
Top with biscuit; bake in 375° oven until biscuits are done.

title: straw hat
directions: Cook and drain meat, then mix all other ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 400°.
On plate, sprinkle with chips.
Top with meat mixture and then sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.

title: slim sour cream
directions: Process all ingredients except scallions.
Scrape in bowl and add scallions.

title: chewy chocolate cookies(club member: brad smith)
directions: In large bowl, mix sugar and unsweetened chocolate; add eggs, one at a time, until all blended well. Mix in vanilla. Mix flour, baking powder and salt; add slowly to chocolate mixture. Cover and chill 2 hours. Drop mixture by rounded teaspoonful into confectioners sugar lightly coating. Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes; set aside to cool.

title: cool lime salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, marshmallows, sugar and hot water.
Leave out of refrigerator until marshmallows are dissolved.
Cover and refrigerate until thickened.
Add whipped cream, pineapple, cream cheese and nuts.
Chill before serving.

title: judy's artichoke dip
directions: Drain water from artichoke hearts and chop them.
Place all ingredients in bowl.
Mix at medium speed with electric mixer. Pour in Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve with bagel chips or tortilla chips.
Double for large group.

title: poppy chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts and pull chicken from bone.
Crush Ritz crackers. Use 1/2 of Ritz cracker crumbs in bottom of casserole. Place chicken on top of crumbs.
Mix sour cream and cream of chicken soup.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Put other half Ritz cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: virginia peanut soup
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add onion and celery; saute for 5 minutes.
Do not brown.
Add flour until mixture is well blended. Add hot chicken broth and cook for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate sour cream cake
directions: Put butter, sugar and unbeaten eggs in bowl.
Beat and blend very well.
Add sour cream, sifted flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Blend well.
Last, make a thin paste of Hershey's cocoa and hot water.
Blend all this into the batter. Stir well and pour into 2 (9-inch) greased layer cake pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven.
Put layers together with any chocolate frosting or whipped cream.

title: mashed potato buns
directions: Let rise; shape into buns and put into greased pan and let rise until light and about double in size.
Bake in 350° oven about 25 to 30 minutes.
This is large portion.
I use 1/2 of recipe.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: molasses krispies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add molasses and egg and mix well. Combine dry ingredients and add to above. Mix well. Chill. Make into small balls. Roll in sugar. Flatten with a fork dipped in sugar. Bake at 375° for 12-15 minutes.

title: t. c. soli's texas salsa
directions: Proportionate downward to fit your need.

title: meat and bean dish
directions: Brown beef with onion and peppers; drain well.
Stir in other ingredients; simmer 10 minutes.

title: italian potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in half.
Score cut surface.
Place melted butter in bottom of baking pan.
Place potatoes cut-side down in pan. Bake at 350° until tender.
Turn potatoes and brush Italian dressing onto cut side.
Bake, cut-side up, 5 additional minutes. When done, brush on more salad dressing.

title: crispy chip chicken(mom or dad will help with hard parts.)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Placing chips in Ziploc bag and using a rolling pin, crush into coarse crumbs (about 2 cups).
Set aside.

title: 14-layer chocolate cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating between each addition.
Add half the flour and half the milk.
Mix well.
Add remaining flour and milk.
Mix well and add vanilla.
Grease (using butter) and flour pans.
Put 2 or 3 tablespoons of batter in each layer, enough to cover bottom. Layers do not have to brown.
Bake at 350° until dry.
Cook about 6 at a time by putting them on both racks of the oven.
Do not wash pans between layers.
Wipe with paper towel and regrease with butter and flour.
Have chocolate filling ready and pour over layers as they get done.

title: chicken broccoli vegetable saute
directions: In skillet over medium heat, in 1 tablespoon olive oil, cook chicken 15 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Remove chicken and keep warm.
In same skillet, in remaining olive oil, cook broccoli, carrots and mushrooms 5 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Reduce heat to low; simmer 5 minutes or until chicken is tender and vegetables are crisp-tender.

title: barbecue cups
directions: In large skillet, brown beef; drain.
Add barbecue sauce and onion.
Separate biscuits and roll flat with rolling pin.
Place each biscuit in muffin pan cup.
Spoon meat into biscuits; sprinkle each with cheese.
Bake at 375° for about 12 to 15 minutes, or until biscuits are brown.
Kids love these; they like to help with the rolling of the biscuits, too!

title: fried dough
directions: Let bread dough thaw.
Break off pieces and flatten.
Fry in hot oil about 5 minutes until golden brown; turn over and fry other side.
Drain on paper towels and sprinkle with cinnamon sugar, powdered sugar or spread with jelly or jam.

title: blueberry muffins(low-fat and special diet)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add blueberries and toss.
Make well in center; set aside.
Combine milk and next 5 ingredients. Add to dry mixture and stir.
Spoon in muffin pan, sprayed with cooking oil.
Fill 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 12 muffins.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Combine flour, shortening, sugar and salt.
Mix very well. Combine vinegar, water and egg and add to flour mixture.
Mix with hand until it forms 1 large ball.
Chill 15 minutes.
Divide into 6 balls.
Roll on lightly floured board.
Makes 6 single crusts or 3 double.
Unused
crust may be frozen or refrigerated.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix margarine and crumbs.
Heat soup.
Remove from heat and add mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Cut broccoli stalks in half lengthwise.
Place broccoli in bottom of 12-quart casserole.
Spread chicken over broccoli and add sauce.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake in preheated oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna mousse
directions: Heat undiluted soup.
Add cream cheese and stir until dissolved.
Soften gelatin in lemon juice and, off heat, add to hot soup.
Let cool.
Drain tuna and stir into the soup mixture along with the other ingredients.
Grease a 6-cup mold with mayonnaise or vegetable spray.
Add tuna mixture and chill. Unmold and serve.
Great with toasted pita or party rye.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar. Add eggs and mashed bananas; mix well. Mix dry ingredients. Alternate dry ingredients and milk to creamy mixture. Mix well and fold in nuts. Pour into 2 well buttered 9-inch pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix
together
in order:
flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon, salt, oil,
eggs,
vanilla,
apples and chopped nuts.
Pour in Bundt pan and bake 2 hours in a 300° oven.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients; press into regular cake pan. Freeze.

title: osgood pie
directions: Separate
eggs.
Cream	sugar
and
oleo.
Add slightly beaten egg
yolks and stir.
Add raisins and pecans.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in first mixture.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and
bake
in a slow 325° oven until set in center. Don't overcook.

title: aunt ruth's broccoli casserole
directions: Grate 2 quart casserole. Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.
Grate cheese and mix with stuffing mix.
Put on top.
Bake about 5 more minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Drain well.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add all ingredients except stuffing mix.
Mix well.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with stuffing mix.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: emergency bars
directions: Melt the margarine on a cookie sheet. Sprinkle cake mix over the top. Arrange in layers on top; marshmallows, chocolate chips and Rice Krispies. Drizzle condensed milk over the top and bake at 350°f. 180°c. gas mark 4 for 20-25 minutes.

title: winter fruit salad
directions: Dressing: In a blender or food processor, combine sugar, lemon juice, onion, mustard and salt. Process until blended. With machine still running, add oil in a slow steady stream until mixture is thick and smooth. Add poppy seeds and process just a few seconds more to mix.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
In bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs, cocoa, sugar and butter.
Press evenly to bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat the cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add sweetened condensed milk, beating until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
In small bowl, toss 1/2 cup mini chips with flour to coat.
Stir into cheese mixture. Pour into prepared pan.
Sprinkle remaining chips evenly over top. Bake for 1 hour.
Turn oven off; allow to cool in oven for 1 hour.
Remove from oven.
Cool to room temperature.
Refrigerate before serving.
Cover and refrigerate leftover cheesecake.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: miracle whip spice cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: e-z cobbler
directions: Melt
butter
in
baking dish.	Mix milk, sugar, baking powder and
flour.
Put fruit in hot melted butter, then pour batter on top.
Do not stir.	Bake at 400° until done.

title: tomato aspic salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water and vinegar.
Mix tomato juice, onion, salt and pepper.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add horseradish, lemon juice and sugar.
Add softened gelatin; stir until dissolved. Cool.
Add cabbage, celery, green pepper and pimento.
Mix well. Pour into mold.
Chill until firm.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Pour rice in bottom of casserole dish.
(Season lightly with salt.)
Cover with onion and bell pepper.
Place pork chops on top.
Pour soup and water over pork chops.
Liquid should cover top of pork chops.
Bake until rice is done.
Easy and delicious!

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients in a large roasting pan.
Add the cheese, oil and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix the 3 salts together and sprinkle over mixed ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake, covered, 1 hour at 250°.
Bake, uncovered, at 250° for 1 hour.
Store in airtight container.

title: steak teriyaki
directions: Cut meat into bite size pieces or 1/2-inch strips.
In large bowl, add chopped garlic, ginger, brown sugar, pepper, oil, water and soy sauce.
Mix well.
Sprinkle tenderizer on steak and pour mixture over steak.
Let set overnight, stirring at least once.

title: spiced cucumber rings
directions: Peel, seed and slice cucumbers.
Use cucumbers that are too big for other uses (those that have turned yellow are okay).
Mix together 1 gallon water and the lime.
Pour over cucumbers; let stand for 24 hours.
Wash thoroughly.
Put into ice water for 3 hours; drain.
Make syrup with the sugar, vinegar and food coloring.
Make a spice bag with the remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil the vinegar, sugar, coloring, spices and candy.
Pour cucumbers into the mixture; bring back to boil.
Let stand for 24 hours.
Bring back to boil; boil for 30 minutes.
Pack into clean, hot jars.
Adjust lids.
Process 10 minutes in a boiling water bath.
Yields 8 pints.

title: egg casserole
directions: Mix together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch shallow casserole (greased).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fantastic bubble recipe
directions: Combine.
Shake and let settle 4 hours before using. (Non-toxic.)

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Grease and lightly flour 2 (8 1/2-inch) round baking pans. Stir together flour and baking soda.
In mixing bowl, beat shortening about 30 seconds.
Add sugar and val; beat until well combined.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 1 minute after.
Stir in cooled chocolate and sour cream.
Add dry ingredients and 1 cup water alternately to beaten mixture; beat after each addition. Turn into prepared pans.
Bake in 350° oven 30 to 35 minutes. Cool 10 minutes on wire racks.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil sugar, margarine and syrup slowly for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, salt and baking soda.
Pour over popcorn and stir well.
Put in very large pan and bake for 40 minutes at 250°.
Stir every 10 or 15 minutes.
Let cool and store in airtight container.

title: jean's chicken
directions: Place rice in bottom of pan.
Place chicken on top.
Mix together soups, milk and water and pour over chicken and rice. Sprinkle onion soup over all.
Seal tightly with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together; form ball.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: chocolate nut clusters
directions: In medium microwave-safe bowl, place chips and shortening. Microwave at High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth when stirred.
Stir in nuts.
Spoon heaping teaspoonfuls of mixture into 1-inch paper candy cups or paper-lined mini muffin cups, filling each cup half full.
Refrigerate until firm.
Peel off paper cup, if desired.
Makes 14 to 16 candies.

title: pasta fagoli(italian soup)
directions: Brown garlic in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add beans, remainder of the oil and all the seasonings.
Cook pasta as directed.
Drain almost half the water off the pasta.
Add other ingredients plus the crushed tomatoes.
Stir and heat 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: apple torte
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, soda and cinnamon. In large bowl, mix oil, sugar, flour and eggs.
Add apples and nuts (thick mixture).
Mix well and place in 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle caramel bits on top.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve topped with whipped cream or ice cream.
Freezes well.

title: crab salad
directions: Cube the bread and toss with the onion.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight. Add the shrimp, crab, celery and mayonnaise.
Place in bowl and decorate.

title: apple bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Cream sugar and vanilla together until fluffy.
Blend in remaining ingredients, except cinnamon and 1 tablespoon sugar. Pour into prepared pan; sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake for 1 hour.
After cooling, this bread may be wrapped and frozen.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar until smooth.
Chill batter to firm.
Add other ingredients.
Roll in dime size balls.
Dip bottom of glass in sugar and press each cookie.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 9 dozen.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Preheat to 350°.
Combine cake mix and gelatin, add oil and milk, eggs one at a time, strawberries, pecans and coconut.
Bake for 30 minutes or until done.

title: spaghetti
directions: Put in meat and spaghetti in pan and cook two hours.
Then put in the rocks.
Then you eat it.

title: oriental spinach salad
directions: Tear spinach into bite size pieces.
Add water chestnuts, bean sprouts, eggs and bacon.
Toss together.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix everything but eggs and milk; beat.
Add eggs and milk; bake 12 minutes at 450° or 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half; remove yolks.
Mash yolks with a fork.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Refill whites with mixture.

title: blue cheese-red wine dressing
directions: Mash cheese with fork.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Stir into cheese gradually.
Serve over salad greens.

title: easy hamburger casserole
directions: Place in baking dish, layering in order.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown meat and onions in skillet and drain.
Spread in a 9-inch pie plate.
In a bowl, beat milk, eggs, baking mix and salt and pepper by hand 1 minute.
Pour over meat in pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with tomato sauce and cheese.
Bake another 5 to 8 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix and bake at 400° in Pyrex pie dish.
This dish can be put on the table.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix together.
Place in a loaf pan or free form in a larger baking pan.
Bake for 30 minutes, until loves are lightly browned and cooked through.

title: bacon rolls
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain well and crumble.
Remove crusts from bread and spread butter on each slice.
Down middle of each slice of bread, put a line of crumbled bacon and sprinkle with cheese and parsley, then paprika and a dash of cayenne pepper.
Roll each slice up tightly and fasten with a toothpick. Broil until brown.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Saute chicken and veggies in 2 tablespoons oil.
Mix in casserole dish with Ranch dressing.
Top with biscuits of your choice.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are brown.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Sprinkle the cucumbers lightly with salt.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Rinse, drain and place in serving dish.
Meanwhile, combine the vinegar, sugar and pepper and let stand 5 minutes. Pour over cucumbers and sprinkle with the parsley.
Chill 2 hours. Yields 6 servings.

title: gooey cake
directions: Mix and spread in 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish.

title: sour-cream-pineapple coffee bars
directions: Mix 2/3 of cake mix with brown sugar and margarine.
Add cinnamon if desired.
Mix until crumbly.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add sour cream and remaining 1/3 box of cake mix.
Batter will be slightly lumpy.
Grease and flour oblong pan.
Put half of batter into pan.
Cover with brown sugar mixture.
Top with half of pineapple.
Repeat layer and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Cook ingredients until thick.
Pour in cooked pie crust. Cover with meringue and brown.

title: grill rub
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Delicious rubbed on beef or pork and grilled.

title: turmeric slaw
directions: Heat vinegar and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over other ingredients while warm.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: hot brown sandwich
directions: Melt butter and stir in flour; cook over low heat, blending until smooth.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Gradually add broth and milk; cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Add cheese; simmer about 10 minutes.
Sauce will be thick.

title: coffee lover's freeze
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine sugar and milk; bring to a boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved.	Remove from heat; let stand until cool.
Combine milk mixture, coffee, vanilla and 1 cup whipping cream; mix well.
Pour mixture into loaf pan and freeze until slush consistency, about 1 to 2 hours.
Beat remaining whipping cream until stiff peaks form; do not overbeat.
Just before serving, stir slush mixture; spoon into dessert dishes, filling 2/3 full.
Top with whipped cream.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix broth and soup together.
Lay chicken in pan; pour soup mix over it.
Mix flour, milk and margarine together; pour over chicken and soup mixture.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes, or until brown.

title: 15 minute chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken on stove first for an hour. Cool chicken, pick off meat and chop. In a crock pot add chicken, some of the broth from boiling, 5 carrots, 4 stalks of celery, 1 onion, 4 garlic cloves, chopped,1 1/2 to 2 c. peas. Season with regular and season salt, pepper, sprinkle of sage. Cook on low overnight. Great for Sundays.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Microwave chocolate and margarine in large bowl at High 2 minutes or until margarine is melted.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir sugar into melted chocolate until well blended.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until wooden pick comes out almost clean.
Do not overbake.
Cool in pan.
Cut in squares.
Makes 24 brownies.

title: monkey bread
directions: Pour 2 teaspoons margarine in bottom of tube pan, then add 3 tablespoons nuts. Add remaining nuts, sugar, water and margarine in saucepan.
Heat to boil and add cinnamon. Cut biscuits in fourths.
Place fourths of biscuits in pan.
Pour or sprinkle half of heated mixture on biscuits, then place another layer of biscuits and remaining mixture on top. Bake.

title: simmered round steak and vegetables
directions: Pound trimmed meat with mallet.
Cut into serving pieces.
Set aside.
Mix 4 tablespoons flour, salt and pepper in plastic bag. Add beef and shake to coat meat.
Heat cooking oil in large skillet.
Add beef and flour mixture.
Brown over medium heat. Layer onion, green pepper and carrots over beef and sprinkle with basil.
Add wine and heat to boil.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 1 hour until meat is tender.
Transfer beef and vegetables to serving plate.
Place cold water in small bowl.
Blend 2 tablespoons flour and stir into drippings in skillet.
Stir in bouillon granules.
Cover and use medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cooked icing
directions: Measure sugar, cold water and unbeaten egg into top of double boiler.
Place over rapidly boiling water and commence beating at once.
Beat until light and fluffy and holds its shape, about 7 or 8 minutes.
Remove from fire and continue beating until thick.

title: round-ups
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the flour, sugar, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Stir in cream and eggs; mix just until combined.
Stir in raisins or dates, if desired.
On a lightly floured surface, knead dough 10 to 12 times.
Pat to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with a 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cabbage ramen slaw
directions: Brown last 4 ingredients together.
Mix cabbage, onions, chicken, noodles and almonds, then sprinkle seasoning from noodles and mix.
Add oil and vinegar and mix again.
The flavors mix together better if it's refrigerated overnight.

title: frozen corn
directions: Cut tomatoes in half.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper. Mix bread crumbs with garlic and olive oil.
Spread over cut tomatoes.
Sprinkle with Romano or Parmesan cheese.
Broil just until barely brown.
Remove from heat.
These can be done ahead, then put back in oven to warm through before serving.

title: veal cordon bleu
directions: On each piece of veal, place a slice each of ham and cheese. Roll up carefully, beginning at narrow end.
Secure with wooden picks.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and allspice.
Coat rolls with mixture.
Drop rolls into egg, then into bread crumbs.
Heat the fat in a 10-inch skillet.
Brown the veal rolls, about 5 minutes. Add the water.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover, and simmer about 45 minutes.
Remove cover the last 3 to 5 minutes to crisp the veal.
Makes 4 servings.

title: wandering jesus
directions: May be rolled or dropped, about 1 heaping teaspoonful.
Bake at 375° until light brown.

title: carrot soup
directions: Melt butter in large pot or Dutch oven, stir in onions and cook until soft.
Stir in carrots, chicken stock, tomato paste and rice.
Simmer gently, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Puree in blender. Stir in cream.
To serve, simmer, stir in butter (optional) and season to taste.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Melt shortening in large skillet. Coat chicken with flour.
Cook in shortening over medium heat for 15 to 20 minutes or until light brown.
Remove chicken; set aside. Add onion rings, green pepper and garlic to skillet; cook and stir over medium heat until onion and pepper are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Add chicken to sauce.
Cover tightly; simmer 30 to 40 minutes, or until thickest pieces are fork-tender. Can serve with hot fluffy rice or spaghetti.
Makes 4 servings.

title: homemade egg noodles
directions: Beat the first 3 ingredients with a fork until smooth.
Add evaporated milk to equal amount of egg yolk mixture.
Add flour until you can't stir, then knead.
Quit just before it starts flaking.

title: tangy frozen fruit
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Freeze overnight.
Thaw slightly before serving.
Can use small muffin tins (spray with Pam; pop out and store in freezer.
May be used as light dessert or as a frozen salad.

title: easy can soup
directions: Brown onion and hamburger; drain grease.
Put "cans" in pot; do not drain.
Add water.
Add browned onion and hamburger. Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: chef's salad
directions: Wash all vegetables; drain and cut.
Combine all ingredients in large salad bowl.
Garnish with hard-cooked egg slices, if desired.
Serve with desired dressing.
Zesty Italian is a favorite.

title: fresh apple bread
directions: Blend eggs, sugar and oil.
Add soda and salt to flour.
Add chopped apples to sugar and flour mixture and mix well.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: cranberry orange cooler
directions: Combine cranberry juice cocktail, orange juice and water in a pitcher.
Stir to mix.
Chill.
Pour into glasses and garnish with orange slices if you wish.
Makes 9 (8 ounce) servings.

title: cocoa-cola icing
directions: Put butter, cocoa and cola in a pan and bring to a boil. Remove from heat.
Add sugar, vanilla and nuts; spread on cake while hot.

title: amish barbecue(pork, turkey, chicken)
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over meat. Cook, covered, at 375° for 1 or 1 1/2 hours until meat is tender.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add broccoli and onion and stir until broccoli thaws and separates. Add low-fat cottage cheese, mayonnaise and mustard.
Makes 3 cups or 6 servings with 40 calories per serving.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, then add buttermilk and flour alternately.
Also add soda to flour.
Bake in 3 bread loaf pans at 300° for 1 hour.
Cut wax paper and put in bottom of pans.

title: cake for diabetics
directions: Put strawberries on top of cake.
Mix jello and pour over cake.
Refrigerate and let jello set.
Serve with prepared low calorie Cool Whip.

title: raw broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, Hidden Valley and sour cream good and let stand 24 hours.
Mix with vegetables.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Fry and drain ground beef.
Cook noodles and drain.
Saute green pepper and onion.
Mix all ingredients together and put in a casserole dish.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni slices. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Freezes well!

title: easy punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin, Kool-Aid and sugar in hot water.
Add cold water, pineapple juice and ginger ale.
Stir and chill.
(Can add orange sherbet to chilled punch.)
Makes 30 servings.
Add any type Kool-Aid to give any flavor.

title: broccoli-onion deluxe
directions: Cook broccoli and onions in boiling salt water until tender (about 8 minutes).
Drain.
Melt butter or oleo, blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk all at once, cook and stir until bubbly.
Blend in cream cheese.
Remove from heat, stir in wine. Fold in vegetables.
Put into 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven from 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle almonds over top.

title: cinnamon twists
directions: Bring cream to boil; add shortening, sugar, soda and salt. Mix well; cool.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix yeast with cream mixture.
Add flour; knead until smooth.
Cover with damp cloth 5 minutes.
Roll into rectangle 1/4-inch thick.
Spread with butter.

title: fruit salad
directions: Sprinkle dry pudding mix over ingredients and mix.
Add 1 large container of Cool Whip.
Garnish with cherries and nuts.

title: white texas sheet cake
directions: In large saucepan, bring butter and water to boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour, sugar, eggs, sour cream, almond extract, salt and baking soda until smooth.
Pour into greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 22 minutes or until cake is golden brown.
Cool for 2 minutes.

title: pecan meltaways
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream the butter, sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Combine the flour and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in pecans.
Chill.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while warm.
Cool and roll in sugar again. Yields about 4 dozen.

title: fantastic dessert
directions: Combine first three ingredients, mixing well.
Press flour mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; let cool completely

title: sock it to me coffee cake
directions: Beat eggs, sour cream, oil and water into cake mix.
Beat well.
Pour half of batter into small tube pan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Sprinkle over batter in pan.
Add rest of batter.
Sprinkle with a little sugar.
Bake in a 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put Stove Top stuffing crumbs in a 1 1/2-quart pan.
Combine water, margarine and seasoning from Stove Top and bring to a boil in a medium saucepan.
Pour liquid mixture over crumbs and mix well.
Make a hole in the center of the crumb mixture by pressing with a spoon.
Fill the hole with chicken.
Blend soup and milk, then pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: jerry's salad
directions: Mix together.
Fold in 1 large bowl Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mixture may be refrigerated up to one month.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mom's brownies
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add eggs, chocolate syrup, flour and baking powder.
Pour in jelly roll pan (or 9 x 13-inch pan).
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pineapple yam apple casserole
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and pineapple juice.
Then add lemon juice and butter.
Mix well.
Peel and slice apples.
In a 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole dish alternate layers of sliced yams, apples and pineapple chunks.
Pour sauce over.
Bake at 325° for one hour, stirring 2 or 3 times during cooking.
Garnish top with sliced pineapple and cherries.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, margarine and sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: italian spaghetti with olive oil
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
In frying pan, as spaghetti cooks, add garlic to oil.
Brown.
Drain spaghetti.
Pour oil-garlic mixture on top of the spaghetti. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and as much cheese as desired.

title: endive with caviar
directions: Combine first four ingredients; beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until smooth.
Spread in middle of endive leaves and lightly sprinkle with caviar.
Makes 8 servings.

title: apple crunch salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold juice and cinnamon and chill until thickened. Fold in apple, celery and nuts.
Spoon into 6-cup mold or bowl.
Chill until firm, about 4 hours.
Makes 5 cups or 10 servings.

title: chocolate pie (lo-cal)
directions: Mix Rice Krispies, peanut butter and honey for crust and set aside.
Mix pudding according to box directions.
Place sliced bananas over crust, then spread pudding over this, alternating until pie pan is full.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: turkey smoked sausage rice skillet
directions: Cut sausage into serving size pieces.
Set aside.
Saute mushrooms, carrots and zucchini in margarine in skillet over medium-high heat for 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes with juice, water, basil, thyme and sausage.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Mix rice into liquid, cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes, stirring after 4 minutes.
Serves 4.
One serving: 3 1/2 protein, 1 vegetable, 1 bread and 1/3 fat.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Go to Foodland nearest you.
Go directly to frozen foods section and find Riches homemade rolls.
Follow directions.
When your family tells you how great they are, simply wipe your forehead and say, "Nothing is too good for my family."

title: hamburger surprise
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together.
Cook macaroni separately. After all are done, mix in casserole dish.
Add grated cheese on top.
Bake until cheese melts at 325°.

title: santa's whiskers
directions: In bowl, cream together butter and sugar.
Blend in milk and rum extract.
Stir in flour, candied cherries and pecans.
Form in 2 rolls, each 2 x 8-inches long.
Roll in coconut.
Wrap in wax paper and chill overnight.
Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 12 minutes or until edges are golden.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: german cake
directions: Cream the soft margarine.
Add sugar.
Mix in egg, vanilla and milk.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to sugar mixture.

title: baked spanish rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
In a large skillet over medium heat, fry bacon crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Crumble and set aside.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons bacon drippings.
In hot drippings, cook onions and green pepper until tender.
In a measuring cup, drain tomatoes; add enough water to tomato liquid to make 1 3/4 cups liquid.
Cut up tomatoes.
To onion mixture, add liquid, tomatoes, tomato sauce, sugar and salt; heat to boiling.
Remove from heat and stir in rice.
Pour into casserole.
Cover casserole and bake 35 minutes or until rice is tender.
Fluff rice with fork.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes.
Garnish with bacon.

title: baked carrots
directions: Scrape carrots; cut into 2-inch pieces.
Cook in salted water until tender; drain, saving 1/2 cup liquid for sauce.
Arrange carrots in buttered casserole.
Mix mayonnaise, horseradish, onion, pepper and water; pour over carrots.
Dot with butter (3 or 4 tablespoons).
Bake at 350° for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: katie's pumpkin pie filling
directions: Mix together.
Put in crust and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vern's light desserts
directions: Mix margarine, flour and sugar well.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 minutes at 325° until light brown.
Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar well.
Add 1/2 of Cool Whip in the cheese mixture.
Cool.
Mix the dry puddings together and beat with milk. Pour over cheese mixture.
Put the rest of Cool Whip on top of all and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: ice cream
directions: Finish filling freezer with whole milk.
Mix peaches and 1/2 cup sugar in blender until mushy.

title: garlic grits
directions: Cook grits by directions on box.
Add butter and cheese while hot.
Stir until melted; blend well then add milk and eggs beaten in milk.
Add milk and egg mixture to grits.
Bake in buttered 6 x 10-inch casserole dish at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill until ready to serve.

title: hush puppy dumplings
directions: Mix dry ingredients first.
Blend egg with buttermilk.
Mix all ingredients together.
Let set for a few minutes.
Will be stiff batter.
Roll into balls.
Put in hot fat (375°) and fry until brown.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Bring syrup to a boil.
Cook 1 minute.
Let stand until cool and pour over cabbage mixture.
Freeze.
Will stay firm and not turn dark.

title: spinach bars
directions: Drain spinach.
In large bowl, mix together the eggs, flour, milk and baking powder until smooth.
Stir in spinach, onion, bacon, cheese and mushrooms.
Melt butter into a baking dish. Pour mixture into dish.
Sprinkle with crushed fried onion rings. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool slightly and cut into small squares.
Makes about 40 bars. Reheats well.

title: sweet-sour carrots
directions: Arrange carrots in casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
