Simmer for 15 minutes and strain.
Pour over carrots.
Cover and chill for 24 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: In a large pot, combine butter and flour.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly, until brown.
Add water, tomatoes, okra, corn (cut into thirds if large or half if small cobs).
Cook slowly (simmer) for 1 hour.
Add crab, oysters, shrimp, fish, cayenne, bay leaves, salt and pepper.
Cook 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach; squeeze all water out.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together, all except the bread.
Refrigerate overnight.
When ready to serve, hollow bread out and save inside pieces.
Pour spinach dip in hollow.
Take inside pieces of bread and break up in chunks and lay around bread loaf to dip in spinach dip.
Enjoy!

title: butterfinger bars
directions: Mix together.
Put on cookie sheet or cake pan.
Melt 1 package chocolate chips.
Pour on top.
Eat.

title: keebler peach crunch
directions: Arrange drained peaches in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Combine rest of ingredients until crumbly.
Sprinkle over peaches and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Topping will be crunchy when done.
Good served with ice cream or Cool Whip.
Or eat it cold right out of the refrigerator.
So good, you'll want to eat it any way.
Fast and easy too!

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Saute corned beef, onion and green pepper.
Pour into casserole dish.
Add 1 or 2 cans soup. Sprinkle cheese on top. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Pour melted butter evenly over casserole.
Bake and brown at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Serve with green peas.

title: roast and gravy
directions: This recipe works well when you put the roast in frozen, but it can be done with out freezing the roast.
Salt and pepper the roast on top and bottom.
Place in roasting pan and cover with foil.
Place in 375 degree oven and cook for 1hour, then turn down to 200 degrees and continue cooking for 3-4 hours.
Remove from oven,
if the roast isn't brown remove foil and return to oven to brown.
When the roast is done, place on platter.
For gravy, place pan with drippings on stove top and heat on med-high heat to brown.
In a jar, shake up water and flour until well blended, when drippings are browned well pour in water and flour, heat, stirring until thick.
May need to add more salt and pepper to gravy.
Serve roast with hot biscuits and gravy!!!! :4
Note:
The secret to this recipe is to cook at a low temp. for a long time.

title: hearty beef stew
directions: Trim all fat from meat.
Put all ingredients in slow cooker; mix thoroughly.
Cover and cook on low for 12 hours (or on high for 5 to 6 hours).

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Mix together sugar and oil.
Blend in egg, vanilla and milk. In separate bowl, combine flour, salt, cinnamon and baking soda. Add to moist ingredients.
Stir in rhubarb and nuts.
Divide batter between 2 well-greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until bread tests done with wooden pick. Turn out onto rack to cool.
Yield: 2 loaves.

title: orange sauce(very good over ham)
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in orange juice and cook until thick and clear, stirring constantly.
Add orange peel.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.
Can be made up ahead of time.

title: company cheese cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add cream cheese, sugar, salt and vanilla. Beat until smooth.
Beat in sour cream.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool and chill.

title: homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion in oil, add remaining ingredients and simmer on low heat for 1 hour.

title: oriental rice
directions: Fry peppers, onion and carrots until onions are transparent. Put in large bowl.
Cook rice; add to bowl.
Brown chopped meat; add to bowl.
Scramble the eggs together and cook; add to bowl. Mix all ingredients together and add soy sauce until everything turns a nice brown.

title: crab ball
directions: Wash celery and separate stalks.
Carefully cut off both ends. Fill celery with peanut butter.
Add raisin "ants" to the peanut butter.
Serve.

title: chili sauce for hot dogs
directions: In large skillet, on low heat, cook ground beef until browned, constantly beating meat to a very fine consistency.
Add seasoned salt while cooking.
Pour into strainer to drain well.
Use 3 tablespoons drippings and return to skillet.
Saute onion until clear and tender.
Add drained beef.
Toss well.
Add remaining ingredients.
When mixture reaches boil, lower heat to simmer for 1 hour.
Quick cool by setting pan in ice before storing overnight in refrigerator.
Remove solidified fat before reheating.
Makes 30 servings.

title: easy carmalitas
directions: Press cookie dough into the bottom a well greased 9 by 13-inch baking dish.
Top uniformly with unwrapped caramels.
Sprinkle chocolate morsels evenly over caramels.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
tags: roll refrigerated chocolate chip cookie dough

title: beef fried rice
directions: Fry beef cubes.
Saute vegetables until soft.
Soft scramble eggs and add vanilla.
Fry rice in soy sauce and butter or oil. Combine all ingredients, salt and pepper to taste and serve.
Any kind of meat, fish or chicken may be substituted for beef.

title: buttered pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar.
Beat well.
Then add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour.
Add salt, soda and baking powder.
Add alternately with buttermilk to the first mixture. Add vanilla, then beat well.
Pour into well-greased tube pan and bake at 325° about 1 hour or 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: hot chocolate dry mix
directions: Mix well and store in airtight container.
Put 1/3 cup of mix in cup; fill with hot water.
Add marshmallows, if desired.

title: crab and corn bisque
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan over medium-high heat.
Add the flour and cook, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes.
Add the vegetables and cook for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add the broth (crab juice and water mixture), 1 teaspoon salt, pepper and bay leaves.
Stir in the crab, milk and Old Bay and bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat to low and simmer for 25 minutes. Remove from heat and fold in the Worcestershire sauce and remaining salt to taste.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: Mix. Pour in muffin pan with paper liners and freeze. When frozen in you may take out of pan and put in plastic bag.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all together; serve on whole wheat toast or buns.

title: janet's stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cut stems from mushrooms and set mushroom caps aside.
Saute mushroom stems and onion with sausage until tender.
Let cool slightly and add bread or cracker crumbs.
Spoon into mushroom caps and place on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° until caps are tender, about 15 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, flour and butter.
Pour in milk and flavoring.
Cook in unbaked crust 30 minutes at 400°.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Boil in saucepan or microwave the oleo, Crisco and water.
Pour this over flour, sugar and salt.
Add buttermilk, soda, eggs and vanilla to first mixture.

title: bread dough clay for fun
directions: Mix well salt and flour.
Add hot water.
Knead well.
Shape into desired figures and bake 1 hour at 300°.
Great project for little children, vacation bible school prints/projects/painted name tags and even for at home.

title: sausage-cheese chips
directions: Coarsely chop kielbasa and set aside.
Arrange chips on greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Sprinkle sausage and cheese evenly over each chip, top with chilies.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° until cheese melts, 3 to 5 minutes.
Serves 6; 40 calories each serving.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and extracts.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with preserves and sour cream.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: joe obey's bread
directions: Mix ingredients together and knead until firm and elastic. Let raise 10 minutes.
Punch down.
Let raise until double.
Put in bread pan and raise again.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sweet potato cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except flour.
Add flour.
Work in gradually. Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Cook at 350° until done.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix mashed sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla and margarine (first 5 ingredients).
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Mix brown sugar, flour and margarine.
Spread on top of potatoes.
Top with pecans.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: johnson meat loaf
directions: In large bowl combine all ingredients.
Mix meat thoroughly with hands until all signs of egg are gone and tomato sauce is completely mixed in.
Shape into loaf.
Place in loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 400°.
Halfway through cooking, spread catsup on top of meat loaf to brown.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Sift flour and next 4 ingredients.
Cut in butter with 2 knives or pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in raisins and seeds.
Mix together vinegar and milk.
Make a well in flour mixture and add liquid all at once, stirring with a fork until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn out on a lightly floured board.
Knead gently 8 to 10 times.
Shape into a ball.
Place in greased pie plate.
Cut a cross from side to side.
Brush top with milk.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then 375° for 30 more minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: robert e. lee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 3 (8-inch) round layer pans.
In large mixer bowl, mix butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Beat for 5 minutes on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
On low speed, mix in flour, baking powder and salt, alternately with milk.
Pour into pans.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: strawberrioca
directions: Thaw and drain strawberries.
Add water to juice to make 2 1/2 cups.
Mix liquid, tapioca, sugar and salt.
Let stand 5 minutes. Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Cool 20 minutes.
Stir in berries and fold in 8 ounces Cool Whip.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add beaten eggs.
Add flour and mix well.
Add nuts.
Shape.
Refrigerate and slice.
Bake at 350.

title: red raspberry jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot water.
Add applesauce and thoroughly mix. Add raspberries.
Refrigerate until set.

title: double chocolate chip cookie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and vanilla, beat well. Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.

title: sharon's lemon delight
directions: Combine the margarine, flour and pecans.
Mix and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Let this cool. Combine the Eagle Brand milk and lemonade concentrate.
Fold in 1 container Cool Whip and spread over the cooled crust.
Refrigerate 30 minutes, then spread the can of lemon pie filling on the second layer.
Top this layer with more Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pumpkin nut cookies
directions: Cream the shortening; gradually add sugar.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and pumpkin; mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and spices together.
Stir in dry ingredients and mix until blended.
Add raisins and nuts.

title: angel food roll
directions: Mix to pea size the flour and oleo.
Blend the remaining ingredients and add to flour mix.
Form into 6 balls and chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: In large bowl, stir together first five ingredients until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss to coat well.
Cover and chill.
Best if sits overnight before serving.
Makes about five cups.

title: apple-sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil sweet potatoes; cool and peel.
Butter sides and bottom of 9 x 13 baking dish.
Slice sweet potatoes 3/4-inch thick and place on bottom of dish.
Peel and slice apples; place layer on potatoes.
Pour half the syrup over them; sprinkle with cinnamon. Repeat the potatoes and apples with the apples on top.
Pour remainder of syrup over them; sprinkle with cinnamon and dot with butter.
Add 1/4 to 1/2 cup water.
Bake in 350° oven until hot and bubbling.
Serve hot or room temperature.
If you don't have fresh apples, you may substitute apple pie filling and omit the water.

title: smoked salmon rolls
directions: Blend cream cheese with sour cream.
Gently fold in caviar and spread on slices with mixture.
Roll up and cut into 1 1/2-inch lengths.
Serve chilled.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apple-lemon punch
directions: In large pitcher, combine juice, lemonade and soft drink. Serve over ice cubes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients to soft ball stage, around 15 minutes. Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in buttered baking dish and let set.

title: ranchers pasta
directions: Soften tomato halves using package directions; cut in strips. Heat oil in large skillet; add garlic and saute 2 minutes.
Add olives, tomatoes and oregano.
Cook 2 more minutes.
Add grated cheese and pasta mix until blended.
Serve.

title: dove pie
directions: Brown doves in butter first.
Then cook covered with small amount of liquid (water or bouillon) until tender and breast can be easily pulled off the bone.
Saute mushrooms and onions in butter until just soft.
Combine dove meat with vegetables and olives and add enough brown gravy mix so that the mixture is juicy and moist but not too thin and runny.
Spray PAM in a 9x13-inch pyrex dish and spread mixture evenly into dish.
Top with crisscrossed strips of pastry sheets which have been rolled out quite thin.
Spray with PAM.
Bake at 350 degrees until the pastry is puffed and golden brown.
Yield:
12 to 14 servings.

title: 15-minute chicken and rice dinner
directions: Heat oil in skillet. Add chicken and cook until browned. Remove chicken. Add soup, water, paprika and pepper. Stir. Heat to a boil. Stir in rice and broccoli. Top with chicken. Season chicken with additional paprika and pepper; cover. Cook on low heat 5 minutes or until cooked through.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix sugars, butter and shortening; add eggs and the soda dissolved in 1 tablespoon boiling water.
Mix well.
Add flour and nuts.
Dough may seem a little dry.
Pack dough in a wax paper lined 8 x 8-inch square pan; cover with wax paper and refrigerate overnight.
Cut dough into thirds; cut each third into 1/4-inch (or less) slices.
Bake at 350° about 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Spray 8 ramekins or other ovenproof dishes with nonstick spray. Set on a baking sheet and set aside. In top of a double boiler or heatproof bowl over simmering water, stir together the cream of chicken soup, Cheddar cheese soup and mayonnaise. Stir well, using a rubber spatula, until the Cheddar sauce has a smooth, airy consistency, about 5 to 8 minutes. Stir the drained potatoes into the sauce. Evenly divide the potato mixture among the prepared ramekins and generously sprinkle the tops with paprika. Bake in preheated 350° oven about 20 minutes or until they are bubbly and the paprika darkens a little. Remove the potatoes from the oven and let them stand a few minutes before serving.

title: court bouillon
directions: Brown flour in oil.
Add onion, bell pepper and green onion and saute.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, 2 cups water, salt and pepper.
Heat mixture throughout.
Add fish cut into 2-inch squares and stir only once!
Stirring will break the fish.
Serve over rice.

title: chocolate mayonnaise sheet cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add salad dressing and vanilla.
Add water.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix warm water and yeast together until dissolved.
Stir in sugar, salt, oil and egg.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time, mixing well.
Do not knead.
Let rise until double in size.

title: munching peanut brittle
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together sugar and syrup. Microwave on High 4 minutes, stirring one time half-way through. Stir in peanuts; microwave on High 4 minutes until light brown, stirring once.
Add butter and vanilla; blend well.
Microwave on High 1 minute.
Peanuts will be lightly brown and syrup very hot. Add baking soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour mixture onto lightly greased cookie sheet or unbuttered nonstick coated cookie sheet.
Let cool 1/2 to 1 hour.
When cool, break into small pieces and store in airtight container.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatine in cold water.
To the beaten egg yolks, add 1/3 cup sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Cook in double boiler over hot, not boiling, water, stirring constantly until of custard consistency.
Add softened gelatine and stir until dissolved.
Add grated lemon rind.
Chill until mixture is consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites to which the remaining 1/3 cup sugar has been added. Pour into baked pastry shell or crumb crust.
Chill until firm.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired, and chopped walnut meats.
Yields one (9-inch) pie.

title: no-peek chicken
directions: Pour all ingredients over chicken breasts in a 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 3 hours in a 250° oven.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mash bananas and add sugar - let stand about 15 minutes. Sift flour, add baking powder, salt and dissolve soda in about 1 Tbsp. of water.
Add shortening to banana and sugar mixture and beat thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients, soda, beaten eggs and nuts. Stir only until mixed.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Trim and shred cabbage.
In a bowl add cabbage, onion, salt and boiling water.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Drain into colander and press water from vegetables.
Put into large serving bowl.
Add vinegar and toss.
Season with pepper and serve.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Blend sugar and cocoa.
Add butter and milk.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Stir.
Drop from a teaspoon onto waxed paper, then let cool 45 minutes.

title: vegetable appetizer pie
directions: Open rolls and spread flat on two cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° until slightly brown on bottom.
Remove from oven and sprinkle on grated cheese while crusts are still warm.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix in a bowl; spread evenly over the two baked crusts.
Add any combination of chopped vegetables and press down into the filling.
Refrigerate overnight for best flavor. Cut into finger-serving sized pieces and serve.
Makes 90 small pieces.

title: hobo stew
directions: Brown ground beef in small amount of oil.
Cook pepper and onions at same time.
Add all other ingredients; simmer for 30 minutes.

title: appetizer ribs(microwave)
directions: Cut ribs into 1-rib pieces.
Place pieces in 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover and cook at Medium-high or cook power 7 (70%) for 15 minutes.
Drain fat; turn and rearrange ribs. Combine the remaining ingredients; pour over ribs.
Cover; cook, covered, at Medium-high or cook power 7 (70%) for 10 minutes. Test for thorough doneness; add more cooking time, if necessary. Serve hot.
Makes 36.

title: diet chicken
directions: Add water to chicken and mix spices together.
Add 1/2 spices to top of chicken and cook 30 minutes.
Turn and add rest of spices.
Cook until done.

title: cooked cabbage
directions: Shred the cabbage into small strips.
Put in a frypan with little water.
Sprinkle on a little red pepper and a little sugar. Place bacon strips over the cabbage or you may use butter or margarine. Cover and cook 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes to 1 hour before serving.

title: snowballs
directions: Mix
butter,
sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
Stir flour and salt
together; blend into butter mixture.
Mix in pecans. Chill dough
minutes
to 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°.
Roll dough into
1-inch
balls
and place on ungreased baking sheet (cookies don't
spread).
Bake
10 to 12 minutes or until set, but not brown.
While still warm, roll in confectioners sugar. Let cool and roll again.
Makes 4 dozen.
Don't use self-rising flour!

title: "tastelicious" impossible pie
directions: Beat eggs; blend sugar, flour and baking powder.
Add eggs and mix.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into greased pie pan.
It makes its own crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: seven bean soup
directions: Add enough water and choice of seasonings. Mix all ingredients in a large crock-pot. Simmer on high for 1 hour. Reduce heat to low and simmer until tender as desired. Serve warm with soup crackers.

title: baked eggplant
directions: In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, alternate layers of tomato juice, sliced eggplant (which have been sprinkled with salt and pepper), garlic and parsley.
Top all with cheese and strips of green pepper.
Cover with foil, slash the top of foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: "burrito" pie
directions: About 1 hour before serving, fry tortillas, one at a time, in salad oil about 30 seconds on each side until lightly browned and blistered.
Drain on paper towels.
Preheat oven to 350°.

In same skillet over high heat, fry hamburger and onion until done. Drain, then add green chilies, refried beans, taco sauce and salt. In 9-inch pie pan, place 1 tortilla; top with 1/4 of bean mixture and 1/4 cheese.
Repeat 3 times.
Bake for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Top with lettuce, tomato and more taco sauce. Sour cream is also good with it.

title: 9 day cole slaw
directions: Put in saucepan:
sugar, celery seed, dry mustard, salad oil and vinegar.
Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Cool and pour over cabbage.
Mix.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand overnight.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in order listed.
Blend throughly and shape into loaf and place in greased pan.
Bake in 350° oven until done for 1 hour.

title: catsup(diabetic)
directions: Puree first 4 ingredients.
Pour mixture into pan; add vinegar, salt and sweetener.
Tie spices loosely in cheesecloth and add.
Simmer uncovered until reduced by about half.
Remove bag of spices.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cook and stir first 4 ingredients in hot oil over medium-high heat until tender, but not browned, about 5 minutes.
Stir in beans with liquid, cooked rice, salt and pepper.
Reduce heat and stir gently until beans are hot.
Makes 5 servings.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13 inch dish, sprinkle in rice, add chicken, onion, and salt.
Spoon soup over chicken, pour water, cover and bake at 350° for one hour and 25 minutes.
You may sprinkle Paprika on top if desired.

title: chicken hawaiian
directions: Skin chicken breasts.
Make marinade, stirring together pineapple juice, garlic, soy sauce, parsley and chicken stock. Place chicken in a baking dish and cover with marinade. Refrigerate for at least 6 hours.
Remove chicken from refrigerator 1 hour before cooking and allow it to come to room temperature.
Leave chicken in same pan and place in oven at 350 degrees for 20 minutes or until lightly browned or cook on grill until done.
Serve with a slice of pineapple.
Or cut into 1 inch cubes served on wooden toothpicks, alternating chicken with pineapple chunks.

title: sausage--potato breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage. Prepare hash browns according to package directions, using 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper. Stir together sausage, hash browns and cheese. Pour in a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Whisk together eggs, milk and remaining 1 teaspoon of salt. Pour evenly over potato mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: harvest loaf
directions: Mix all in one method.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Reduce heat after 1/2 hour.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes. Beat with mixer until smooth. Add nuts, if desired. Pour onto buttered plate or waxed paper.
Refrigerate to set.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix brown sugar, shortening, margarine, vanilla and egg yolk.
Stir in flour and salt until dough holds together.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Beat egg whites slightly. Dip each ball into egg white; roll in nuts.
Place about 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press thumb deeply in center of each.
Bake until light brown about 10 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet; cool.
Fill thumbprints with jelly. Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: phyllis's chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and bananas.
Stir in dry ingredients and nuts.
Place in well-greased and floured loaf pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: marinade for brisket roast
directions: Double all ingredients, except barbecue sauce.
Mix and pour over roast and let it stay in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 300° for 3 1/2 hours.
Open foil and cook 1 hour.
Cool and slice thin.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook vanilla pudding.
Add milk and raisins; let stand 10 minutes.
Add about 1 1/2 cups cooked rice and a small amount of cinnamon.
If pudding gets too thick, add a little milk.

title: dill dip for raw vegetables
directions: Chill for 1 hour.

title: nacho shrimp dip
directions: Slowly melt cream cheese and salsa, stirring continuously. Stir in rest of ingredients.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: zucchini bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla and oil.
In another bowl, sift together flour, salt, baking soda, powder and cinnamon.
Add grated zucchini to egg mixture alternating with flour mixture. Add nuts and raisins.
Bake in greased and floured pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream clam dip
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together sour cream, chopped onion, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Spoon into shallow serving dish.
Swirl cocktail sauce over top.
Serve with crackers, cocktail bread or chips.

title: cream cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, blending well.
Shape into balls and bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until slightly brown.
Remove and roll in powdered sugar.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix peanut butter and shortening into cake mix. Add eggs and water.
Mix well. Shape into
1 1/2-inch balls and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hamburger
directions: Make hamburger into patties.
Coat with flour and brown lightly in oil.
Add mushroom soup and simmer for about 15 minutes.

title: swiss cheese corn
directions: Cook corn in boiling water 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain well. Combine corn with evaporated milk, egg, chopped onions, salt, pepper and shredded cheese.

title: 3 baked bean hot dish
directions: Brown the hamburger, bacon and onions. Add the ketchup, brown sugar, mustard and salt. Bake 4 hours in crockpot.

title: fresh plum bubble
directions: Combine plums and pineapple tidbits in a 10-inch ovenproof baking dish.
Mix sugar and cornstarch together and stir into fruit mixture.
Dot with butter/oleo and bake in a 400° preheated oven and top with biscuits.
Brush biscuits with melted butter/oleo and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Continue baking at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes longer.
Serve warm.
This is a great dish for brunch or can be topped with whipped cream or ice cream for dessert.

title: shrimp in cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour.
Stir in milk.
Stir until sauce thickens and boils.
Add salt, pepper, cheese soup and shrimp. Bring to a boil.
Place in baking dish.
Top with slices of Cheddar cheese and bake 10 minutes until cheese melts at 400°. (Can be served over noodles, etc.)

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: Place chicken in large greased baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place sauerkraut over chicken.
Top with Swiss cheese.
Pour dressing evenly over cheese.
Sprinkle with crushed rye chips; cover with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley and serve.

title: surprise cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter with electric mixer.
Beat in brown sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Blend in vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients until blended.
Arrange English walnut halves on cookie sheets, about 2-inches apart.
Shape dough into balls, using 1 tablespoon of dough for each.
Press each ball onto walnut half.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until cookie tests done.
Cool to warm.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, softened sharp cheese and pimento cheese.
Mix well until blended.
Add chopped green peppers, onion, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and salt.
Mix well.
Chill.
Shape into a ball and roll in chopped pecans.

title: alda's hot cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Melt cheese into meat. Add picante sauce to mixture.
Keep hot in slow cooker and serve with nacho chips.

title: crab and shrimp quiches
directions: Bake pie shells until light brown.
Line the shells with the Swiss.
Combine the beaten eggs, sour cream and chowder in a bowl; mix well.
Stir in shrimp, crab meat, mushrooms and seasonings. Pour evenly into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut
biscuits in half.	Dip each piece in melted butter to cover.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Layer covered biscuits
in
Bundt
pan that has been buttered.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese and onion appetizer
directions: Mix all together thoroughly and spread on bread slices.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Broil for just a few seconds or until lightly brown.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: jelly roll
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into a large flat pan (greased and floured).
Bake in moderate oven until top rises and is brown.
Turn out on a towel and spread with jelly; roll immediately.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Spray muffin tins with Pam. Stir dry ingredients together. Set aside. Combine egg, milk and oil, mix well. Remove quarter cup of dry ingredients and sprinkle over blueberries. Stir gently. Set aside. Combine liquid and dry ingredients, stir until smooth. Add blueberries and stir gently. Fill muffin tins 3/4 full. Bake at 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus and layer in casserole dish.
Place mushrooms on top of asparagus.
Spread soup over the two, adding seasoning salt and garlic salt (sprinkle small amounts), then slice eggs on top and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: carol channing's hello dolly bars
directions: Melt
butter
in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.	Sprinkle
in
a layer each of graham cracker crumbs, coconut,
chocolate	bits and nuts. Pour condensed milk over the nuts.
Cook in
pan at 350°
for
30 minutes.
Cool and cut into 16
squares.
Delicious!

title: moo goo gai pan
directions: Fry chicken for 30 seconds.
Boil bok choy 1 minute.
Add vegetables and garlic to hot oil.
Stir-fry 1 minute.
Add chicken.
Stir-fry 1 minute.
Add sauce and bring to a boil. Serve with rice.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Roll crackers into crumbs.
Chop cherries and pecans.
Melt margarine and marshmallows.
Combine marshmallow mixture with crumbs and cherry liquid.
Add cherries, raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Form into long roll on wax paper (will be sticky).
Roll in wax paper and then roll in aluminum foil.
Refrigerate.
Cut into slices as needed.
Yield: 3 large rolls.

title: reese's cup candy
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan.
Add graham cracker crumbs, peanut butter and confectioners sugar, mixing well.
Pat down firmly in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan (a slightly later pan may be used).
Melt the Hershey candy bar and smooth on top.
Let cool before cutting.

title: christmas fruit tea
directions: Pour first 5 ingredients into (30-cup) electric percolator. Place nutmeg, cinnamon and ginger in percolator basket.
Perk complete cycle; let stand 1 hour.
Serve hot.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: mary's potato salad
directions: Peel, cube and cook potatoes until real tender.
While cooking, put on eggs to boil.
Dice vegetables.
Drain water off cooked ingredients.
Add onions, pickles and 5 eggs to potatoes. Then stir in mustard, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Slice 6th egg in slices and place on top of salad.

title: cocktail dogs
directions: Cut hot dogs in little pieces.
Mix jelly and mustard together; pour over hot dogs in crock-pot and let simmer at least 2 hours.
Better if left in crock-pot all day!

title: deviled ham puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend together cream cheese, egg yolk, onion, baking powder, salt and horseradish.
Toast bread on one side.
Spread onto toasted sides with deviled ham and cover each with a mound of the cheese mixture.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until puffed and brown.
Serve hot. These can be prepared ahead and frozen.
Thaw and bake.
Melba toast may be substituted for the bread.

title: jiffy cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix cake mix, yeast, salt and warm water.
Add 3 cups flour. Use the remaining flour to knead dough.
Knead 6 to 8 minutes.

title: orangey harvard beets
directions: Mix all ingredients, except beets in microwave dish, covered. Microwave 3 1/2 minutes.
Stir until smooth and thickened.
Add drained beets and microwave 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir and serve hot.

title: pea salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order given.

title: disgustingly rich brownies
directions: Grease the inside of an 8 or 9-inch baking pan.
Melt the butter over low heat.
In the mixing bowl, stir the cocoa and sugar together, then stir in the melted butter.
Add the eggs and vanilla and stir again.
Now add the flour and salt; mix just until smooth, not too much.
(If adding chocolate chips, now is the time.)

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over broccoli.
Add cheese; let set overnight in refrigerator.
Add bacon.
May add salt and pepper before serving.
Garnish with red onion slices (optional).
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pennsylvania dutch green beans
directions: Leave 1 tablespoon bacon fat in pan.
Add onion; brown lightly.
Combine cornstarch, salt and mustard in cup.
Drain beans and reserve 1/2 cup liquid.
Stir bean liquid and vinegar into dry ingredients and add to pot.
Stir until it boils.
Add beans and bacon; heat thoroughly.
Garnish with egg slices or finely chopped egg.

title: mother's fresh coconut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating after each.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add alternately with milk.
Continue beating at medium speed, scraping sides of bowl with a rubber spatula or wooden spoon.
Add vanilla. Bake in 11 x 7-inch pans (3) for 35 minutes at 350°.
Let cake cool.
Frost with Mother's Coconut Cake Frosting (recipe follows).

title: deviled macaroni salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except radishes or cucumbers in kettle in which macaroni was cooked.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until heat through.
Stir in radishes or cucumbers. Serve hot.
Ingredients can be combined and served cold also. Yields 6 servings.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Prick potatoes with a fork and bake in a 375° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool slightly and cut potatoes in half.
Scoop out potatoes, leaving a thin shell.
Put pulp in a small mixer bowl and add cheese and seasonings.
Beat until smooth.
Add milk and beat until fluffy.
Pipe or spoon mixture into shells.
Sprinkle with paprika and place on cookie sheet.
Cover loosely with foil.
Bake for 10 minutes, then uncover and bake for 10 more minutes.

title: boiled icing
directions: Let sugar, water and vinegar cook to soft ball.
Pour 1/2 of syrup slowly over stiffly beaten egg whites.
Continue beating. Return remaining half of syrup to stove.
Cook until hard ball stage.
Pour slowly over other mixture, beating continuously until proper thickness to spread.

title: quick chicken pie
directions: In a bowl, combine vegetables, soup and chicken. Transfer to an ungreased 9-inch pie plate. In another bowl, combine egg, milk and biscuit mix just until moistened. Pour over chicken mixture. Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine the Karo and sugar; boil to 300° or until brittle when a little is dropped in cold water.
Add the soda and vanilla to the candy and spread thickly on oiled pans, containing a layer of roasted peanuts.

title: lemon curd
directions: Place sugar, egg yolks and lemon juice in a medium saucepan over low heat.
Whisk to combine, then switch to a wooden spoon.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and coats back of spoon.
Cook a few minutes more but do not allow to boil. Remove from heat, stir in butter and zest and let cool.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill until ready to use.
Makes about 3 cups. This is a tangy topping for gingerbread, scones and crumpets.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough into their slices.
Arrange slices in greased pie pan or oblong glass casserole dish.
Make sure slices come up the sides.
Bake according to cookie dough directions. Let cool, then fill with cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla mixture.
Top with fruit arranging it beautifully.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion.
Add all remaining ingredients except noodles.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Mix in noodles.
Pour in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: In a medium size bowl, mix vanilla pudding and juice from oranges and pineapple.
Mix until smooth.
Add oranges and pineapple.
Chill.
Add slices of bananas and marshmallows before serving.

title: holiday dessert
directions: Mix and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: cauliflower medley
directions: Wash cauliflower.
Break into flowerets.
Cook covered in small amount of boiling salted water, about 10 minutes.
Cook Brussels sprouts and onions according to directions.
Combine all vegetables in lightly greased 9 x 13 dish.

title: potatoes, shredded, smothered, covered and trashed
directions: Take 1 cup of shredded potatoes or hash browns.
Cook to a light brown, along with the onions.
After they are light brown, take one slice of cheese and slightly melt it in the potatoes and onion.
Then take some leftover chilli, pour it over the potatoes, onion and melted cheese.
Throw in the tomatoes and eat.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Pour into casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Crush crackers and sprinkle over cheese.
Melt margarine.
Spread over crackers.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: chocolate crackers
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Line a cookie sheet with foil and spray lightly with Pam. Place crackers, salty side up on cookie sheet. In a saucepan, boil butter and brown sugar for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Then add the almond extract. Pour mixture over crackers and bake for 6 minutes. Take out of oven and top with broken pieces of chocolate. Spread evenly as chocolate begins to melt. Cool completely in refrigerator, then break apart.

title: spicy walnut-raisin pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Prepare pastry.
Beat eggs, sugar, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, corn syrup and margarine with hand beater until blended.
Stir in walnuts and raisins. Pour into pastry-lined pie plate.
Bake until set, 40 to 50 minutes.

title: blanche's chocolate cookies
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Stir in and beat the egg, milk and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Chill for 1 hour or longer.
Drop by spoon 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mexican chocolate
directions: Place chocolate chips, coffee and water in a 4-cup measuring bowl.
Heat for 3 minutes in a microwave.
Remove from oven and stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat for 4 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: nutty fingers
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts.
Roll into fingers.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: mom's sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, margarine, sour milk and eggs together.
Add soda, baking powder, vanilla and enough flour to roll.
Cut with cookie cutters or glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: barbecue steak
directions: Cut round steak into 6 pieces.
Brown slowly.
Blend vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, catsup, water, salt and pepper.
Pour over meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mrs. upson's blueberry muffins
directions: Mix together all ingredients except blueberries.
Stir in blueberries.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.
Yield: 1 dozen blueberry muffins.

title: american goulash
directions: Cook macaroni in salt water until tender and drain. Brown meat and onion in fat.
Add macaroni, meat and all remaining ingredients in greased baking dish. Sprinkle with crushed corn flakes or bread crumbs.
Bake until nice and brown at 350°.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot and cook until chicken and rice are done.

title: pink lima beans
directions: Wash and soak
lima
beans
for 30 minutes.
Cook 1 1/2 hours. Wash meat	and cook in separate pot until tender.	Add meat, green pepper,
tomato
sauce,
black
pepper and salt to lima beans.
Season to your taste.
Cook 1/2 hour longer.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichoke up fine and combine with other ingredients. Bake in a greased pie plate for 20 minutes at 350 degrees.
Serve hot with crackers or chips.

title: jello-sicles(child-approved; no drip)
directions: Mix all ingredients well until Jell-O and sugar are dissolved. Add 2 cups cold water.
Stir and pour into popsicle forms or small paper cups with popsicle sticks in them.
Freeze.

title: pecan delights
directions: Spray miniature muffin pans with Pam. Mix all ingredients well and drop by spoon into muffin pan. Bake at 350° until lightly brown. Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: vegetable pizza squares
directions: Press rolls together in a jelly roll pan to make crust. Bake until brown. Mix the cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing together and spread over cooled crust, forming filling. Sprinkle the raw vegetables over filling and top with the shredded cheese. Cut into squares.

title: easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter; stir in remaining ingredients.
Microwave 2 minute or until melted; pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Chill, cut into squares.

title: eggplant caponata
directions: Heat oil in a skillet on medium-high.
Add celery and onions and cook for approximately 5 minutes, until onions are limp.
Add eggplant cubes and saute just until tender.
Add tomatoes, wine vinegar, a little sugar, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; stir in capers and olives.
Cover and chill until serving time.
Serves 6.

title: hamburger pizza
directions: Mix Bisquick and water and pat into 11 x 17-inch jelly roll pan; add pizza sauce, ground beef and grated cheese.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Last 5 minutes, add slices of American cheese.

title: mushroom chicken
directions: Place fried chicken in deep pot on low flame or low setting. Pour both cans of soup over chicken and let it simmer; this makes gravy over the chicken and makes a delicious meal served with rice and a nice salad.

title: grandma's herbed cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except lemon pepper, together.
Form into a ball and cover with lemon pepper.
Wrap cheese ball in wax paper and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: hamburger a la "roni"
directions: Brown hamburger meat until done.
Drain grease off hamburger. Then add tomatoes.
Stir well.
Then add cooked elbow macaroni. Serves for 6 people.

title: teriyaki barbecue sauce
directions: Blend together until smooth.
Makes approximately 1 quart.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and equally divide into two loaf pans.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter toast
directions: Put bread in toaster until golden brown.
Spread peanut butter on bread all over.
Sprinkle sugar all over peanut butter.
If you want, put butter after it is golden brown.

title: false-kick punch
directions: Combine juice, sugar and extract.
Stir until sugar dissolves. Chill.
To serve, pour ginger ale in juice.
Serve over ice.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine dry ingredients and set aside. Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk (begin and end with dry ingredients).
Add vanilla, bananas and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes, or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: eggplant patties
directions: Place cubed eggplant in saucepan with enough water to cover. Heat until water comes to a boil, then cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Place eggplant in a bowl and add cheese, bread crumbs, parsley, garlic, salt, pepper and eggs.
Blend well.
In a skillet, add the oil and heat. Drop eggplant mixture by spoonful in pan to size of hamburg. Fry on both sides and add more oil as needed.

title: out-of-the-garden pizza
directions: Allow cream cheese to set at room temperature 30 minutes or until soft.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Separate rolls into 8 triangles; place on greased 12-inch pizza pan with elongated triangle points toward center.
Press dough together to form crust.
Brush with beaten egg.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until brown.
Cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter and mix with stuffing.
Put 1/2 in baking dish and small pieces of chicken in a layer over stuffing.
Pour 1 can broth over chicken.
Mix sour cream with undiluted cream of chicken soup and spread over chicken.
Add remaining stuffing and pour second can of broth over this.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: funfetti party bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
In a large bowl, combine cake mix, margarine and eggs.
Stir by hand until thoroughly moistened.
Stir in nuts and candy bits from cake mix.
Spread in greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 13 to 17 minutes or until light golden brown and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely.
Frost cooled bars with frosting. Sprinkle with candy bits from frosting.
Cut into bars.
Makes 48 bars.

title: crock-pot roast and vegetables
directions: Place roast, potatoes, carrots and onions in a crock-pot.
Mix water, salt, pepper and flour together to form a gravy and pour over first four ingredients.
Cook on low for 6 to 12 hours and on high for 4 to 6 hours.

title: cora's cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Grease pan.
Layer in pan the nuts, coconut and chocolate chips.
Pour cake mix on top of ingredients.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine oil, eggs, sugar, zucchini and vanilla in a large bowl.
Stir in flour and cinnamon. Blend well (do not beat). Stir in nuts. Spoon batter in a well-greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Drain clams; reserve liquid. Fry salt pork until crisp in a large saucepan; remove. Add water, potatoes, onions and reserved clam liquid to fat in saucepan. Cook, covered, until potatoes are tender, about 10 to 15 minutes. Add milk, cream, clams and salt pork. Heat slowly just to a boil. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Float butter atop each serving.

title: mother's coconut pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients as listed.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: princell ann stuffing
directions: Trim bread; let dry out completely.
Soak bread in water; press out water thoroughly.
Chill overnight in cloth bag with heavy weight on top to press out any remaining excess water.
Put pork through food chopper using medium blade; cook over low heat until pink color shows.
Put turkey liver through chopper; cook with pork until lightly browned.
In a separate small skillet, cook the celery and onion in butter or oleo until onion is transparent.
Crumble bread in large mixing bowl; add pork and liver together with drippings.
Add celery, onion and eggs.
Mix well.
Season with salt, pepper and monosodium glutamate.
Will make enough stuffing for 12 pounds dressed turkey.

title: baked artichoke spread
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Drain and chop artichokes. In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Place in a decorative ovenproof shallow dish and bake about 15 minutes until bubbly.
Serve with crackers or bread rounds, toasted.

title: lemon tea bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake for one hour at 325°.

title: dump cake
directions: Add melted butter to cake mix and 2 eggs.
Mix well.
Spread in bottom of a large pan. Blend 2 eggs and cream cheese together. Add the powdered sugar.
Spread on top of cake mix.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat cream cheese and butter at high speed until creamy. Gradually add powdered sugar, beating at low speed until smooth. Stir in vanilla and pecans. Yields 3 1/2 cups. Makes enough for 3 (9-inch) cake layers. Preparation time: 5 minutes.

title: dijon-roasted new potatoes(lighter eating - 3 points)
directions: Coat a 9 X 13 baking dish with cooking spray. Heat over to 425°. Whisk together oil, mustard, paprika, thyme, salt and pepper in a large bowl. Add potatoes and stir until they are coated. Transfer potatoes to the baking dish and roast 15 minutes. Stir and roast another 15 minutes.

title: mulled cider
directions: Add all of the cider, orange juice, cinnamon sticks and cloves together in a large pot and simmer for 15 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: alfredo sauce(very low-fat)
directions: Combine all ingredients in the container of an electric blender; process until smooth.
Heat thoroughly over very low heat; don't cook, just heat.
Combine this with various vegetables for a low-fat meal.
Serve with the pasta of your choice.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapples, reserving 3 Tbsp. of its juice.
Combine sugar and flour.
Stir in reserved pineapple juice.
Add pineapple and cheese.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture into greased casserole dish. Combine melted margarine and cracker crumbs, stirring well. Sprinkle crumbs over pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
You may double this recipe.

title: walnut roast
directions: Saute chopped vegetables with sage, salt and soy sauce in 1/4 cup water.
Blend flour and sunflower seeds with 2 cups water. Add to sauteed vegetables and simmer a few minutes.
Place in bowl bread crumbs, walnuts and brown rice.
Add sauteed vegetables and sunflower mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, until well browned.
Serve with Chicken-like or Cashew Gravy.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix together until cheese is soft to work with.
Wash and take stems out of mushrooms.
Chop 4 or 5 of the stems real small and add to cheese.
Spoon cream cheese into center of mushrooms and serve.

title: orange julius
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender.
Blend until smooth.
Serve immediately.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; add cold water and the rest of the ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite size pieces.
This will take about 2 months.
Reserve trunk as you will need something to store the pieces in.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook over kerosene fire for about 4 weeks at 465°.
This will serve 3,800 people.
If more are expected, add the 2 rabbits, but do this only if necessary as most people do not like hare in their stew.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Fry out 1 pound hamburger meat; drain off all grease and add one large onion.
Mix everything together in crock-pot and cook six to 8 hours.

title: tomato herb sauce with crabmeat and scallops
directions: Over medium heat, heat oil.
Add onion; cook until soft for 2 minutes.
Add garlic; cook abut 1 minute.
Add chicken broth and seasonings.
Heat to boiling; cook 1 minute.
Add tomatoes with juice; return to boiling.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add crabmeat and scallops.
Cover and cook until scallops are tender.
Serve over pasta.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Clean and slice strawberries; add glaze (set aside).
Spread cookie dough on pizza pan.
Bake until golden brown.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over cooled cookie dough, cream cheese mixture, then strawberries and glaze.
Refrigerate for about 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Put rice (uncooked) in casserole. Sprinkle dry onion soup on top.
Add 2 cups water and stir. Place chicken on top.
Mix mushroom soup with 1/2 cup water.
Pour over breasts or strips.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Drop by spoon into hot oil and deep fry until brown.
(Makes 12 to 15.)

title: frozen cole slaw
directions: Add salt to cabbage.
Let stand one hour; squeeze out extra juice.
Boil last 7 ingredients 1 minute; let cool to lukewarm, then pour over squeezed cabbage.
Pour into containers and freeze.

title: pan burritos
directions: In a saucepan, combine the first 6 ingredients; simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
In a skillet, brown the beef.
Drain; stir in 1/3 of the sauce.
Spread another third on the bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place 3 tortillas over sauce, tearing to fit bottom of pan.
Spoon half of meat mixture over tortillas; sprinkle with 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Add 3 more tortillas.
Spread refried beans over tortillas; top with remaining meat.
Sprinkle with 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Layer remaining tortillas; top with the remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting. Serve with taco sauce, sour cream, chili peppers, chopped onion and/or guacamole if desired.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: vienna bread
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together; let set 10 minutes.
Add 3 cups flour.
Beat smooth and bubbly.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Add oil, salt and 9 cups flour.
Knead until smooth.
Let rise until double, about 1 hour.
Punch down and cut into 5 pieces.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Form into loaves and place on floured pan.
Let rise until double.
Just before putting in the oven, slash 4 or 5 times or 1 slash longways.
When done, brush with butter and cool, uncovered.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: rio grande beans
directions: Mix thoroughly beef, bread crumbs, egg, salt, pepper and 1 teaspoon chili powder.
Shape firmly into 16 meatballs.
In 8-inch skillet, brown meatballs, pour off fat.
Add onion and remaining chili powder. Cover; cook over low heat 20 minutes or until done. Add beans.
Heat; stir occasionally.
Garnish with cheese.
Makes 3 cups.

title: old-time jam cake
directions: If self-rising flour is used, omit soda and baking powder and use sweet milk.
This makes a 3 or 4 layer cake.

title: pumpkin cake bars
directions: Mix eggs, pumpkin, sugar and spices together; pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top.
Drizzle melted butter over mix; sprinkle nuts over all.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cover with foil loosely the first half of baking time (to keep from browning too soon).
Cut into squares and serve with cream.

title: crock-pot venison
directions: Place all ingredients except carrots and rice in crock-pot. Cook on high setting for 3 to 4 hours.
Add carrots and rice; simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 additional hours.
Place on low until ready to eat.
Delicious with corn bread.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems and inside of mushrooms. Mix all the other ingredients in a bowl. Stuff mushroom caps and place in a casserole dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: ham delights
directions: Mix together all ingredients (not the rolls).
Cut rolls in half; spread with mixture.
Wrap each roll with aluminum foil. Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.

title: pecan cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add baking powder and sugar and beat into egg whites.
Fold in crushed vanilla wafers and chopped nuts.

title: shrimp and fettucine
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add onion and garlic and cook slowly until onion is soft.
Add parsley, thyme and cayenne.
Add raw shrimp and cook about 20 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients
and bake in 12-inch Dutch oven for 1 hour.

title: mexican breakfast
directions: Scramble eggs and set aside.
Cook bacon, crumble and set aside.
On medium-high heat, melt 1 tablespoon of butter.
Place 1 tortilla shell in pan for 30 seconds.
Turn shell quickly.
Put 1/4 of scrambled eggs, 1/4 of crumbled bacon and 1/2 slice of cheese on half of the tortilla shell.
Fold other half of shell over fillings.
Remove from heat.
Makes 4.

title: cole slaw
directions: Finely chop cabbage; add salt and sugar.
Stir somewhat; add onion and stir again.
Add milk and salad dressing and stir well. Let the flavors blend awhile for better flavor.

title: citrus cooler(especially refreshing on a hot summer afternoon)
directions: In blender container, combine half of the cold water, half of the orange-grapefruit or orange-pineapple juice concentrate and half of the lemon sherbet.
Cover and blend 15 seconds.
Pour into 3 tall glasses.
Repeat with remaining water, concentrate and lemon sherbet.
Carefully fill glasses with chilled ginger ale. Stir gently.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked peaches
directions: Combine the honey, sugar, butter, lemon juice and cinnamon. Set aside.
Peel and pit peaches.
Place peach halves in baking dish.
Fill cavity with honey mixture.
Pour water around peaches. Bake at 375° for 15 or 20 minutes.
Pour over angel food cake or ice cream.
(This also goes really well with meats such as chicken or roast pork.)

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.

Into a large bowl, sift the flour with baking soda and salt. Add sugar, egg, vanilla and butter. With wooden spoon or electric mixer at medium speed, beat until smooth and well combined (about 1 minute). Stir in walnuts and chocolate pieces.
Drop by the teaspoonful, 2-inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden. Remove to wire rack.
Cool.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: snowball cookies(makes 3 dozen)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients except powdered sugar.
Beat at low speed, scraping bowl often, until well mixed.
Shape rounded teaspoonful dough into 1-inch balls.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 18 to 25 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm and when cool.

title: tortilla hors d'oeuvres
directions: Soften cream cheese 4 to 5 hours.
Combine all ingredients, except mayonnaise; mix well, then add mayonnaise for a smooth consistency.
Layer with flour tortillas.
Wrap in plastic wrap and leave overnight in refrigerator.
Cut with a sharp knife into 1/4-inch slices and serve.

title: collards 'n pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops and season to taste.
Put pork chops into Dutch oven or large pot with a lid.
Add the chopped collard leaves and the remainder of the vegetables along with a small amount of water.
Cover tightly and steam for 30 minutes, checking liquid level frequently.
Pour cream of mushroom soup over all the ingredients in the pot.
Put the lid back on the pot and simmer until all the vegetables are tender.
It's very good.

title: cheesecake dreams
directions: Grease an 8-inch square pan.
In small bowl, mix first 3 ingredients. Stir in melted butter and combine well.
Reserve 1/3 cup crumbs.
Pat remaining gently into pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick margarine and the crumbs.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs, 2 sticks margarine and powdered sugar together for 15 minutes.
Spread mixture over unbaked crumb mixture.
Add sliced bananas and pineapple, then a layer of whipped topping.
Sprinkle cherries and nuts over topping.
Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: devil nuts
directions: Put nuts on a shallow baking dish in a 300° oven.
Pour other ingredients over nuts, stirring occasionally.
Drain on paper towels.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix beans with taco seasoning, then layer beans and then sour cream.
Add cheese on top.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 12-inch dish.

title: jean's thing
directions: Melt sugar and Karo until dissolved.
Stir in peanut butter. Remove from heat. Add corn flakes.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper. Sets up real quickly.
Ready to eat.

title: pinwheel cookies(yields about 7 dozen)
directions: Mix sugar, butter, eggs and extract.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
After dough is mixed, divide into halves.
Stir 1/2 teaspoon green or red food coloring into one-half.
Cover both halves and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients together cold and store in covered container in refrigerator.
These keep for months and are truly delicious!

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend sugar and oil together.
Add 1 egg at a time with carrots, then pineapple and nuts.
Gradually add dry ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with lime Jell-O.
Bring water to boil and pour over Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and chill.

title: egg ribbon soup
directions: Bring the broth to a boil in a medium size saucepan over medium heat.
Meanwhile, lightly beat the eggs in a mixing bowl; rinse, stem and chop the fresh greens or drain the frozen spinach well.
Add the greens to the broth and bring the liquid back to a simmer.
Whisking constantly, pour the beaten eggs into the soup. The eggs will curdle into ribbon shaped strands.
Season to taste with salt and pepper and remove the pan from the heat.
Ladle the hot soup into bowls and sprinkle Parmesan over each portion.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix cream cheese, chives and onion flakes.
Take one piece of ham, 1 piece of cheese and spread with cream cheese mixture.
Roll up pinwheel style and secure with 5 toothpicks.
Repeat procedure with rest of the ingredients.
Chill for one hour.
Slice each roll into 5 pieces.
Yields 50 rolls.

title: giant chalk sticks
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Pour into small waxed paper cups.
Remove cup when
mixture has hardened.

title: taco casserole
directions: Fry hamburger meat, seasoning to taste.
Add soups and enchilada sauce.
Add together with meat and seasoning.
Put bag of chips in baking dish.
Pour mixture over chips.
Sprinkle cheese over.
Bake for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: date roll
directions: Cook in heavy boiler for 20 minutes.
Add dates and butter. Cook until you can pull it from the sides of the boiler with the spoon.
Remove from fire; add pecans and vanilla.
Beat until it creams, then pour it on a damp cloth and shape it in a roll.

title: ham pie
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in oil until tender.
Add cream of chicken soup and water.
Mix in ham.
Simmer until blended.
Put biscuits on top.
Bake at 350° until biscuits brown.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add taco seasoning mix according to package directions.
Add can of drained chili hot beans.
Cook for 15 minutes on low.
On plate layer tortilla chips, lettuce, bean and beef mixture, cheese, sour cream, salsa, onion and olives. Enjoy!
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: creamy vegetable soup
directions: Combine water and all vegetables.
Cook until well done.
Add cheese and canned chicken soup.
Simmer until well blended.

title: cheese ball
directions: Save some beef to roll the cheese ball in. Shape into a ball and chill.

title: chicken spread
directions: To softened cream cheese, add all ingredients.
Form into any desired shape.
Cover with nuts.

title: best raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Simmer raisins in 1 cup water until plump (15 minutes).
Drain raisins, reserving the liquid and add enough water to make 1/2 cup.
Mix shortening, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Blend in the 1/2 cup raisin liquid.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet by rounded teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Makes about 6 1/2 dozen.

title: mike's favorite cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together and shape into a ball.
Roll ball in nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: quick and easy pound cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and continue beating.
Add flour. Heat milk and oleo together.
Add to mixture and mix well.
Add vanilla or lemon and baking powder.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for about 1 hour.
Check to see if it needs to cook a few minutes longer.

title: doritos chicken
directions: Crush Doritos and just cover bottom of 2-quart baking dish. Mix all other ingredients except cheese and place on Doritos. Crush more Doritos on top of this.
Add cheese on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: aunt verda's fruitcake cookies
directions: Dredge fruit in flour. Add salt, coconut and nuts. Add milk and mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake 25 to 30 minutes in preheated 275° oven.
Store cooled cookies in an airtight container about 5 days before serving, then enjoy!
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: shrimp and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute shrimp for 6 to 8 minutes in butter.
Mix the sauces. Follow instructions on the package for the Hollandaise sauce and mushroom sauce for the quantity of liquid, but use half and half instead of milk.
Layer broccoli in baking dish (flat).
Cover with shrimp.
Pour sauce over.
Bake at 325° to 350° for about 30 minutes.
Can sprinkle Italian bread crumbs 5 minutes before done.

title: easy broccoli casserole
directions: In ungreased 2-quart casserole, place chopped broccoli and water chestnuts.
Cover with cream of chicken soup.
Mix bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and butter; sprinkle on top of soup.
Bake uncovered for one hour at 350°.

title: brandied caramel flan
directions: Melt in heavy skillet to form light syrup.
Coat 10-inch pie dish (deep) on bottom and partially up sides.

title: david's favorite goulash
directions: Cook noodles; set aside.
In large saucepan combine all ingredients except noodles and simmer 30 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine noodles with rest of ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish and cover.
Cook in oven for 30 minutes or so until desired thickness of juices.
Serve with bread and butter and tossed salad.

title: chili dog sauce
directions: Cook and drain ground beef with onion.
Mix spices and water and add to ground beef.
Add water to keep thin.
Simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Combine all except shrimp.
Heat and pour over washed shrimp. Cover and bake 1 hour at 325°.
Serve with French bread.

title: low country boil
directions: Bring a pot of water to boil with lemons. Drop in boiling water the potatoes and cook 10 minutes. Add the corn and polish sausage and boil 10 minutes more. Last, add the shrimp and boil about 2 minutes or until the shrimp turns pink.

title: meatball hoagies
directions: Place all ingredients in crock pot for 1 1/2 hours on low heat. Serve on hoagie buns or your choice.
For a large crowd.

title: shrimp crab casserole
directions: Dice green pepper, onion and celery.
Saute in 2 tablespoons butter until soft.
Add 1 pound crab meat and 1 pound shrimp. Simmer 5 minutes.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Drain spinach in colander to remove excess water.
In mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Brown the ground beef with the onion and pepper and drain off fat. Mix the beans with the BBQ sauce, add beef and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: date and chocolate chip bars
directions: Mix together dates, water and baking soda and set aside to cool.
Cream together butter and sugar in a separate bowl.
Add 2 well beaten eggs to creamed mixture and mix well.
Add cooled date mixture.
Then add sifted flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured.
Sprinkle top with chocolate chips, nuts and sugar.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pauline's hamburger pie
directions: Brown beef in skillet with onion, chili powder, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Spread in baking dish.
Cover with diced potatoes, green peas and corn.
Mix juice from corn and peas with 1 small can of tomato paste.
Mix the cornmeal with the egg and buttermilk. Spoon over mixture. Bake at 400° for 35 minutes (until corn bread is brown).

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse blueberries from mix with cold water and drain.
Arrange peach slices in ungreased 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle blueberries over peaches, combine water and brown sugar in liquid measuring cup.
Pour over fruit.
Combine muffin mix, pecans and melted butter in large bowl.
Stir until blended (mixture will be crumbly).
Sprinkle crumb mixture over fruit. Sprinkle contents of topping packet from mix over crumb mixture. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: george strait's king ranch chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together the first 4 ingredients and set aside.
In a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole, layer the ingredients in the following order: chicken, tortillas, onions, soup mixture and top with cheese.
Bake for 1 hour or until mixture is bubbly.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Coat the bottom and sides of a large roasting pan with a nonstick vegetable spray.
Place popped corn in pan.

title: macaroni-hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add macaroni, soup and milk.
Stir in banana pepper and olives.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cut or shred cheese into mixture.
Bake in 1 or 2 casserole dishes.
Top with squares of Velveeta.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: white bean soup
directions: Heat oil in a large, heavy saucepan.
Saute onion and garlic until onion is tender.
Add chicken broth, beans, salt, Italian seasoning, basil and pepper.
Bring to a boil; simmer over low heat for 10 minutes.
Puree in blender until smooth; return to saucepan. Slowly stir in evaporated milk; heat through.
Top with fresh basil.
Yield:
About 4 cups.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: scripture cake
directions: Chop raisins, figs and almonds.
Sift together flour, salt and sugar.
Cream in butter.
Beat in water and eggs.
Add raisins, figs and almonds.
Stir in honey and spices.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients; shake well. Store in refrigerator.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain spinach and squeeze.
Mix all ingredients.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients except egg, then add egg and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage 'n' potatoes
directions: Mix together Cheez Whiz and sour cream.
Add onion, parsley flakes and salt.
Slice smoked sausage in half, then cut in small pieces.
Mix together potatoes, sausage and cheese mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: fruit cake bonbons
directions: In
saucepan,
combine	juice, molasses and raisins and simmer 5 minutes.	Remove from heat and add fruit peel.
Cream butter, sugar
and	egg,
one
at
a time.	Stir together dry ingredients and
add
to creamed mixture.
Add orange mixture and nuts and mix well.

title: no-knead bread
directions: Dissolve dry yeast in warm water; add remaining ingredients one by one.
Mix by hand until moist.
Seal in Tupperware fix-n-mix bowl until seal pops off.
Divide into 4 loaves.
Cover with towel and let rise 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: zesty potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, bacon, Parmesan cheese, onion and salt; mix lightly.
Gradually add dressing to softened cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Pour over potato mixture; mix lightly.
Spoon gently into serving bowl; chill several hours.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a saucepan; add sugar and milk. Bring to a boil and boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Drop by spoonfuls on aluminum foil.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: beef and noodle casserole(microwave)
directions: Place butter in a shallow dish.
Microwave at High for 4 to 5 seconds, until butter melts.
In another shallow dish, mix cornflake crumbs, Parmesan cheese, chives and parsley.
Dip chicken in butter, then crumbs to coat.
Arrange chicken pieces, bone side down, in shallow pan.
Microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes.
Turn over.
Cook for 5 to 8 minutes longer, until juices run clear.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, sugar, salt and baking soda; set aside.
Mix egg, orange juice, melted shortening and hot water in a bowl.
Add flour mixture.
Fold in cranberries and nuts.
Mix until it holds together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean after being inserted.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Cream the cream cheese and oleo together.
Add flour and mix well.
Form into 24 small balls and press into bottom and sides of small ungreased muffin tins.
Put a few broken nuts into bottom of tarts and add filling.

title: pecos pasta
directions: Prepare elbow macaroni according to package directions. Drain.
In a large skillet melt butter; add green pepper and onion.
Cook until tender (do not brown).
Add Hormel chili, corn, seasoned salt and pepper.
Simmer on low heat 5 minutes.
Stir in cooked macaroni; top with shredded cheese.
Cover and heat on low 5 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chip dip
directions: Put cream cheese in a bowl and start with 1/4 cup of milk. Mix and keep adding milk until the mixture is fairly smooth and the thickness is to your liking.
I like mine fairly thick so that it stays on the chip.
Then stir in onions.
You can add as many or as little onion as you want, it is what you like best.
Add salt and pepper to taste if desired.

title: egg custard
directions: The egg custard
recipe
was
told to me by a Great Aunt before she died.
This
is
not
a standard recipe and may take some "trial
and
error" to perfect this one.
The instructions are written as she told them to me.
She used this basic recipe for chocolate,
coconut
and
other
flavors
as
well.
But my family enjoys it just as a vanilla cream egg custard.

title: rhubarb coffee cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg alternately and sift dry ingredients with buttermilk and vanilla.
Stir in fruit.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle on top 1 cup white sugar; mix with 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake for 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; mix until smooth.
Add additional milk to thin if necessary.
Batter should resemble pancake batter. Working in batches, dip tomato slices into batter, allowing excess batter to drop back into bowl.
Fry in 2 inches of hot oil (375°) in a large, heavy skillet until browned, turning once carefully with tongs.
Transfer to colander to drain.

title: ham dip
directions: Mix or grind the ham.
Mix ham with mayonnaise, chili sauce, mustard, and sugar.
Serve with crackers or potato chips.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Pick crabmeat, place in large bowl.
Add parsley and crumbs. Beat together egg, mayonnaise, mustard, salt, pepper and baking powder.
Pour this mixture over the crabmeat, parsley & crumbs. Mix well.
Shape into balls - flatten.
Fry until brown.

title: harry's cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine margarine, butter, cream cheese and sugar; beat well until fluffy. Add dash of salt and vanilla. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flour and mix well. Pour batter into a greased and floured 10 inch tube pan. Place pan in a cold oven and set at 275°. Bake for 1 1/2 hours until done. Cool in pan.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: In a large mixing bowl, melt marshmallows and butter in microwave. Stir well and add cereal. Mix until well coated. Press in a 9 x 13 buttered pan. Let cool and cut into squares.

title: corned beef and chip casserole
directions: Mix noodles, soup, milk, corned beef, cheese and onion. Pour into
a 1 1/2 quart greased baking dish.
Top with potato chips. Bake for 15 minutes in a 425° oven.

title: hot chili dip
directions: Brown beef and onions in a skillet, season with salt and pepper.
Place beef and onions in slow cooker, add chili, Ro-Tel tomatoes and beans.
Stir, cover and cook for 2 hours on high setting.
When ready to serve, top with cheese, olives and green onions.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Serves approximately 25.

title: pineapple cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into (ready made) graham cracker crust or Keebler cookie crust.
Refrigerate before serving.
Yields 2 pies.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut Crisco into flour slowly with fork until well mixed. Slowly mix in ice water, a little at a time, mixing well.
With hands, shape into a ball.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll on floured surface. Makes 4 crusts.

title: neb's orange cake
directions: Grease tube pan (medium size) or loaf pan and place wax paper in the bottom.
Grease again and dust lightly with flour.
Shake out excess flour.
Mix sugar, shortening, eggs and orange rind; add buttermilk and flour, soda and salt.
Add nuts and dates.

title: disgustingly rich brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°, then grease an 8 or 9-inch baking pan. Melt butter over low heat.
Stir cocoa and sugar together.
Then stir in the melted butter.
Add the eggs and vanilla and stir. Now add flour and salt and mix just until smooth.
Spread in pan and bake for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add beaten egg, water, salt and softened yeast.
Add flour, a little at the time, and mix well.

title: go to school cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cut into cookies and bake on a cookie sheet 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: easy gravy
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium-sized storage container or plastic bag.
Store tightly covered at room temperature.
Shake or stir before using to make gravy (recipe follows).
Yields about 1 3/4 cups.

title: kaposzta(stuffed cabbage leaves)
directions: Fill each empty can with water and add.
Cover pot tightly and cook for approximately 2 hours on very low flame.
Serve hot.

title: mom's fudge(formerly kathy's fudge)
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa and salt in a deep, heavy saucepan. Bring to a rolling boil.
Stir constantly.
Test for soft ball stage every 2 to 3 minutes.
At the soft ball stage, remove from heat.
