Add butter, vanilla and Karo syrup.
Beat with electric blender until glossy (4 to 5 minutes).
Pour into a buttered platter to set.

title: hot barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook slow for 30 minutes.

title: fire beef
directions: Combine oil, soy sauce, water, peppers, garlic powder and sugar. Next, marinate thin strips of meat in sauce for at least 2 hours. Grill or stir-fry meat. Serve with buttered toast squares or crackers.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix pineapple with juice and vanilla instant pudding until blended.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Fill and frost entire cake.

title: broccoli salad supreme
directions: Cut broccoli to bite size pieces.
Place in bowl with the grapes, seeds, bacon and onion.
Next, mayo, sugar and vinegar. Toss gently.
Chill 2 to 4 hours.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix together well.
Stir into box of Jiffy cornbread mix. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese the last 5 minutes of baking time.

title: baked bean and ham casserole
directions: Arrange chops in single layer on rack in pan.
Put into a 375° oven for 20 minutes or so.
Take out and heap stuffing on each chop; continue cooking for 35 to 40 minutes longer (depends on thickness of chops).

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix hamburger, egg and cracker or bread crumbs together.
Add milk and onion.
Mix all together.
Bake in loaf pan.
Make holes on top of hamburger and pour catsup in them.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: date delight
directions: Let milk, dates and marshmallows set 15 minutes.
Add enough graham crackers to make mixture thick enough to handle.
Divide mixture into 2 parts.
Form into rolls.
Roll in crumbs on waxed paper.
Refrigerate in waxed paper.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: no bake peanut butter fudge
directions: Sift dry milk and powdered sugar into a bowl.
Add other items.
Mix well and press into pan.
Chill for 1 hour or until firm.
If desired, mix sugar, cream cheese and dry milk by hand until smooth.
Add other items; mix well and press into a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, vegetable oil and vinegar.
Cool and pour over vegetables.
Can be kept a couple of weeks in the refrigerator.

title: noodles
directions: Cut and drop in hot water until done.
After noodles are tender, drain and rinse in cold water.
Put them in your favorite broth, chicken, beef, pork, turkey, etc.

title: eva st.  clair's apple sliced cinnamon
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Make syrup of sugar and water.
Add red devils.
Pour over apples.
Stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until apples are done.

title: kolachi
directions: Melt oleo and cool.
Put yeast and sugar in large bowl.
Add warm milk and mix.
Let stand about 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients in order given.
Mix well.
If tacky, add a little more flour.
Knead for 5 minutes on a floured board.
Cut in four pieces and form four balls.
Knead each ball for 3 minutes and set in lightly floured bowl.
Cover with a heavy towel.

title: egg custard
directions: Separate eggs, reserving egg whites.
Beat egg yolks with sugar, milk and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Place in unbaked pie shell and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: short ribs mexicana
directions: Trim fat from meat.
Sprinkle with seasoning mix.
Brown in skillet.
Add remaining seasoning mix, juice and water; stir well. Cover tightly; simmer for 1 hour, or until tender.
Makes 2 servings.

title: southwest pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sprinkle cornmeal onto bottom of greased 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Spread dough into pan. Pre-bake 5 minutes.
Spread with combined tomato sauce and chili powder.
Top with green and red pepper, chilies and cheese, tossed with cilantro.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Cover bottom of 11 x 15-inch pan with graham cracker crust. Reserve 1 cup of crumbs.
Slice bananas crosswise and layer over crust.
Slice ice cream in 1/2-inch thick slices and place over bananas.
Sprinkle ice cream with nuts.
Freeze until firm.

title: dutch butter cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl with hands.
Spread in shallow 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake about 40 minutes at 350°.
Watch while they are in the oven so they don't get too brown.
Cut in 2-inch squares.

title: fudge pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake on 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Combine softened creamed cheese and cucumber.
Beat until smooth.
Add seasonings and chill.

title: cinnamon pickles
directions: Pour lime over cucumbers and cover with water.
Stir occasionally.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain and rinse well.
Set in ice water for 3 hours.
Drain, rinse and cover with 2 cups vinegar, red food color, 1 tablespoon alum and 8 1/2 quarts water. Set 3 hours.
Drain, do not rinse!
Discard juice.
Heat but don't boil 2 cups vinegar, 8 cinnamon sticks, 2 cups water, 20 ounces red hots and 10 cups sugar.
Pour over cucumbers.
Bring to a boil once a day for 3 days.
On 4th day seal in jars.
Ready to eat in 1 week.

title: cheesy potato pancakes
directions: Melt butter in a skillet and arrange the first layer of potatoes so that they cover the skillet, overlapping.
Next, season lightly and add a layer of cheese.
Repeat.
End with a layer of cheese.
Cover the pan and cook at a medium heat for 40 to 50 minutes.
Loosen and serve.
Garnish with orange and apple slices.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with vegetable oil to keep rice from sticking.
Line dish with instant rice, evenly over bottom.
Sprinkle dry soup mix over rice.
Pepper chicken parts and place on top of rice and dry soup mix.
Mix water and soup and pour over chicken.
Lift corners of chicken to let liquid down to rice.
Bake in oven at 350° for about one hour.

title: roast wild goose 1
directions: Dress goose and soak several hours in salt and water.

Put a small onion inside and plunge into boiling water for 20 minutes. Stuff with chopped celery, chopped eggs, mashed potatoes, bits of fat pork or other cold meat, a little butter, a raw turnip (grated), a tablespoon of pepper vinegar, small chopped onion and pepper and salt to taste.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Then pour over ice.

title: chinese noodles with broccoli(low-fat)
directions: Heat sesame oil in a saucepan.
Add the minced garlic; cook, stirring, over medium-high heat until garlic is just golden.
Stir in ginger; continue cooking for 5 minutes.
Stir in chicken broth and hoisin sauce.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 2 to 3 more minutes.
Serve over pasta with a sprinkling of low sodium soy sauce and a scattering of chopped scallions or red pepper flakes.
Toss broccoli with pasta.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugar, molasses and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to sugar mix.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Spray roasting pan with nonstick spray.
Mix soups and milk. Pour half into roasting pan.
Sprinkle with the rice.
Place chicken on top.
Sprinkle contents of seasoning packet over chicken. Pour rest of soup over all.
Bake at 350° until chicken is done, approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: yum yum dessert
directions: Line the bottom of a bowl with 1/2 of the cake.
Spread 1/2 of the crushed pineapple including juice over cake.
Mix and beat pudding with the milk and pour 1/2 over the cake mixture.
Slice one banana thin on top of pudding.
Spread 1/2 of Cool Whip on top. Repeat process with 2nd layer.

title: fruit cake
directions: Add the 2 cups water to the mincemeat and cook for a few minutes. Cool. Before adding flour, put the soda in mincemeat. Line pan with paper.
Cream together the shortening, sugar and eggs. Add the flour, salt and all ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Fifteen minutes before done, glaze with syrup.

title: pea salad
directions: Layer in pan and refrigerate overnight.

title: pineapple wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients; bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix flour with baking powder and salt.
Mix together cereal, cinnamon and melted butter or margarine; set aside.
Combine sour cream and soda; set aside.
Cream butter or margarine and sugar together, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Alternately add flour mixture and sour cream mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Pour half of the batter into a greased 9-inch square pan; top with half the cereal mixture.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes, or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 9 servings.

title: rice pudding
directions: Add sugar to beaten eggs.
Pour in milk.
Add cooked rice, raisins, vanilla and salt to taste.
Bake until set in a moderate oven.

title: potato chip pecan crunch cookies
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add crushed potato chips and pecans; stir.
Stir in flour.
Form into small balls using 1 tablespoon dough.
Press balls flat on greased cookie sheet with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 16 to 18 minutes or until light brown.

title: joe's punch
directions: All ingredients, except champagne, can be mixed together ahead of time and chilled.
Add cold champagne just before serving.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together in saucepan and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add oleo and vanilla.
Spread while warm on cooled cake.
This frosting is not as sweet as the non-cooked ones.

title: easy tartar sauce
directions: Add relish to mayonnaise.
Serve at once.
This is a fast and easy tartar sauce.

title: hungarian goulash soup(not just a soup - a meal!)
directions: Trim all visible fat from the round steak and brown in the olive oil and garlic clove. Drain fat. Add to stock pot with tomato sauce, onions, vinegar, beef bouillon, paprika, caraway seeds, marjoram, bay leaf, salt, pepper and water. Bring to boil and simmer 2 hours or until beef falls apart with a fork. Remove steak, shred and return to pot. Add diced potatoes and simmer until tender - approximately 1 hour. Serve in soup bowls with dark bread and unsalted butter. Serves 8.

title: marinated cabbage slaw
directions: Pour over cabbage and refrigerate overnight.
Even better after 2 or 3 days.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until "tender."
Add water, the juice from the clams, diced potatoes and carrots.
Simmer on medium heat 15 to 20 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Stir in the mushroom soup and evaporated milk and simmer until hot.
Add the clams and corn; heat and serve.

title: chocolate whipped cream cake
directions: Bake cake in 2 (9-inch) or 3 (8-inch) layer pans.
(Save one layer for another dessert.)
Cool and divide layer in half.
Fill and cover with following:
Combine and sift confectioners sugar, cocoa and salt.
Add to 2 cups whipping cream; chill at least 2 hours.
Add vanilla and beat until stiff.
Fill layers slightly and cover sides and top of cake.
May be frozen.
Then add garnish of toasted almonds (sliced), chopped walnuts and shaved chocolate. Will thaw in 15 to 20 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Heat undiluted mushroom soup.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water; mix with soup.
Add cream cheese and blend well.
Add shrimp, celery, green onions and mayonnaise.
Place in salad mold and refrigerate overnight.
Unmold and serve with crackers.
Makes 20 servings.

title: broccoli with basil mushrooms
directions: Cook broccoli spears according to package directions.
Drain well.
Melt butter in small saucepan; add basil and mushrooms. Cook and stir until thoroughly heated.
Spoon over broccoli.

title: linda's mexachili dip
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients. Combine remaining ingredients and add to the vegetables. Chill 2 hours.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chicken breast scampi
directions: Cut raw boneless chicken breast into approximately 2 ounce chunks (like huge shrimp) and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Melt butter in a saucepan over low heat.
Add garlic, scallions, parsley, dill, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook on low heat for 2 minutes, then pour the mixture over chicken breasts.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Separate chicken pieces and cook for another 10 minutes.
Turn on broiler to brown chicken for 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve over rice or cooked spaghetti.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet. Add green onion and simmer 1 minute. Add flour and simmer 2 minutes. Heat cream and add to flour mixture. Simmer 5 minutes. Add crawfish, shrimp and remainder of ingredients, except Mozzarella cheese. Pour into buttered baking dish and sprinkle with Mozzarella and more Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: german kraut noodle skillet
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water with salt.
Drain.
In frying pan, braise onions in butter.
Add kraut and cook until lightly brown.
Add noodles to kraut mixture.
Add cheese and sour cream just before serving.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Fry sausages, drain and cut in half.
Add fruit and juices. Mix up last 4 ingredients in cup.
Add to sausages and fruit. Stir and heat until thick.

title: chicken delight(serves 6)
directions: Line baking dish with beef.
Place chicken on top.
Mix soup, sour cream and mushrooms.
Spoon over chicken.
Place half slice of bacon on chicken pieces.
Cover and bake at 300° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: no fail pie crust(really)
directions: Cut Crisco into flour with pastry blender. Add salt.
Cut in more until completely blended.
Add water a little at a time until mixture forms a ball. You may not need all the water. Never touch dough with your hands when mixing. Roll out.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown and break up hamburger.
Add the onion, garlic and oil. Mix corn meal with 1 cup of tomato puree.
Add this mixture, tomato puree, salt and chili powder.
Cook, stirring often, 15 minutes.
Take off heat.
Add beaten eggs, milk and olives.
Mix well.
Put in lightly greased 3-quart baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350° to 375°.

title: papier-mache
directions: Mix water and flour in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Mixture should be the same thickness as heavy cream. Coat a mold* with one layer newspaper strips which have been dipped in water.
Then dip strips in flour mixture and lay over first layer of strips until mold is well coated.
Let stand until strips on mold are dry and hard.
Paint over the strips if you like.

title: beer bread
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in bowl.
Stir until it makes a batter.
Pour into loaf pan.
Dot top with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot or cold.

title: chili-day chili
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet until meat is thoroughly brown. Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Season with salt, pepper, onion powder and chili powder according to your taste.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jello into boiling water.
Add frozen orange juice and juice from pineapple and enough water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Let stand in refrigerator until it begins to congeal.
Add can of cranberry sauce, drained pineapple, and nuts.
Mix and pour in mold and let congeal.

title: cocoa krispie roll
directions: Cook syrup and sugar until mixture bubbles.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter and 2 tablespoons butter.
Add Rice Krispies. Press firmly on wax paper on cookie sheet (spread it out over whole cookie sheet).

title: brown bag fried-fish
directions: Mix dry ingredients in brown paper bag.
Dip fish in milk. Then place in brown bag and shake.
Deep fry in 375° cooking oil deep enough to float fish.
Remove fish when it floats.

title: edna's brownies
directions: Beat eggs, oil, vanilla and water together.
Mix dry ingredients together (don't prepare pudding; add mix to dry ingredients).
Combine dry ingredients with creamed mixture.
Add the walnuts.

title: peaches and creamy dip with waffle wedges
directions: Place all ingredients, except waffles and cinnamon, in blender and process until smooth.
Set aside.
Toast waffles and cut each waffle into 6 wedges.
Place cream cheese mixture in a small serving bowl and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Serve with waffle wedges for dipping.
Makes 24 wedges and about 3/4 cup cream cheese mixture.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt margarine.
Boil sugar, milk and margarine.
When it begins to boil, time for 2 minutes and then take off the stove. Add peanut butter and Fluff and oatmeal and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Stir until peanut butter and Fluff melt.
Pour into a pan and refrigerate.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, and mix well; add broken vanilla wafers; add coconut and pecans.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie shells and garnish with mandarin oranges.
Refrigerate.

title: sausage spaghetti
directions: Cut sausage in bite size pieces.
Brown sausage and onions; add peppers and cook a few minutes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook for several hours.
Add water, if needed, although thick sauce is best. Serve over spaghetti.
You can alter ingredients to suit yourself. Add 1 tablespoon sugar to remove bitter taste of tomato paste, if you desire.
Italian seasoning may be added.

title: spiced red cabbage
directions: Place cabbage in a large kettle of boiling saltwater. Boil for 1 minute. Drain. Return to kettle; stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until cabbage is tender. Remove bay leaf. Yield: 6 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes.
Mix cream cheese, then add other ingredients and whip until light and fluffy.
Pour into ungreased casserole; sprinkle French fried onions over top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until brown.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cauliflower with shrimp sauce
directions: Wash cauliflower and break into flowerets. Cook covered in small amount of boiling, salted water for 10 to 15 minutes. Drain.
Heat soup over low heat, stirring frequently.
Add 1/2 cup sour cream; cook and stir just until hot.
Add 1/4 cup toasted slivered almonds; pour sauce over hot cauliflower.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: easy homemade ice cream
directions: For other flavors, instead of milk, use strawberry drink or any other type drink.

title: potatoes, onion, mushroom au gratin
directions: Cook potatoes the night before with jackets on.
Cool, peel and cut in cubes.
Heat butter in large kettle and saute mushrooms until brown.
Stir in flour, milk, cream or evaporated milk, consomme and grated cheese.
Also add seasoned salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook, stirring until smooth and thick. Remove from heat and add potatoes and drained onions.
Mix. Spoon into shallow pan or 4-quart casserole.
Cover in fridge overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
In a 2-quart saucepan, melt butter and chocolate over low heat.
With wire whisk, beat in 2 cups sugar and 3 eggs until blended.
Stir in flour, salt, nuts and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread evenly in pan.
Beat cream cheese, remaining 1/2 cup sugar, 1 egg and 1 teaspoon vanilla until well blended, about 3 minutes.
Drop 6 dollops of cream cheese mixture on top of batter.
Swirl with a spatula to marbleize.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool pan on wire rack.
Cut when completely cool.

title: pig-pickin' cake
directions: Grease and flour three cake pans.
Mix eggs, oil and cake mix. Fold in oranges and juice thoroughly.
Pour into cake pans and bake at 325° for about 20 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg yolks well (save whites for top of pie).
Add milk and stir well.
Mix flour, cocoa and sugar all together.
Add slowly with egg and milk.
Put on top of the stove and cook on low heat until thickened, then add butter and vanilla.
Pour in uncooked pie shell and cook at 350° until thickened.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except carrots, in a bowl until well blended.
Stir carrots in last.
Pour into a Bundt pan that is greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until tested done.

title: chocolate candy cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar and soda in a mixing bowl and set aside. Place water and margarine in a 4-cup batter bowl.
Microwave 2 minutes at Full power.
Add cocoa and blend well.
Cook 1 minute and 30 seconds at Full power or until mixture boils.
Gradually stir liquid mixture into flour mixture.
Stir in buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into greased 10-inch square baking dish. Cover with wax paper and microwave 8 minutes at Full power. While warm, prick surface with a fork.
Spread with Chocolate Candy Frosting.

title: creamy chicken casserole
directions: Prepare noodles according to directions. Drain. Prepare sauce. In 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, in hot butter, cook mushrooms and onion until tender. Do not brown. Stir in remaining ingredients except macaroni and bread crumbs.
Heat thoroughly. In 2 1/2-quart baking dish, combine sauce and macaroni. Toss to coat evenly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Stir. Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Drain beans; reserve liquid.
Fry bacon pieces until crisp. Add onion to brown during last few minutes.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit and heat to dissolve the jello.
Add cheese, then add Cokes, pineapple, cherries and nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: vegetable stew
directions: In a stew pot, begin sauteing onions, garlic, potatoes and eggplant in butter.
Salt and pepper lightly.
When potatoes begin to get tender, add celery, broccoli, carrots

and Burgundy. Steam until all vegetables begin to be tender, then add zucchini, tomato paste, mushrooms, molasses and dill. Cover and simmer over low heat about 20 minutes. Correct seasoning. Serve piping hot, topped with sour cream and freshly chopped parsley.

title: shrimp-rice salad
directions: Drain shrimp and chill.
Combine rice, water chestnuts, celery, olives and onions in a large bowl.
Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, soy sauce, ginger and curry powder.
Mix well.
Pour over rice mixture and mix well.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Fold in shrimp.
Serve on lettuce and garnish with tomato wedges.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients together, except soda.
Add dry ingredients to pecans.
Add soda to buttermilk and eggs.
Add this to creamed mixture.
Now add flour. Blend well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Yields 3 small or 2 large loaves.
Bake in 9 x 7 x 3-inch large pans or 6 x 3 x 3-inch small pans.

title: taco seasoning
directions: Mix together. Store in air tight container. Add 2 tablespoons to 1 pound of hamburger. Can also use a couple of squirts of ketchup while mixing with burger.

title: curds and whey(dravle)
directions: Heat sweet milk until it comes to a boil.
Beat eggs into the buttermilk and add slowly to the hot milk.
When cheese settles, turn down heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Turn heat up and cook 1/2 hour or more.
Add sugar and raisins.
Thicken with cornstarch mixed with cream or milk.
When cooking, handle very gently so as not to break the cheese curds.
Use a wooden spoon to stir.
You may turn cheese chunks gently several times while cooking.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Chop first 4 ingredients.
Pour melted butter over and set aside.
Combine rest of ingredients, then pour chopped mixture in.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, then reduce heat to 250° and bake 1 1/2 hours longer (2 hours total baking time).

title: meat and potato pie
directions: Combine meat, green pepper, onion, egg, bread crumbs and seasoning.
Mix lightly.
Press meat mixture onto bottom and side of a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Drain excess fat from meat shell.
Mash hot potatoes with milk and butter. Stir in cheese and parsley.
Fill hot meat shell with potato mixture.
Continue baking 15 minutes more.

title: grilled swordfish steaks with pesto
directions: Baste fish with pesto sauce.
Grill 10 minutes total per inch of thickness, approximately 5 minutes per side.

title: aunt bea's favorite pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put batter in your favorite cake pan.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Add vinegar over soda, set aside.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs together.
Make paste with food coloring and cocoa.
Then add to cream mixture.
Then add flour, vanilla, salt and buttermilk. Mix well.
Fold in vinegar and soda mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple pecan dessert
directions: Mix pie filling, water and nutmeg.
Pour into greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Top with biscuits. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: ham viennese with rice
directions: While rice is cooking, saute ham in butter for 2 minutes (use a large skillet).
Add onions and celery.
Continue cooking until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Stir in soup, mustard and dill weed; heat thoroughly.
Add sour cream, just heat through, do not boil. Serve over a bed of fluffy rice.

title: cherry clafouti
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease an 8-inch square baking pan or 9-inch deep dish pie plate.
Drain canned fruit, reserving 1/2 cup syrup.
If the fruit is large pieces, cut it into pieces the size of cherries.
Put the flour, sugar, cornmeal, baking powder and cinnamon into a bowl.
In a separate bowl, lightly beat eggs. Stir them and reserved fruit syrup into flour mixture.
Stir in chopped fruit.
Pour batter into prepared pan and bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve hot sprinkled with confectioners sugar.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Stir in applesauce, flour, soda and vanilla.
Beat at low speed.
Add raisins and nuts.
Mix well. Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° until done.

title: supreme chocolate cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine.
Press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Combine cream cheese and milk, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Blend in chocolate and vanilla; pour over crust.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Loosen cake from rim of pan.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Heat last 4 ingredients to dissolve sugar.
Cook sauerkraut 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and drain juice.
Pour heated mixture over all.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: million dollar pie(will make 2 pies)
directions: Cook and cool pie crusts and set aside.
Combine first 6 ingredients.
Fill pie crusts and refrigerate 1 hour before serving.
Enjoy.

title: honey-baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange chicken pieces in shallow baking pan, skin-side up.
Combine margarine, honey, mustard, salt and curry powder, and pour over the chicken.
Bake 1 1/4 hours, basting every 15 minutes, until chicken is tender and nicely browned.
Good served with rice.

title: lime-pear jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot juice and water.
Blend in blender the pears, cream cheese and hot Jell-O.
Cool and add 1/2 large carton Cool Whip.
Makes 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: In a bowl, combine lima beans, soup, celery and milk.
Pour in a greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer or until the bread crumbs are lightly browned.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9-inch pie plate.
Mix baking mix, milk, sesame seed and egg.
Beat vigorously 30 strokes. Spread in bottom and sides of pie plate (do not spread onto rim). Cook and stir beef until brown; drain.
Mix in pepper and tomato sauce.
Heat to boiling and reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Spoon into pie plate.
Top with onions; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until crust is golden brown and cheese is bubbly, about 20 minutes.
Cut into wedges and serve.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Combine chicken, pimento, pepper, onion and mushrooms. Add broth, soup, salt and pepper.
Mix. Add 2 cups Cheddar cheese and spaghetti. Bake at 350° in 9 x 13 pan for 1 hour.

title: gourmet corn bread
directions: Whip together oil and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch square pan. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes. This can be frozen ahead (uncooked). Grease pan.

title: pork stew with olives and green beans
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons olive oil in Dutch oven over medium-high heat.
Season pork with salt and pepper.
Add pork to pot and cook until brown, stirring occasionally, using slotted spoon.
Transfer pork to plate.
Add remaining 2 tablespoons olive oil to pot.
Add onions and saute until tender.
Add garlic and cook for 3 minutes. Return pork to pot.
Add tomatoes with juices, chicken broth, white wine and spices.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, about 1 hour. Add olives and cook 45 minutes.
Add green beans, cook until tender, about 8 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: fruity frappe
directions: Place prepared drink mix, yogurt and fruit in a blender. Blend on high speed until smooth. Serve immediately.

title: chicken cashew noodles
directions: Cover bottom of a 9 x 13 inch baking dish with 1 can of noodles.
Mix together cubed chicken, celery, green onion, chicken soup and milk.
Spoon over noodles and cover with 1 can of noodles and cashews.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sauce for meatballs
directions: Mix together and serve over meatballs.

title: cheese stuffed celery
directions: Combine cheese, water, green pepper and pimento.
Fill crisp celery ribs with a knife.
Serve chilled as an appetizer or salad accompaniment.

title: divinity fudge
directions: `Boil sugar, water and salt to hard boil stage.
Place Marshmallow Creme in bowl.
Pour boiling mixture over Marshmallow Creme, beating until slightly stiff.
Fold in nuts and vanilla. Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper or pour into oblong pan.
Cut into squares.

title: chow fresh cabbage
directions: In Advance:
Shred cabbage.
Dissolve cornstarch in 2 tablespoons of chicken broth and add m.s.g., sugar and pepper. Arrange ingredients on a tray in the order in which they will be used.

title: drop noodles(spaetzle)
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Beat together egg and water. Add flour mixture; stir until smooth (batter should be very thick).
Bring to a boil 2 quarts water and 2 teaspoon salt. Spoon batter into boiling water by 1/2 teaspoon, dipping spoon into water each time.
Cook only one layer of noodles at a time. After noodles rise to the surface, boil gently for 5 to 8 minutes. Remove from water and place in warm bowl.
Toss with melted butter or serve with gravy.

title: easy chicken enchiladas
directions: Cut up chicken in small pieces.
In large bowl, combine all cans.
In large baking dish, spread cut up chicken.
Cut tortilla in strips and lay on top of chicken.
Pour soup mixture over all and soak tortillas thoroughly for 1 hour.
Cover with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated.

title: pecan pies
directions: Mix sugar, flour and syrup.
Add butter, then well beaten eggs. Add pecans and flavoring.
Pour into unbaked pie shells and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: crisp dill slices
directions: Cut pickles in crosswise slices.
Cover with brown sugar in bowl.
Cover bowl and refrigerate 24 hours before eating.
Pickles get very crisp and crunchy when mellow.

title: enchiladas
directions: Cook onion, green pepper and garlic in butter until soft.
Add flour, salt and chili powder; stir until smooth.
Add tomatoes and meat stock or water.
Cook until thick and smooth, about 5 minutes.
Strain if desired (reserve vegetables).
Makes 3 cups.

title: mushroom sauce
directions: Wash, slice and cook mushrooms until tender.
Drain.
Cook flour and butter together until brown.
Add stock, onion and bay leaf.
Cook about 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove onion and bay leaf.
Add mushrooms.
Add salt and pepper to taste and reheat.

title: glazed carrots
directions: About 25 minutes before serving:
Put carrots and salt in medium saucepan over medium heat in 1 inch boiling water.
Cook for 15 minutes, or until tender but still firm.
Drain.
Add butter, sugar and nutmeg.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until carrots are glazed.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together over low heat.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Put marshmallows on top of done cake.
Over low heat, mix the confectioners sugar, milk, cocoa, butter and vanilla.
Stir well.
Pour over the top of the marshmallows.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix and pour in buttered casserole. Place boneless chicken breast pieces on top.
Sprinkle 1 package Lipton dry onion soup mix on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: 1936 caramel frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large saucepan.
Bring slowly to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Boil hard for 2 minutes (2 1/2 minutes on a rainy day).
Cool to lukewarm.
Add vanilla and beat until creamy.

title: chilean sea bass
directions: Rinse bass in cold water and pat dry with paper towels. Lightly season fish with salt and pepper; coat with flour.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add fish and cook until lightly browned, about 1 minute per side.
Transfer to plate; set aside.
Add onion and garlic to skillet and cook about 1 to 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes, lemon juice, bay leaves, rosemary, oregano and coriander; cook on high for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add fish and gently press into tomato mixture.
Cover and cook over medium heat until fish is no longer opaque in center, 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove bay leaves and serve with rice.

title: spam salad
directions: Grate Spam in large mixing bowl; add chopped vegetables. Season to taste. Mix in enough salad dressing to desired consistency for spreading on favorite bread for sandwiches or serve with favorite crackers. If serving with crackers, I sprinkle top with paprika and slice green olives on top as a garnish.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix flour with sugar, salt, and beaten egg yolks.
Stir in milk a little at a time so the mixture won't be lumpy.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat, add butter and vanilla, cool.
Beat egg whites until foamy, add sugar gradually and beat until stiff, but not dry.
Pour over cooled filling into shell.
Cover with meringue and bake at 325-350 degrees until golden brown.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Grind first four ingredients together and let stand overnight in 1 cup of salt.
Drain off as much juice as possible.
Add remaining ingredients from brown sugar on.
Boil until thick.
It must be stirred often to keep it from sticking or burning. Stirring also helps juices evaporate.
Place in sterilized jars and seal.

title: pralines
directions: Cook together until syrup forms a soft ball when tested in cold water.
Remove from stove and add 1 1/2 cups pecans, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 tablespoon butter.
Beat until mixture begins to hold shape.
Drop by spoon on wax paper that has been sprinkled generously with salt.

title: tater tot and ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onion in skillet, stirring until ground beef is crumbly; drain.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine soup and milk in bowl; mix well.
Fold in green beans.
Stir in ground beef mixture.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with French fried onions.
Arrange single layer of Tater Tots over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: out of this world chocolate pie
directions: Place chocolate bar in top of double boiler and melt over hot, not boiling, water.
Stir occasionally until fully melted.
Remove from bottom of boiler and let stand until slightly cooled. Simply fold the Cool Whip into the chocolate gently, but fully.
Pour into pie shell.
Place in refrigerator for several hours before serving.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Bake about 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chicken and rice salad
directions: Cook rice (Minute rice will do).
Stir in mayonnaise, celery, green onions and cauliflower (flowerets broken into small pieces), then stir in chicken and salt and pepper to taste.
Chill before serving.
May need to add a little more mayonnaise if it appears too dry.

title: new england dinner
directions: Place carrots, onion and celery in a 5-quart slow cooker. Place the roast on top; sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.

Add soup mix, water, vinegar and bay leaf. Cover and cook on low for 7 to 9 hours or until beef is tender. Remove beef and keep warm; discard the bay leaf. Add cabbage. Cover and cook on high for 30 to 40 minutes or until cabbage is tender. Meanwhile, melt butter in a small saucepan; stir in flour and minced onion. Add 1 1/2 cups cooking liquid from the slow cooker. Stir in horseradish and remaining salt; bring to a boil. Cook and stir over low heat until thick and smooth, about 2 minutes. Serve with roast and vegetables.

title: hollywood potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in their jacket until tender.
While still hot, peel and roll each in melted butter, then in grated cheese.
Place in well buttered shallow baking dish and heat under broiler until lightly browned.

title: apricot-glazed cornish hens
directions: Mix apricot preserves and orange juice in small bowl.
Remove giblets from hens.
Place hens on rack in roasting pan; sprinkle lightly with salt and paprika.
Roast hens in preheated 350° oven until thickest parts are fork tender and drumstick meat feels soft when pressed, 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Baste frequently with sauce during last 30 minutes of cooking time.
Saute green onions in 2 tablespoons margarine in medium saucepan until tender, about 2 minutes.
Stir in rice; cook according to package directions, substituting chicken broth for water and omitting salt.
Stir parsley into rice.
Saute cashews in 2 tablespoons margarine in medium skillet until golden, about 2 minutes; stir into rice. Spoon rice onto serving platter; arrange hens on rice and serve.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook the chicken breast and then shred it; cook the chilies. Crush the chilies and then put a little salt in the chilies to taste. Fill the tortillas with chilies, the chicken and chopped onion; fold the enchilada over. Put sour cream and cheese on top. Heat in the oven briefly or heat in the microwave, if needed.

title: albacore tuna fettucine
directions: In a large pot of boiling water. cook broccoli until tender-crisp.
Remove with a slotted spoon to serving bowl.
Add fettucine to same pot of boiling water and cook until tender. Drain and add to broccoli.
Stir in albacore tuna.
In same pot, combine remaining ingredients, stirring until sauce is smooth and heated through.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Pour over pasta
mixture and toss.

title: herbed pot roast
directions: Dredge
roast
in
flour
and brown in vegetable oil in Dutch oven.
Place onion slices on top.
Combine sherry, water and catsup and all herbs.
Pour over roast.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add potatoes and carrots and cook 1/2 hour more
or until vegetables are tender.
Serve with liquid over beef.
Smells so good; you can't wait to eat!

title: baked ham
directions: Have the butcher slice the ham in dinner slices before the purchase.

title: spicy beef
directions: Cook meat, onion and garlic.
Add rest of ingredients except cheese and chips.
Simmer for 30 minutes. Serve over chips with cheese on top or stir together and serve immediately.

title: crab canapes
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well and spread over muffin halves. Cut each in 4 sections; place on cookie sheet and freeze.
Store in plastic container or bag up to 4 weeks, until ready to use. Place canapes under broiler and heat until lightly brown and bubbly.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let the cheeses set out at room temperature to soften.
Mix the 3 cheeses with Worcestershire sauce, salt and onion flakes thoroughly.
Combine minced pecans and parsley together.
Add half of this mixture to the cheese mixture; chill.
Shape into a ball after chilling, then roll in remaining parsley and pecan mixture.

title: cinnamon candy
directions: Cook to hard crack; take off fire.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon oil.
Stir very well. Pour into molds.
Let cool.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine and simmer until margarine melts.
Good with chops, ribs, roast and chicken.

title: savory pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into strips and coat with mixture of flour, salt and pepper. Brown strips in oil in large skillet.
Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid.
